<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="1"><PB N="31">
<HEAD>The firste chapitle //</HEAD>
<P>&para; &THORN;e .iij. techinge is of difference of woundis &amp; of general|curis / We schulen undrestonde &thorn;at wounde, &amp; old wounde, festre|&amp; cankre woundid, &amp; boon out of ioynte, &amp; a boon to-broken, &amp;|apostyme, alle &thorn;ese ben clepid vndoynge of &thorn;at &thorn;at is hool.  &amp; alle|&thorn;ese sijknessis, &amp; many oon o&thorn;ir as weel, moun falle to consimile|membris as to official membris / vulnus is a newe wounde / vlcus is|an old rotid wounde. <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="15a">I schal tellen in her placis &thorn;e difference of |festre &amp; cankre &amp; apostyme; plage comounly is taken for an oold|wounde, &amp; ofte tymes we fynde &thorn;at an old wounde is clepid vulnus,|as ypocras sei&thorn; / vulnera anua necesse est in eis os taliefieri<NOTE PLACE="foot">Read <I>tabefieri</I>.</NOTE> &amp; cicatrices|concauas fieri: &thorn;at is to seie, it is nedful<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>it is nedful</I> in margin.</NOTE> &thorn;at &thorn;e boon in an|oold wounde to be rotid &amp; &thorn;e cicatrices to be holow&yogh; / Cicatrice is &thorn;e|place of &thorn;e schynboon<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>schynboon</I>, read <I>schyn above</I>.  See below.</NOTE> &thorn;e wounde, whanne &thorn;at it is hool / Summe|woundis ben symple, &amp; summe compound / in two maner he is|clepid a symple wounde / oon maner, for he ha&thorn; not lost of fleisch /|ano&thorn;er maner for he ha&thorn; noon o&thorn;ir sijknesse wi&thorn; him, ne is nou&yogh;t|distemperid / A wounde compound is clepid contrarie to him &thorn;at is|symple / but bo&thorn;e symple &amp; compoundis sumtyme is in &thorn;e fleisch or
<PB N="32">|in &thorn;e senewe, or in &thorn;e boon, or in &thorn;e veynes, or in &thorn;e arterie / also &thorn;ese|woundis han dyuers cause.  Summe comen fro wi&thorn;inne of &thorn;e malice,|ei&thorn;er of to greet multitude of humouris.  *[forto gret multitude of|humores] o&thorn;irwhile tobreki&thorn; &thorn;e membre &amp; wi&thorn;holdi&thorn; &amp; woundi&thorn;|him / Cold matere streyne&thorn;, drie mater kutti&thorn;, moisture wi&thorn;oute| mater maki&thorn; no wounde, but selden with <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="15b">mater, but he drawe &thorn;e|lyme to brode. &amp; also &thorn;e cause wi&thorn;oute<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>The cause wi&thorn;oute</I>, causa exterior.</NOTE> mai be dyuers o&thorn;irwhile|wi&thorn; a swerd ei&thorn;ir wi&thorn; a &thorn;ing &thorn;at kutti&thorn; along, o&thorn;er while wi&thorn; a knyf|or wi&thorn; a spere or an arowe &thorn;at pricki&thorn;, &amp; summe ben maad wi&thorn; a staf|or wi&thorn; a stoon ei&thorn;ir wi&thorn; fallynge, &amp; summe ben maad wi&thorn; bitynge of|an hound ou&thorn;ir a wood hound; &amp; alle &thorn;ese ben diuers aftir &thorn;e dyuersite|of her causis; &amp; also &thorn;e maner of helynge is dyuers / Al &thorn;e intencioun|of helynge of woundis is for to sowden or to helen &amp; to restoren|&thorn;at, &thorn;at is departid, &thorn;e which &thorn;at mai not oueral be doon / for if|&thorn;at membris of office ben kutt of, &thorn;ei moun neuere be restorid, ne|noon of &thorn;e consimile membris mai be restorid, if he be doon awey:|as boonis, pelliculis, gristlis, ligamentis &amp; skyn / For &thorn;e cause of|her generacioun is &thorn;e sperme of &thorn;e fadir &amp; of &thorn;e modir, as I tolde|tofore / but in place of &thorn;ing &thorn;at is I-lore, kynde restori&thorn; &thorn;at, &thorn;at is|moost conuenient to &thorn;e place; but fleisch mai be restorid bi cause
<PB N="33">|&thorn;at &thorn;e blood is engendrid al day in us, &amp; &thorn;e blood is &thorn;e mater of &thorn;e|fleisch / &amp; summe seien &thorn;at veynes, arteries, &amp; senewis my&yogh;t not be|restorid as &thorn;ei weren tofore; but &thorn;ei moun <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="16a">be restorid as boonys |ben / But Galion and Auicen &amp; I &thorn;at am expert here seiynge,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>I &thorn;at am expert here seiynge</I>.  Lat.: ego qui sum expertus eorum|dicta.</NOTE>|we<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>we</I>, added above line.</NOTE> seie &thorn;at &thorn;ei moun be restorid wi&thorn; veri consolidacioun, whanne|&thorn;at her kuttynge is litil, &amp; whanne &thorn;at &thorn;e senewis &thorn;at ben newe|kutt &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&amp;</I>, mistake for <I>ben.</I></NOTE> soude a&yogh;en; but &thorn;ei moun not be consoudid, whanne &thorn;at|her kuttynge is myche &amp; greet; &amp; resoun graunti&thorn; it / Senewis bi|kynde ben neische &amp; viscouse; &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei moun<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>not</I>, erroneously added above line.</NOTE> ben consoudid,|&amp; &thorn;e veynes &amp; &thorn;e arteries moun be consoudid bi resoun of &thorn;e blood|&thorn;at is in hem.  I &thorn;enke to ordeyne ech chapitle bi him-silf after|&thorn;e dyuersite of lymes &amp; of placis, &thorn;e whiche &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben maad|ynne / &amp; I wole bigynne at a symple wounde maad in fleisch /</P>
</DIV4>
<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="2">
<HEAD>&thorn;e secunde chapitle of &thorn;e &thorn;ridde techinge /</HEAD>
<P>Now we wolen trete of a wounde maad in fleisch.  We wolen|bigynne at a symple wounde maad wi&thorn; knyf or wi&thorn;|swerd, or spere or arowe, or wi&thorn; ony o&thorn;ir &thorn;ing semblablele to hem.
<PB N="34">|Bynde togideris &thorn;ilke wounde with a boond &thorn;at closi&thorn; &thorn;e wounde|togideris, &amp; kepe &thorn;ilke wounde from swellynge wi&thorn; &thorn;e whi&yogh;t of an ey|leid aboue &thorn;e wounde, &amp; lete &thorn;e wounde be in reste; &amp; &thorn;er nedi&thorn; noon| o&thorn;er cure, namely, <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="16b">whanne &thorn;e wounde is wi&thorn;oute akynge; but, &amp; &thorn;er|be in &thorn;e wounde greet akynge, &thorn;anne it is a tokene, &thorn;at &thorn;er is a senewe|prickid vndir &thorn;e wounde, ei&thorn;er a pannicle &thorn;at is bitwene &thorn;e fleisch and|&thorn;e boon; &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;er is ano&thorn;er cure, as I schal telle in &thorn;e chapitle|of puncture of a senewe. &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at</I>, scribal insertion.</NOTE> I haue heelid a man &thorn;at was *[sefenty|&yogh;ere olde &thorn;at was] smyte wi&thorn; a spere &thorn;oru&yogh; &thorn;e fleisch of &thorn;e buttoke,|bi &thorn;e lenk&thorn;e of a fote, *[&amp; more] but &thorn;ilke wounde touchide no|senewe, &amp; &thorn;at I wiste sikirliche, for he hadde noon akynge / I heeld|&thorn;e wounde open aldai wi&thorn; a litil smal tent &amp; a schort, &thorn;at I my&yogh;te|wite, if &thorn;at he schulde aken on &thorn;e morowe, &amp; I comaundide him to|reste / &amp; on &thorn;e morowe I foond noon inflacioun ne akynge; &amp; &thorn;anne|I took awey &thorn;e tent &amp; lete &thorn;e wounde closen, &amp; so comaundide I|him to reste &thorn;e secunde dai / In &thorn;e &thorn;ridde day he was hool. &amp; if a|wounde were maad wi&thorn; a swerd or wi&thorn; ony &thorn;ing &thorn;at biti&thorn; in lenk&thorn;e,|anoon &thorn;ou must loke if &thorn;e wounde be so litil &thorn;at he nede no sowynge,|&amp; &thorn;anne brynge &thorn;e parties of &thorn;e wounde togideris, &thorn;at it may|be weel ioyned, &amp; leie aboue &thorn;e wounde a poundir maad oon partie
<PB N="35">|of frankencense, &amp; of two parties<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="17a"> of sandragoun,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Sandragoun</I>. Sanguis draconis: the gum of the Dragon-tree. Kersey. 1706.|See Notes.</NOTE> &amp; of &thorn;re parties |of quyk lym, &amp; lete nou&yogh;t &thorn;e poudre entre bitwene in &thorn;e wounde|but aboue, for &thorn;er schal no &thorn;ing entre in &thorn;e wounde, &amp; kepe &thorn;e|parties of &thorn;e wounde &thorn;at ben brou&yogh;t togidere wi&thorn; a plumaciol<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Plumaceoli</I>: Bolsters used by Surgeons.  Kersey.  1706.</NOTE> .iij.|cornered maad of herdis or of towe in &thorn;is maner: <FIGURE></FIGURE> oon bi &thorn;e|sidis of &thorn;e wounde, so &thorn;at bo&thorn;e &thorn;ilke plumaciols holde &thorn;e wounde &thorn;us|iclosed<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>iclosed</I>, inserted in margin.</NOTE>: <FIGURE></FIGURE> &amp; ioyned togidere as it was ioyned arst, or|it were kutt / &amp; bynde &thorn;e wounde togidere aboue &thorn;e plumaciols wi&thorn;|a rolle &thorn;at goi&thorn; ouer&thorn;wert aftir &thorn;is lettre .X. &amp; take a lynnen cloo&thorn;|&amp; wete him in two parties of &thorn;e white of an ey, in oon partie of|oile of rosis, &thorn;ei ben togidere medlid, undir &thorn;e plumaciols, leid aboue|&thorn;e wounde &thorn;at is brou&yogh;t togidere, for to kepe &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>wounde</I>, cancelled.</NOTE> poudre; &amp; do|nou&yogh;t awey &thorn;i medicyn til .iiij. daies ben goon, but if &thorn;at &thorn;e|wounde ake or be to-swollen. &amp; &thorn;anne bynde &thorn;e wounde as it was|biforn wi&thorn; &thorn;e white of an ey; oile, poudre, &amp; plumaciols.  But if|&thorn;e wounde were so myche, &thorn;at byndynge wolde nou&yogh;t suffice, or were|kutt ouer&thorn;wert ouer &thorn;e lyme, so &thorn;at &thorn;e parties of &thorn;e lyme my&yogh;t nou&yogh;t|wel be <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="17b">brou&yogh;t togideris, &thorn;anne sowe &thorn;e wounde on &thorn;is maner / Ioyne|&thorn;e lippis of &thorn;e wounde, &amp; be war &thorn;at noon oile *[ne dust] ne no |&thorn;ing ellis, &thorn;at letti&thorn; consolidacioun, falle bitwene &thorn;e lippis of &thorn;e
<PB N="36">|wounde, &amp; haue a nedle &thorn;re cornerid, whos i&yogh;e schal be holid on|bo&thorn;e sidis, so &thorn;at &thorn;e &thorn;red &thorn;at is in &thorn;e nedle may lie in &thorn;e holow&yogh;|place, &amp; &thorn;ilke &thorn;red schal be twyned, &amp; wi&thorn;oute knotte, &amp; I-wexid,|&amp; &thorn;e lippis of &thorn;e wounde schal be sowid togideris; &amp; &thorn;e &thorn;red schal|be knytt wi&thorn; two knottis in &thorn;e firste place, &amp; in &thorn;e secunde place|wi&thorn; oon knotte; &amp; so make as manye poyntis, as it is nessessarie,|&amp; ech poynt schal be from o&thorn;ir bi &thorn;e brede of a litil fyngir, &amp;|streyne &thorn;e wounde with knottynge &amp; &thorn;e sewynge of &thorn;e lippis of &thorn;e|wounde togidere &thorn;at he ake sumwhat, but nou&yogh;t to myche. &amp; if &thorn;at|&thorn;er nede mo poyntis to be &thorn;ere &thorn;an two, euermore &thorn;er schal be odde|poyntis. as .iij. v. or .vij. &amp; &thorn;e oon poynt schal be first from &thorn;e oon|eende of &thorn;e wounde, bi &thorn;e space of a litil fyngir, &amp; &thorn;e to&thorn;ir poynt|schal be at &thorn;e o&thorn;ir ende of &thorn;e wounde, &amp; &thorn;e &thorn;ridde poynt schal be|in &thorn;e myddil of &thorn;e wounde / &amp; if it be nede to haue mo poyntis,| &thorn;anne schalt &thorn;ou <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="18a">bigynne at &thorn;e myddil poynt, &amp; make as manye|poyntis on bo&thorn;e sidis as it is nede, til &thorn;ou come to bo&thorn;e eendis / For|bi &thorn;is maner of sowynge nei&thorn;ir partie schal be crokid, &amp; so &thorn;e place|mai faire be restorid, &amp; euermore take kepe &thorn;at *[&yogh;if] &thorn;e wounde be|not depe, &thorn;i sowynge schal be nou&yogh;t deep / &amp; if &thorn;i wounde be deep,|&thorn;i sowynge schal be deep, &thorn;at alle &thorn;e parties of &thorn;e wounde moun
<PB N="37">|be ioyned / For if &thorn;e wounde were deep, &amp; &thorn;i sowynge not deep,|nede &thorn;er muste be in &thorn;e dep&thorn;e of &thorn;e wounde a greet holownes, to|&thorn;e which holownes blood &amp; quyttere schulde be cast; &amp; &thorn;ilke|quyttere &amp; blood schulde lette &thorn;e helynge of &thorn;e wounde. &amp; &thorn;e|poudre &thorn;at is seid in &thorn;e same chapitle, schal be leid aboue on &thorn;e|same wounde; &amp; &thorn;ou schalt kepe &thorn;e sewynge &amp; &thorn;e parties of &thorn;e|wounde &thorn;at I brou&yogh;te togidere wi&thorn; plumaciols &thorn;re cornerid, &amp; wi&thorn;|alle &thorn;e o&thorn;ere &thorn;ingis &thorn;at ben in &thorn;is chapitle tofore seid / And if &thorn;at|a wounde ha&thorn; be to longe in &thorn;e eir open, which &thorn;at is &thorn;e cause of|quyttere &thorn;at letti&thorn; consolidacioun, &thorn;anne we musten clense &thorn;e wounde|wi&thorn; &thorn;is mundificatif &thorn;at is maad of flour of wheete &amp; hony &amp; water|&amp; mel roset, <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="18b">I-colat, &thorn;at is to seie, clensid from &thorn;e rosis, and of |barly mele / Of &thorn;ese mundificatyues &thorn;ou schalt haue a ful techinge|in &thorn;e laste tretis /</P>
<P>But if &thorn;e wounde be compound, a leche muste haue as manye|intenciouns as &thorn;er ben accidentis to &thorn;e wounde / I sette an ensaumple.|I suppose &thorn;at a wounde be compound wi&thorn; holownes &amp; lesynge of|fleisch &amp; of skyn, &amp; &thorn;ere be myche quytter, &amp; also &thorn;at &thorn;er be|apostyme, &amp; &thorn;er be a greet akynge; al &thorn;is is clepid a wounde compound|/ &thorn;anne schulen we nou&yogh;t onliche take hede to consolidacioun|of &thorn;at wounde: &thorn;at is to seie, helynge; but first we schulen aswage
<PB N="38">|ak&thorn;e &amp; apostymes, as it schal be teld in &thorn;e chapitle of an enpostyme|&amp; of akynge / Aftirward we schulen clense &thorn;e quytture, &amp; aftir &thorn;at|regenere fleisch, &amp; at &thorn;e laste brynge ouer cicatrice.  In alle &thorn;e worchingis|of medicyns, where &thorn;at ak&thorn;e is, first we schulen aswage ak&thorn;e,|for aboue al o&thorn;ir &thorn;ing strong akynge ouercome&thorn; my&yogh;t of vertu &amp;|strenk &thorn;e / &amp; also resoun telli&thorn;; membris<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat., Membra quoque dolorem habentia, dolor ipse est causa attrahendi|aliunde humorum pessimitatem.</NOTE> &thorn;at han ak&thorn;e, &thorn;ilke ak&thorn;e is|cause of drawynge from &thorn;e o&thorn;ere placis to &thorn;e membre &thorn;at aki&thorn; &thorn;e|worste <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="19a">&thorn;ing of &thorn;e humouris / Auicen sei&thorn;: humouris ben drawen| to lymes &thorn;at aken for .ij. causis: o cause, for kynde *[&amp; Spiritus|and humoures rennyth &thorn;edyre; &thorn;e secunde cause, for ak&thorn;e feblyth &thorn;e|lyme, &amp; humours] &amp; spiritis rennen to &thorn;e feble lyme / &thorn;e swellynge|schal eer be heelid &thorn;an &thorn;e wounde / Galion &amp; Auicen tellen: &thorn;at al|&thorn;ing &thorn;at consowdi&thorn; &thorn;e wounde greue&thorn; &thorn;e wounde, if &thorn;at &thorn;er be|apostyme wi&thorn; &thorn;e wounde / &amp; &thorn;e quytture schal be clensid or &thorn;ou leie|ony regeneratijf to holow&yogh; woundis.  Auicen telli&thorn; &thorn;e cause, whi|&thorn;at yuel fleisch growi&thorn; in a wounde / If &thorn;at a leche wolde bisie him|wi&thorn; a medicyn regeneratijf to regendre fleisch in a wounde, &amp; er &thorn;an|&thorn;e quytture were clensid / &amp; whanne &thorn;at &thorn;e wounde is clensid, &thorn;anne|we schulen fulfille &thorn;ilke holownes wi&thorn; fleisch or &thorn;at &thorn;e wounde be
<PB N="39">|heelid, lest perauenture<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>perauenture</I>.  See N. E. Dict., adventure, 1. b.</NOTE> &thorn;at &thorn;er dwelle an holownesse vndir &thorn;e|wounde, whanne &thorn;at he is helid, in whom &thorn;at quytture schulde be|engendrid, &thorn;erwith<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;erwi&thorn;</I>, scribal error for <I>&thorn;e which.</I></NOTE> ech dai schulde augmente &thorn;ilke holownesse, &amp;|so we moten be constreyned to opene ano&thorn;ir tyme &thorn;at, &thorn;at was|heelid tofore / &thorn;ou maist fynde in &thorn;e chapitle of woundis of senewis,|how &thorn;ou schalt aswage ak&thorn;e, &amp; in &thorn;e .vj. chapitle of &thorn;is techinge |&thorn;ou schalt fynde &thorn;e cure <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="19b">of a wounde &thorn;at ha&thorn; a swellynge, &amp; is|out of kynde distemperid; &amp; &thorn;ou schalt haue in &thorn;e chapitle of olde|woundis, how &thorn;ou schalt clense quytture &amp; regendre fleisch /</P>
</DIV4>
<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="3">
<HEAD>The &thorn;ridde techinge of &thorn;e firste tretis is of heelynge|of a wounde maad in senewe /</HEAD>
<P>Almy&yogh;ti god hath &yogh;eue to senewe greet felyng, &amp; if &thorn;at he be|hirt, he suffri&thorn; greet akynge / Galion sei&thorn;: a senewe &thorn;at is more|selynge &thorn;an ano&thorn;er *[lyme] it is nessessarie &thorn;at he haue grettere|ak&thorn;e / Vndirstonde &thorn;at a wounde &thorn;at is maad in a senewe, mai not be|wi&thorn;oute akynge.  Ne<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>no</I>, scribal error for <I>&thorn;e.</I></NOTE> woundis &thorn;at ben maad in senewis, ou&thorn;er &thorn;at|ben in lenk&thorn;e or in brede / &THORN;e woundis &thorn;at ben maad in lenk&thorn;e of|&thorn;e2 senewe, ben lesse perilous &thorn;an<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;an</I> erroneously inserted.</NOTE> &thorn;o &thorn;at ben maad in brede of &thorn;e
<PB N="40">|senewe ben moost perilous / O&thorn;erwhile a senewe is kutt al atwo / &amp;|&thorn;anne &thorn;ilke lyme, to whom &thorn;at senewe serue&thorn;, lesi&thorn; his meuynge &amp;|&thorn;e felynge, &thorn;at &thorn;ilke senewe brou&yogh;te to him from &thorn;e brain.  &amp; &thorn;ilke|senewe o&thorn;irwhile is not kutt al atwo, but he is I-preickid, &amp; &thorn;anne|it is perilous lest &thorn;e crampe come for to greet ak&thorn;e / For ak&thorn;e entri&thorn;|into &thorn;e part of &thorn;e senewe &thorn;at is kutt or prickid; &amp; bi &thorn;e <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="20a">partie| of &thorn;e senewe &thorn;at is hool, ak&thorn;e is brou&yogh;t to &thorn;e brayn.  &amp; so &thorn;e|crampe mai come to &thorn;e wounde bi oon of &thorn;re weies: &thorn;at is to greet|ak&thorn;e, cold, or rotynge.  Of &thorn;ese &thorn;re or of oon bi him-silf mai come|a drawinge togidere of a senewe &thorn;at is cause of a crampe / &amp; &thorn;at|&thorn;at is seid of a wounde of a symple senewe may fallen ofte-tymes|in a wounde of a corde &amp; a brawn, &amp; nameliche of a corde &thorn;at is in|bigynnynge of a brawn.  &THORN;o woundis &thorn;at ben in &thorn;ese &thorn;re consimile|membris, &thorn;at is *[to] seie senewe, corde, &amp; brawn han o. drede in|cours of &thorn;e crampe, &amp; also o. drede of felynge, lesynge &amp; meuynge /|&amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&amp;</I>, above line.</NOTE> &thorn;erfore be-war in &thorn;e cure of a wounde maad in senewe, whe&thorn;er|&thorn;at it be a prickynge or &thorn;at it be kutt ouer&thorn;wert, or ellis be kutt|oonly bi his lenk&thorn;e.  If oonly he be prickid &thorn;e wounde of &thorn;e skyn|is hool, &amp; &thorn;anne it is clepid a blynde puncture; ei&thorn;er &thorn;e wounde is|open, &amp; it is clepid an open puncture / In a blind puncture it is
<PB N="41">|nessessarie to opene &thorn;e skyn, &amp; aftirward heelde into &thorn;e hoole as|hoot as he mai suffre, hoot oile of rosis swete smellynge, &thorn;at is|maad of oile de oliue &thorn;at is nou&yogh;t ripe, til al &thorn;e wounde be ful.  &amp;|aboue &thorn;e wounde leie whi&yogh;t terebentine<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="20b"><NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>terebentine</I>, from Pistacia Terebinthus, L.  The <I>Alah</I> of the Old Testament,|and the <GAP DESC="Greek"> of Theophrast.: now almost obsolete.</NOTE> I-drawe abrood bitwene |two clowtis, &amp; anoynte alle &thorn;e membris aboute &thorn;e wounde wi&thorn; hoot|oile of rosis maad &thorn;icke with bool armoniak.  &amp; aftir &thorn;at leie a|lynnen cloo&thorn; I-het aboue, &amp; aftir &thorn;at a good quantite of tow I-tosid,|&amp; bynde &thorn;e lyme softliche wi&thorn;oute streynynge; &amp; if &thorn;e ak&thorn;e wi&thorn;|&thorn;is medicyn wole not ceessen, remeue &amp; chaunge &thorn;is medicyn ofte|tymes in &thorn;e dai &amp; in &thorn;e ny&yogh;t / &amp; if &thorn;e prickynge be in &thorn;e foot,|anoynte &thorn;e grynde<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e grynde</I>, inguina.  <I>W. Wr.</I>, p. 589. 39, 15th cent.: inguen, the grynde.</NOTE> wi&thorn; hoot comoun oile; &amp; vndir &thorn;e arme holis|&amp; in &thorn;e necke pitt, if &thorn;at &thorn;e prickynge be in &thorn;e hand, for &thorn;is|enoynture rarefie&thorn; &amp; euene&thorn; &thorn;e placis bi whom ak&thorn;e goi&thorn; to &thorn;e|brain, &amp; it letti&thorn; drawynge togidere of &thorn;e senewe / &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at &thorn;ou|seest nou&yogh;t &thorn;e ak&thorn;e ceesse in summen as hastiliche as &thorn;ou woldist,|neuer-&thorn;e-lattere chaunge not &thorn;i medicyn, for &thorn;er may be no bettere|medicyn.  But if &thorn;at ak&thorn;e dure ouer longe, it is not yuel to putte a|litil opium to &thorn;e oile of &thorn;e rosis &amp; &thorn;e bole armoniak, &thorn;at &thorn;ou leidist|aboute &thorn;e wounde.  &THORN;e sike man muste reste &amp; bi no wey he
<PB N="42">|schulde nou&yogh;t be wro&thorn;; his bed muste be maad soft, euene, &amp;| smo&thorn;e, &amp; &thorn;at he <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="21a">my&yogh;te haue reste / Whanne &thorn;at &thorn;e ak&thorn;e aswagi&thorn;|&amp; &thorn;e wounde &yogh;eue&thorn; sum quytture, &thorn;anne &thorn;e sike man is saaf from al|maner perel, but if he do ony newe errour / Of &thorn;is wounde Ypocras|speki&thorn;: in vulneribus malis &amp; fortibus sanie non apparante&mdash;&thorn;at|is to seie: in yuel woundis and strong woundis, if no quytture|appere it is yuel / Strong woundis ben clepid woundis &thorn;at sore|aken / Yuel woundis ben &thorn;o, to whom scharpe humouris rennen|&amp; ben nou&yogh;t obedient to kyndeli heete, to be turned into quitture|/ And &thorn;erfore Ypocras seide: &thorn;at whanne akynge &amp; quytture|appere&thorn; it is a tokene of heele / &THORN;e &thorn;ridde signe a man muste|knowe in &thorn;is place, &thorn;at lewide men, seyinge akynge &amp; swellynge|in a lyme &thorn;at is woundid, leie &thorn;erto a potage in maner maad of|eerbis &amp; swynes greece &amp; water &amp; wheete flour, corruptyn &thorn;e|lyme, &amp; &thorn;ilke corrupcioun is cause of &thorn;e crampe / For Galion sei&thorn;:|&thorn;at a senewe is maad of moist mater &amp; a cold, &amp; &thorn;erfore he|roti&thorn; of heete and moistnes / Also summen, for to aswage ak&thorn;e as<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>as</I>, error for <I>of</I>; see below.</NOTE>|a senewe &thorn;at is prickid, putti&thorn; &thorn;e lyme in hoot watir *[o&thorn;er ellys| caste it on &thorn;e lyme] &thorn;e which mater<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>mater</I>, error for watir.</NOTE> is &thorn;e moost greuaunce <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="21b">to|&thorn;e senewe / Galion sei&thorn; / Hoot watir, &thorn;ou&yogh; it aswage ak&thorn;e to &thorn;e
<PB N="43">|prickynge of a senewe is most greuaunce / Cold also greue&thorn; sore &thorn;e|senewe as wel in somer as in wyntir / And Ypocras sei&thorn; in &thorn;e .v.|part of his auforismus: cold is bitynge &amp; greuous to senewis &amp;|woundis, &amp; also in &thorn;e chapitle next folowynge, but it be in a|crampe wi&thorn;oute wounde / Galion sei&thorn; in &thorn;e eende of his coment:|coold is moost greuous to a senewy lyme &thorn;at is woundid &amp; is sore|swollen; namely, &amp; he haue &thorn;e crampe.  It schewi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>schewi&thorn;</I> for <I>sewi&thorn;</I>; see below.</NOTE> &thorn;anne &thorn;at an|hoot medicyne &amp; a drie is moost acordynge to senewis &thorn;at ben|woundid; but nou&yogh;t to hoot a medicyn, lest perauntre &thorn;at he make|&thorn;e lyme to swelle; &amp; if it be drie, nou&yogh;t wi&thorn; stipticte, an auntre if|&thorn;at he closi&thorn; &thorn;e poris of &thorn;e skyn / Galion sei&thorn;: &thorn;at it is yuele to|close &thorn;e poris of a lyme &thorn;at is pricked.  &THORN;e medicyn &thorn;anne muste|be hoot &amp; drie with subtiliate as terebentine to moiste bodies; &amp; to|drie bodies he muste be medlid wi&thorn; a litil enforbium, azafetida<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Asa f&oelig;tida</I>, a sort of gum pressed out of a certain plant, which grows|in Persia.</NOTE> is|best medicyn if &thorn;ou make of him enplastre, serapinum,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Serapinum</I> = Sagapenum ... A gum resin obtained from the Ferula|Persica.  See <I>Notes</I>.</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;e fecis<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fecis</I>, Lat. f&aelig;ces, dregs.</NOTE>|of a litil wex, &amp; &thorn;e fil&thorn;e of &thorn;e vessels of been, alle &thorn;ei ben gode to|a senewe &thorn;at is prickid, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at &thorn;ou putt <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="22a">ech of hem bi him-silf |or ellis compound / &amp; &thorn;ow schalt fynde a ful techinge of &thorn;ese|medicyns in &thorn;e antidotarie of &thorn;is book / &THORN;ou schalt nou&yogh;t close a
<PB N="44">|wounde where &thorn;at &thorn;e prickynge of a senewe is, til &thorn;at &thorn;e senewe|be perfi&yogh;tly clensid &amp; heelid, &amp; til &thorn;at &thorn;ou be sikir &thorn;at &thorn;e place|schal not swelle / Galion telli&thorn; of a man &thorn;at was prickid with a|poyntel in &thorn;e pawme of &thorn;e hand, to whom came oon of tisilies<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat., unus de secta Thessali.  Thessalus lived in Rome at the time of|Nero, and enjoys the reputation of being the first great quack.</NOTE>|clerkis &thorn;e which took hede to heele alle woundis generaliche; &amp; he|leide to &thorn;ilke prickynge a consowdynge oynement &thorn;at was more|acordynge to a wounde maad in fleisch; &amp; he leide &thorn;erto a plastre|maturatijf, wherfore al &thorn;e hand rotide &amp; he fel into a crampe, &amp;|so he diede, or &thorn;at &thorn;e .vij. daies weren passid / &amp; if &thorn;at ilke leche|hadde maad &thorn;at wounde broddere, &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;at he hadde helt into|&thorn;e wounde hoot oile of rosis, &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;at he hadde do<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat., Si .. saniem .. subtiliter desiccantibus expectasset.  Add. MS.|translates literally, abyde.  The use of <I>do</I> (= faire) is further illustrated by|M&auml;tzner.  See <I>don</I> .6.</NOTE> comen out|quytture wi&thorn; hoote medicyns sotil &amp; driynge, &amp; nou&yogh;t wi&thorn; moist|medicyns, &thorn;at man schulde not haue be deed /</P>
<P>If &thorn;at a senewe hadde ben I-kutt ouer&thorn;wert ouer al atwo &thorn;anne,|&thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at Tederious<NOTE PLACE="foot">Theodoricus, an Italian (?) monk of the 13th century, was the author|of a <I>Surgery.</I></NOTE> &amp; summe o&thorn;ere seien &thorn;e contrarie, it is good &thorn;at| &thorn;ow <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="22b">sowe togidere &thorn;e eendis of &thorn;e senewis &thorn;at ben kutt wi&thorn; &thorn;e|sowinge of &thorn;e skyn.  &amp; aboue &thorn;ilke maner of sowinge, &thorn;e firste|dai leie oile of rosis, in &thorn;e which oile, maddockis<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>maddock</I>, O.E. ma&eth;ek, Dan. maddik.  See Skeat, <I>Etym. Dict.</I>, under|maggot and mawkish.</NOTE>&mdash;&thorn;at ben wormes
<PB N="45">|of &thorn;e er&thorn;e&mdash;han be boilid, &amp; caste aboute &thorn;e wounde &thorn;e poudre &thorn;at|kepi&thorn; &thorn;e sowynge .o. day or two aftirward, &amp; kepe &thorn;e sowynge wi&thorn;|plumaciols .iij. cornerid, &amp; wi&thorn; byndynge, &amp; kepe &thorn;e lyme from|swellynge, for bi sich a maner sowynge of a senewe &thorn;ou maist consowde|&thorn;e senewe a&yogh;en; for &thorn;e lyme schulde han be lost in partie or|in al, &thorn;e meuynge &thorn;at was brou&yogh;t vnto him fro &thorn;e braun, for bi &thorn;at|senewe &thorn;e lyme mai rekeuere his felynge, &amp; so &thorn;e restoringe of &thorn;e|braun may be fastere &amp; schapliker.  &THORN;ou schalt nou&yogh;t drede of &thorn;e|akynge &thorn;att schulde be maad of prickynge<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>prickynge of &thorn;e senewe</I>.  The Latin, <I>acus punctura</I>, is correctly translated|in Add. MS.  See below.</NOTE> of &thorn;e senewe, for &thorn;e|ak&thorn;e schal be doon awei wi&thorn; oo leiynge to ei&thorn;er tweyne of &thorn;ilke|oile / Ne sich maner ak&thorn;e may nou&yogh;t make &thorn;e crampe, for &thorn;e senewe|is al kutt atwo ne no man *[make an] obieccioun wi&thorn; Galion|wordis, &thorn;at we schulden be war in ioynynge parties of a wounde|togidere *[&thorn;at non here ne oyle ne scholde no&yogh;t entre wi&thorn;ynne &thorn;e|lippes of a wounde, &thorn;at bet&thorn; y-brought togedre] To &thorn;ilke abieccioun|we answeren: &thorn;at &thorn;e stipticite <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="23a">of &thorn;e rosis &amp; &thorn;e oile &thorn;at was |nou&yogh;t ripe, &amp; &thorn;e glutinosite of &thorn;e wormes of &thorn;e er&thorn;e remeuen &thorn;e ak&thorn;e|of &thorn;e senewis &amp; al &thorn;e harm &thorn;at schulde come of &thorn;e ilke sowynge.</P>
<P>If &thorn;at a senewe were woundid in lenk&thorn;e, he mai wel &amp; li&yogh;tliche
<PB N="46">|be sowdid togidere wi&thorn; ioynynge of lippis, &amp; wi&thorn; &thorn;e sowynge &amp; wi&thorn;|&thorn;e kepinge of &thorn;e lyme &thorn;at he swelle nou&yogh;t / Vndirstonde here in|&thorn;is place: &thorn;at &thorn;er is no &thorn;ing more worschipful to a leche ne more|profitable to a sijk man &thorn;an to kepe a lyme woundid fro swellynge,|&amp; ne&thorn;eles it is hard to kepe senewis &thorn;at ben woundid from swellynge|/ Ne&thorn;eles a leche here schal take heed aftir &thorn;e techinge &thorn;at|schal be &yogh;eue him in &thorn;e chapitle of &thorn;e cure of a wounde, whanne|&thorn;at &thorn;er is wi&thorn; him a swellynge.  If &thorn;at a wounde were chaungid|of &thorn;e eyr and made quytture, &thorn;at &thorn;e sowynge were to-broke and &thorn;e|puncture were vndir,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>undir</I>, mistake for <I>undo</I>.  See below.</NOTE> &thorn;anne make a medicyne mundificatif &amp; leie|him abrood on a lynnen cloo&thorn; &amp; leie it aboue &thorn;e wounde, &amp; putte a|litil smal tent in &thorn;e eende of &thorn;e wounde &thorn;at is moost lynynge,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lynynge</I>, for <I>declynynge</I>.</NOTE> &amp;|&thorn;ilke tent schal touche no senewe ne make noon ak&thorn;e vndir<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>undir &thorn;at</I>, donec.</NOTE> &thorn;at,| &thorn;at ilke wounde be <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="23b">weel dried.  A mundificatijf medicyn of|senewis woundid is maad in &thorn;is maner: Take mel roset colat <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .iij.|smal flour of barly &amp; medle hem togidere &amp; boile hem slili &thorn;at &thorn;ei|brenne nou&yogh;t, &amp; remeue hem fro &thorn;e fier &amp; bete hem longe togidere|wi&thorn; a spature;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>spatur</I>, spatula.</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;anne putte &thorn;erto <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. of whit terebentyne;|&amp; if &thorn;ou mowe finde noon whi&yogh;t terebentyne, &thorn;anne waische o&thorn;ere
<PB N="47">|terebentyne with cold watir til it be whi&yogh;t, &amp; whane &thorn;at be &thorn;is|medicyn &thorn;is wounde is almoost drie, &thorn;anne putte in &thorn;e same medicyn|a litil poudre of frankencense mastik &amp; saundragoun, medle|hem togidere &amp; leie aboue &thorn;e wounde til it be hool / &amp; whanne &thorn;at|it is hool manye daies aftir, leie flex in good strong wiyn het hoot|til it be perfi&yogh;tli al hool, &amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;er leue ony hardnes in meuynge,|after &thorn;at it is hool, &thorn;anne &thorn;ou schalt vse &thorn;e techinge &thorn;at schal be|&yogh;ouen to &thorn;ee in &thorn;e laste tretis &thorn;at schal be antidotarie in &thorn;e chapitle|of medicyns mollificatyues; &thorn;ere &thorn;ou schalt fynde &thorn;e maner how &thorn;ou|schalt helpe best lymes &thorn;at ben heelid and moun not ri&yogh;t weel meuen /</P>
</DIV4>
<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="4">
<HEAD>&THORN;e firste<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>firste</I>, mistake for <I>fur&thorn;e</I>.</NOTE> techinge of &thorn;e firste tretis is of heelynge of|a wounde maad in boon /</HEAD>
<P>Whanne &thorn;at woundis ben so depe &thorn;at <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="24a">oonly fleisch is not |woundid but &thorn;e boon &thorn;at is vndir &thorn;e fleisch &amp; &thorn;e senewe / &thorn;anne a|man muste biholde, wher &thorn;at &thorn;e boon be kutt al atwo, as ofte-tyme|it may happe in &thorn;e boon of &thorn;e thie &amp; schene boonys &amp; &thorn;e boonys|of &thorn;e armes.  And &thorn;anne &thorn;ilke wounde is ful perilous; &amp; nameli if|&thorn;e boonys of &thorn;e thie ou&thorn;ir &thorn;e boon of &thorn;e arme from &thorn;e schuldre to|&thorn;e elbowe be kutt al atwo, so &thorn;at &thorn;e marie go out.  But ofte-tymes
<PB N="48">|oon boon of &thorn;e schene or o. boon of &thorn;e armes is kutt al atwo|ouertwert ouer &amp; ne&thorn;eles afterward may be restorid; ou&thorn;er a boon|is not kutt al atwo but sum of his substaunce is don awey, &amp; &thorn;ilke|substaunce, ou&thorn;er he is doon awey or ellis he hangi&thorn; togidere / A|general rule is in cure of woundis in whom boonys ben woundid:|&thorn;at neuere bi a leche fleisch schal ben I-sowdid aboue &thorn;e boon, but|first pleynerliche bi repeire<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>repeire</I>, erroneously for <I>repeired</I>.</NOTE>; for &thorn;e boon may neuere be<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>be</I> has to be cancelled.</NOTE> wi&thorn; verri|consolidacion be consowdid, for his mater was &thorn;e sperme of &thorn;e fadir|&amp; of &thorn;e modir; but in summe children, for &thorn;e age<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>for &thorn;e age is toward ofte tyme</I>, for, <I>for &thorn;e ny&yogh;te of tyme</I>.  See below.</NOTE> is toward ofte|tyme &thorn;at &thorn;ei were sperme / but &thorn;er schal be maad a maner of|restorynge in place of &thorn;e boon &thorn;at was broken ei&thorn;er lost, &thorn;at men|clepen <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="24b">poris sarcoides or ellis caro poroydes, &amp; a<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a</I>, above line.</NOTE> maner &thorn;ing &thorn;at is| restorid is hardere &thorn;an &thorn;e fleisch &amp; neischere &thorn;an &thorn;e boon / &amp; if &thorn;at|ilk mater &thorn;at is restorid be ny&yogh; as hard as is &thorn;e boon, it is clepid|porus sarcoides / &amp; if &thorn;at ilke mater be not hard but sumwhat|neische, it is clepid caro poroydes / &amp; if &thorn;at a neische fleisch were|&amp; a moist nou&yogh;t regenered vpon boonys &thorn;at ben sett togidere, a man|schulde not haue his purpos to heele &amp; consowde &thorn;e wounde.  Loke|&thorn;anne whe&thorn;er &thorn;e boon be kutt atwo altogidere ouer&thorn;wert ouer, &thorn;at
<PB N="49">|&thorn;ou bryngist togidere &amp; bindist &thorn;e parties of &thorn;e wounde, as it|schal be told in &thorn;e .viij. chapitle folowynge, where &thorn;ou schalt haue|how a wounde schal be heelid &thorn;at is out of ioynte I-kutt atwo &amp;|to-broken / &amp; if a wounde<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wounde</I>, erroneously for <I>boon</I>.</NOTE> be not kutt atwo al togidere ouer&thorn;wert|ouer, loke if ony pece of &thorn;e boon dwelle sadliche with &thorn;e o&thorn;ere|partie of &thorn;e hool boon / &amp; &thorn;anne if &thorn;ou my&yogh;t, brynge &thorn;ilke pece to|&thorn;e place &thorn;at he was yn tofore wi&thorn; &thorn;ristynge doun &thorn;ilke pece wi&thorn;|sum instrument acordynge &thorn;erto, &amp; sowde &thorn;ilke pece wi&thorn; &thorn;e hool|boon wi&thorn; &thorn;e poudre &thorn;at I shal telle aftirward; for so the <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="25a">schap of |&thorn;e lyme mai dwelle<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hool</I>, cancelled after <I>dwelle</I>.</NOTE> faire &amp; strengere / &amp; if &thorn;at ilke pece haue no|fastnes to &thorn;e hool boon, do &thorn;at pece awey &amp; regenere in &thorn;e place of|&thorn;e boon &thorn;at &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="foot">The second <I>&thorn;at</I> has to be cancelled.</NOTE> was lost a repeirement / For &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at ypocras &amp;|Galion tellen &thorn;at it is nessessarie after quantite of &thorn;e boon &thorn;at is|lost, an holow&yogh; cicatrise to be alwey, ne&thorn;eles wi&thorn; &thorn;is poudre &thorn;e|generacioun of &thorn;ese poris may be mendid, not a litil, but ri&yogh;t|myche / &THORN;is is &thorn;e poudre: take frank-encense, mastik, mirre, dragagantum,|gumme arabik, ana. <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij. flour of fenegrek, .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>. s' caste|&thorn;is poudre vpon &thorn;e defaute of &thorn;e boon &thorn;at is lost, til &thorn;at &thorn;ou holde|a pleynere repeirement *[&amp; a restauracioun.  &THORN;enne &amp; no&yogh;t ere|brynge ouere fflesch ouere &thorn;e repeyrment wi&thorn;] regeneratiuis, mundificatiuis
<PB N="50">|&amp; consolidatiuis aftir &thorn;e techinge &thorn;at &thorn;ou haddist biforn /|Undirstonde &thorn;at al &thorn;ing &thorn;at is seid of boonys in &thorn;is chapitle is of|alle &thorn;e boonis of &thorn;e bodi saf &thorn;e heed / I schal make a chapitle by|hym-silf //</P>
</DIV4>
<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="5">
<HEAD>The fif&thorn;e chapitle of &thorn;e &thorn;ridde techinge of &thorn;e firste|tretis of woundis &thorn;at ben maad wi&thorn; smytynge of|staf or stoon, or fallynge or smytynge of an hors,|or wi&thorn; ony o&thorn;ir &thorn;ing semblable.</HEAD>
<P>To hem happen greet difference <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="25b">fro woundis &thorn;at ben maad wi&thorn;|kuttynge, as wi&thorn; swerd, knyf, ei&thorn;ir arowe prickynge; &amp; in o&thorn;ere|maner &thorn;ei schulen ben I-heelid / For &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at verry consolidacioun|be &thorn;e firste &amp; principal entencioun of heelynge of a wounde, to &thorn;is|chapitle it acordi&thorn; nou&yogh;t, for in smytynge, &thorn;e fleisch &amp; &thorn;e veynes,|&amp; senewis, &amp; arteries ben brusid, for in &thorn;e ynnere part of &thorn;e lyme|&thorn;e boon a&yogh;enstondi&thorn;, &amp; on &thorn;e ouer part <NOTE PLACE="foot">The passage is corrupt; the correct version is given by Add. MS.: <I>&thorn;e|&thorn;ynge &thorn;at smyte&thorn; &amp; kutte&thorn; no&yogh;t.</I></NOTE>of &thorn;e &thorn;ing &thorn;at is smyten|knytti&thorn; nou&yogh;t / Wherfore it is nessessarie, if &thorn;er schulde be a|wounde, &thorn;at alle &thorn;e smale lymes &thorn;at ben bitwene &thorn;e boon &amp; &thorn;e &thorn;ing
<PB N="51">|&thorn;at smyti&thorn;, schulde be brusid, &amp; o&thorn;erwhile &thorn;e fleisch &amp; &thorn;e o&thorn;ere|consimile membris ben brusid wi&thorn;oute wounde / Wherfore &thorn;e curis of|bo&thorn;e I wole ordeyne in &thorn;is chapitle.  If &thorn;at a leche wolde enforse|him to ioyne togidere wi&thorn; consolidatiuis &thorn;e wounde &thorn;at is maad wi&thorn;|smytynge, nedis quytture &amp; corrupcioun bi &thorn;ilke consolidatif muste|be vnder &thorn;e wounde; &thorn;e which quytture schulde corrupte &thorn;ilke lyme|&amp; brynge him to putrifaccioun, but if &thorn;at kynde were so my&yogh;ty,|&thorn;at he my&yogh;te eftsoone opene &thorn;ilke wounde, &thorn;at was consowdid bi a|sori leche<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bi a sori leche</I>, a malo medico.  See Halliwell, <I>Dict</I>., sorry Laten.</NOTE>; or wi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wi&thorn;</I>, mistake for <I>&thorn;at.</I></NOTE> a good leche come &amp; knowe &thorn;ilke disposicioun<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="26a"> |&amp; knowe helpe, wi&thorn; propre eir<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>eir</I>, read <I>cur</I>.</NOTE> to rectifien &thorn;e corrupcioun of &thorn;ilke|lyme / What schalt &thorn;ou &thorn;anne do?  &THORN;ou muste loke whe&thorn;er &thorn;at &thorn;e|bodi be ful of wickide humouris, ei&thorn;er be clene; if &thorn;at he be ful|late him blood, if alle particuler &thorn;ingis acorden, as vertu, age, conplexioun|&amp; consuetude; &amp; &thorn;ese &thorn;ingis moten alwey<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>be</I> wanted after <I>alwey</I>.</NOTE> taken in|mynde, &thorn;ou&yogh; alwey &thorn;ei be not I-nempned &amp; namely vertu; &amp; he be|not strong &amp; alle o&thorn;ere &thorn;ingis acorden, &thorn;ou schalt not lete blood, but|&thorn;ou maist ventosen, if &thorn;at it be nessessarie, or ellis [lose] *&thorn;e wombe|if &thorn;at he be costif<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>costif</I>, costive, subject to be bound in body.&mdash;Kersey.</NOTE>; &amp; if &thorn;at he be feble, &amp; &thorn;e brosure were in &thorn;e|ouer parti of &thorn;e bodi, voide &thorn;e fecis of his wombe bi clisterie.  &amp;
<PB N="52">|if &thorn;ou wolt lete blood, &thorn;ou schalt lete blood on &thorn;e contrarie partie|of &thorn;e veyne, bryngyng norischinge to &thorn;e lyme &thorn;at was hirt; &amp; &thorn;ilke|veyne &thorn;ou schalt knowe, if &thorn;at &thorn;ou knowist pleynerliche anotamie,|&thorn;at I haue tau&yogh;t &thorn;ee in &thorn;is same book / &amp; whanne &thorn;at &thorn;e bodi is|clensid, if &thorn;at &thorn;e brosour be wi&thorn;oute &thorn;e wounde, anoynte &thorn;e membre|&thorn;at is brosid, which bigynne&thorn; to haue an enpostym, with hoot oile|of rosis, &amp; caste aboue a poudre maad of &thorn;e seed of mirtilles, &amp;| bynde it softly; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="26b">for ofte-tymes it nedi&thorn; noon o&thorn;er eir<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>eir</I>, read <I>cur</I>.</NOTE> / For &thorn;is|medicyn fastne&thorn; &thorn;e place, &amp; defendi&thorn; him fro putrefaccioun.  &amp;|&thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at &thorn;is medicyn mowe not letten al &thorn;e mater from rotynge,|ne&thorn;eles it defendi&thorn; myche of &thorn;e same mater fro rotynge / &amp; if al &thorn;e|mater mai not be defendid from putrifaccioun, but sum partie &thorn;erof|putrifie&thorn;, opene &thorn;e place &amp; exclude &thorn;e quytture, &amp; clense al &thorn;e place.|&amp; his cure schal be seid in &thorn;e chapitle of apostymes<NOTE PLACE="foot">Latin, <I>de apostematibus exituris</I>, apostems which discharge pus.</NOTE> &amp; of exitours /|But if<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>if</I>, above line.</NOTE> &thorn;at a brusour were wi&thorn; a wounde, anoynte aboute &thorn;e|wounde or ellis &thorn;e place &thorn;at is brusid wi&thorn; &thorn;e forseid oile of rosis, &amp;|caste aboue &thorn;e forseid poudre of mirtilles, for it fastne&thorn; &thorn;e place,|ne it letti&thorn; nou&yogh;t &thorn;e corrupcioun to spreden ei&thorn;er to be drawen|abrood; &amp; it casti&thorn; to &thorn;e wounde &thorn;e corrupt mater &thorn;at is in &thorn;e
<PB N="53">|place &thorn;at is brusid / Wi&thorn;inne &thorn;e wounde leie &thorn;e &yogh;elke of an ey, wi&thorn;|oile of rosis, with stupis, or ellis wi&thorn; lint.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lint.  Prompt. Parv.</I>, schauynge of lynnen clothe.</NOTE>  Leid<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>leid</I>, mistake for <I>leie</I>.</NOTE> aboue &thorn;e|wounde a potage maad of .iiij parties of watir &amp; oon partie of|oile de olyue, &amp; flour of wheete &thorn;at suffici&thorn; to &thorn;e medicyn, &amp; leie|&thorn;is medicyn to &thorn;e wounde, til &thorn;at &thorn;e ak&thorn;e be aswagid, &amp; til &thorn;at &thorn;e|quytture be engendrid; aftirward clense <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="27a">&thorn;e wounde, aftir &thorn;e |clensynge regenerer, &amp; at &thorn;e laste cicatrice.  &amp; &thorn;ou schalt haue a|ful techinge in &thorn;e antidotarie of mundificatiuis &amp; cicatri&yogh;atiuis /|But if &thorn;e membre &thorn;at was brusid be ful of senewis, as &thorn;e hand|ou&thorn;er &thorn;e foot, &thorn;ou schalt not chaunge &thorn;i cure if &thorn;at &thorn;er be no|wounde; but &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;er be a brusour in senewy membre I-woundid,|leie not &thorn;ere &thorn;e potage tofore seid, but oonly hoot oile of rosis, &amp;|aboue &thorn;e oile poudre of mirtillis, &amp; aboue &thorn;e wounde leie terebentine|I-waischen &amp; drawen abrood bitwene two lynnen cloo&thorn;is.  &amp; make|a plastre of pich &amp; hony &amp; bene flour, &amp; leie aboute &thorn;e lyme &thorn;at|is ful of senewis, as &thorn;e hand, &thorn;e foot, &amp; speciali whanne &thorn;e flux of|humouris ceessen not / &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at &thorn;i cure be drawe along, ne go|not awei from &thorn;is cure / &amp; whanne &thorn;at al &thorn;e ak&thorn;e is ceessid and &thorn;e|swellynge is aswagid, for to clense &thorn;e wounde, vse &thorn;e medicyn of|mel roset colath with barly mele, seid in &thorn;e wounde of senewis /
<PB N="54">|&THORN;is cure is apreued bi galion, &amp; I haue preued &thorn;is medicyn ofte|tymes /</P>
</DIV4>
<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="6">
<HEAD>&para; &THORN;e sixte chapitle of &thorn;e &thorn;ridde techinge is of woundis|&thorn;at han enpostymes &amp; be distempered //</HEAD>
<HEAD>Off woundes Impostemede.</HEAD>
<P><MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="27b">A Wounde &thorn;at ha&thorn; enpostym or an yuel discrasiam&mdash;&thorn;at is to|seie out of kynde distemperid, ei&thorn;er to cold ei&thorn;er to hoot&mdash;|he mai not be heelid, ne he schal not ben heelid, but first he<NOTE PLACE="foot">The correct version is given by Add. MS.</NOTE> be|aswagid in &thorn;e yuel discurciour be amendid / &amp; as I haue seid in|ano&thorn;er place, it is profitable to &thorn;e sijk man, &amp; worschipe to &thorn;e leche,|if &thorn;at he mowe defende &thorn;e lymes &thorn;at ben woundid from enpostyme|&amp; from an yuel discrasie.  For &thorn;anne a leche schal kepe &thorn;e canoun|o<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>o</I>, mistake for <I>of</I>.</NOTE> galion, &thorn;at is oon of &thorn;e .iiij. canouns; oon is to kepe lymes in|her owne kyndely complexcioun.  For woundis moun not ellis be|heelid, but if &thorn;ei be brou&yogh;t first into her owne kynde / &amp; a wounde|mai be kept from apostyme &amp; an yuel discrasie if &thorn;at &thorn;e leche be|kunnynge &amp; do his deuer, &amp; &thorn;e sike man be obedient to &thorn;e leche /|&THORN;e leche muste loke if &thorn;at &thorn;er go blood y-now&yogh; out at &thorn;e wounde;|&amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;e wounde haue not bled blood y-now&yogh;, &thorn;e pacient muste
<PB N="55">|be lete blood or ellis ventusid, takynge reward to alle particuler|&thorn;ingis tofore seid / &amp; ordeyne him a couenable dietynge, as schal be|told in &thorn;e chapitle of dietynge; &amp; leie a defensif aboute &thorn;e wounde,
<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. of bole armoniak distemperid wi&thorn; oile of <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="28a">rosis, &amp; a litil vinegre:|as &thorn;icke as hony tempere it / &amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;e tyme of &thorn;e &yogh;eer were |hoot, putte to &thorn;is medicyn &thorn;e ius of sum cold erbe: as morel,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>morel</I>, Lat. Solathrum.  See Notes.</NOTE>|penywort,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>penywort</I>, Lat. umbilicus Veneris.</NOTE> virge pastoris.  Late not &thorn;e lyme hange; but if it be|the arm, hange it aboute &thorn;e necke / &amp; if it be &thorn;e foot ei&thorn;er &thorn;e|schene, lete him ligge / &amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;e lyme ake, aswage &thorn;e ak&thorn;e wi&thorn;|an oynement of hoot oile of rosis / For as Galion sei&thorn;: &thorn;er is no|&thorn;ing more noious to a wounde &thorn;an is ak&thorn;e &amp; declinacioun of a|lyme, for &thorn;ese .ij. maken soone an hoot swellynge, &thorn;e which is to &thorn;e|feuere as a welle, &amp; to &thorn;e bodi as an ouene / &THORN;e woundid man|muste absteyne him after &thorn;e chapitle of dietynge techi&thorn;, &amp; bo&thorn;e &thorn;e|sike man &amp; &thorn;e leche, &amp; alle &thorn;at ben aboute &thorn;e sike, moten absteyne|hem fro fleischly knowynge of a womman, [ne a womman] *in tyme|of menstrue,<NOTE PLACE="foot">See Notes.</NOTE> ne loke not on &thorn;e sike man / &amp; oonys in &thorn;e dai &thorn;e sike|man schal go to priuy;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>privy.  Prompt. Parv.</I>, p. 414, Pryvy or gonge (or Kocay), Latrina,|cloaca, ypodromium; p. 202, Goo to pryvy, or to shytyn, Acello.  <I>Pryvy</I>|still used in Yorkshire.</NOTE> &amp; if he mai not schite oonys kyndeli in
<PB N="56">|&thorn;e dai after &thorn;e quantite of mete &thorn;at he taki&thorn;, make him a clisterie|ou&thorn;er a suppositorie oonys ech day.  &amp; if &thorn;ou my&yogh;t not wi&thorn; alle|&thorn;ese &thorn;ingis defende &thorn;e lyme from apostyme, it is an yuel signe, for| &thorn;e lyme is <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="28b">feble, &amp; &thorn;e humouris arn wickide; &thorn;anne bigynnen<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bigynnen</I>, mistake for <I>bigynne</I>.</NOTE> to|materen &thorn;e swellynge wi&thorn; potage maad of flour, oile &amp; watir, or|ellis wi&thorn; &thorn;is maturatif / Take malowe leues &amp; leues of violet, &amp; &thorn;e|rote of holihocke; se&thorn;e hem weel in water, &amp; staumpe hem, &amp; take|a pound of water, &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben soden ynne, &amp; comoun oile; <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .iij.; of|wheete flour <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .iij.; of flour of lynseed <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j.; of flour of fenegrek|dj.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>dimidium</I>.</NOTE> <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>.; of erbis I-staumpid half a pound. &amp; boile alle &thorn;ese togidere|in a panne ouer &thorn;e fier, &amp; stire it weel wi&thorn; a spature; &amp; &thorn;is|maturatif leie on a lynnen cloo&thorn;, &amp; leie it on &thorn;e postyme til &thorn;at it|be maturid / &amp; whanne &thorn;at &thorn;e postyme is maturid, make &thorn;e quytture,|if &thorn;ou maist, be cast to &thorn;e wounde; &amp; if it mai not be cast to &thorn;e|wounde, opene &thorn;e place &thorn;at is moost lowist &thorn;ere, as &thorn;e quytture mai|best goon out; &amp; &thorn;anne hele &thorn;e wounde, as I schal telle in &thorn;e|&thorn;ridde chapitle of apostymes / Take hede alwey to &thorn;is techinge;|&amp; if &thorn;e postyme were for &thorn;e prickynge of a senewe, ne leie not|&thorn;erto &thorn;is potage maturatijf, but wi&thorn; &thorn;e oynement of oile of rosis, &amp;|of o&thorn;ere &thorn;ingis, as it is seid in &thorn;e woundis of senewis /</P>
<P>
<PB N="57">&THORN;ou schalt knowe &thorn;e yuel discrasie of a wounde, <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="29a">if &thorn;at &thorn;ou |seest &thorn;e skyn &thorn;at is aboue &thorn;e wounde to reed &amp; to hoot in felynge,|&thorn;anne &thorn;e wounde is discrasie in hete; namely, if &thorn;at &thorn;er come out|of &thorn;e wounde<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. erroneously inserts <I>quytture</I> after <I>wounde</I>.</NOTE> a sotil quytture, reed; &thorn;ilke discrasie &thorn;ou schalt|helpe wi&thorn; coldynge &thorn;e lyme aboute &thorn;e wounde with oile of rosis &amp;|vnguentum album, Rasis of ceruse, which &thorn;ou schalt fynde in &thorn;e|antidotarie, &amp; with &thorn;e ius of &thorn;e o&thorn;ere eerbis colde.</P>
<P>&amp; &thorn;ou schalt knowe a cold discrasie bi &thorn;e whi&yogh;tnes ei&thorn;er &thorn;e|wannesse of &thorn;e place / &amp; whanne &thorn;e place is cold in towchinge, &amp;|whanne &thorn;at &thorn;e quytture is &thorn;icke; &thorn;e which discrasie &thorn;ou schalt|remeue bi &thorn;e enoynture of hote oiles, as oile of coste,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>oile of coste</I>, Lat. cum oleo de castoreo.</NOTE> oile of|laurine, oile of enforbium, &amp; so o&thorn;ere hoote oilis /</P>
<P>A moist discracie &thorn;ou schalt knowe bi &thorn;e neischenes of &thorn;e|place, &amp; bi aboundaunce of whi&yogh;t liquide rotenes, &thorn;e which &thorn;ou|schalt helpe wi&thorn; desiccatiuis: as wi&thorn; waischinge of wiyn &amp; hony|togidere, in &thorn;e whiche ben soden balaustie,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>balaustie</I>.  Balaustium, the floure of the wylde Pomgranate.  Halle.|<I>Table</I>, p. 16.&mdash;1565.  Turner, <I>Herbal</I>, II., fol. 49 b., calls it Balaustrum.</NOTE> gallis &amp; &thorn;e ryndis of|some garnadis, or alle or summe bi hem-silf /</P>
<P>&THORN;e drie discrasie &thorn;ou schalt knowe bi &thorn;e smalnes of &thorn;e lyme, &amp;|&thorn;e smalnes of &thorn;e lippis of &thorn;e wounde, &amp; litil quytture, if &thorn;at &thorn;e|quytture be &thorn;inne; &thorn;e which discrasie &thorn;ou schalt <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="29b">helpe: with 
<PB N="58">|castynge on of hoot water til &thorn;at &thorn;e lyme wexe reed, &amp; wi&thorn; an|oynement &thorn;ou muste<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;ou muste</I>, mistake for <I>of moiste</I>.</NOTE> grece, as hennes, goos, &amp; dokis, &thorn;e marie boon|of a calf, &amp; wi&thorn; plenteuousnes of good mete &thorn;at norischi&thorn;: as &thorn;e|bro&thorn;is of fleisch, &amp; temperate wiyn, &amp; rere eyren, &amp; smale fischis,|&amp; wi&thorn; reste, &amp; softnes of al &thorn;e bodi, &amp; of &thorn;e lyme &thorn;at is hirt; &amp;|alwey to &thorn;is techinge take hede &thorn;at as soone as a membre is brou&yogh;t|to his kyndeli disposicioun, anoon a&yogh;enstondi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a&yogh;enstondi&thorn;</I>, mistake for <I>a&yogh;enstonde.</I></NOTE> wi&thorn; contrarious|medicyns, &amp; turne a&yogh;en to &thorn;e principal cure of &thorn;e wounde.  But|&thorn;enke nou&yogh;t to heele &thorn;e wounde as longe as it is enpostemed, or|ellis haue an yuel discrasie; but first remeue &thorn;ilke discrasie, or &thorn;at|&thorn;ou heele &thorn;e wounde / For whanne two &thorn;ingis &thorn;at schulden ben|heelid ben togidere, &amp; &thorn;e oon of hem mowe not be helid wi&thorn;oute|helynge of &thorn;at o&thorn;ere, first we schulen heelen him, &thorn;at mai nou&yogh;t|be heelid wi&thorn;oute &thorn;at o&thorn;er helyng, as &thorn;e apostyme ei&thorn;er &thorn;e discrasie|/ &THORN;us Auicenne techi&thorn; in &thorn;e laste chapitle of &thorn;e firste book.|Neuer-&thorn;e-lattere for&yogh;ete nou&yogh;t &thorn;e principal cure, &thorn;at whanne &thorn;e|accidentis ben asesid turne a&yogh;en to &thorn;e principal cure //</P>
</DIV4>
<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="7">
<PB N="59">
<HEAD>&para; &THORN;e .vij. chapitle of &thorn;e .iij. techinge is a wounde maad|with a wood hound, ei&thorn;er of ony o&thorn;er venemous|beest /|<NOTE PLACE="foot">Heading to leaf 30, in a later hand, <I>Off woundes betten with doges.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P><MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="30a">Bvt whanne an hound ha&thorn; biten a man, loke first if &thorn;at &thorn;e|hound be wood; &amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;e hound be not wood, heele &thorn;e|wounde as &thorn;ou doist o&thorn;ere comoun woundis; &amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;e hound|were wood, &thorn;ou schalt knowe it bi certeyn cause &amp; disposiciouns /|For a wood hound flee&thorn; mete &amp; water; &amp; he renne&thorn; hidirward &amp;|&thorn;idirward as a drunken man, wi&thorn; open mou&thorn; &amp; his tail bitwene hise|leggis; his tunge hangi&thorn; out, but he wolde biten alle men; ne he|knowi&thorn; not &thorn;o men &thorn;at ben in houshold.  He berki&thorn; not / &amp; if|&thorn;at he o&thorn;irwhile berke, his vois is ful hors, &amp; o&thorn;ere houndis fleen|fro him &amp; berken vpon him.  Also &thorn;ou schalt knowe bi disposicioun|of &thorn;e same wounde.  For if &thorn;at &thorn;ou wetist a crumme of breed in|&thorn;e blood of &thorn;e wounde, &amp; &yogh;euest it to ano&thorn;er hound to ete, he|wole not ete it; &amp; if &thorn;at he ete it, he wole die / Or ellis take an|ote, &amp; staumpe it, &amp; leie it on &thorn;e wounde al ny&yogh;t, &amp; on &thorn;e morowe|&yogh;eue it to an hen; &amp; &thorn;e hen wole not ete it / &amp; if &thorn;e hen ete it, &thorn;e|hen schal die /
</P>
<P>
<PB N="60">And anoon as &thorn;ou woost &thorn;at &thorn;e hound was wood, sette a greet|ventuse aboue vpon &thorn;e wounde, &amp; drawe out &thorn;e myche blood out|of &thorn;e wounde, &amp; aftirward drawe abrood &thorn;e wounde; &amp; aboue al| o&thorn;ere &thorn;ing, brennynge of hoot yren to &thorn;e ground <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="30b">of &thorn;e wounde is|moost profitable.  &amp; leie aboue &thorn;e wounde actractiuis, to drawe out|&thorn;e venym /  Summe of &thorn;ese actractiuis ben symple, &amp; summe compound|/  Symple be&thorn;: &thorn;e lyuere of &thorn;e same wood hound &thorn;at boot|&thorn;e man, garlik stampid, salt fisch, aischis of wiyn lies, appoponak|&thorn;at is wondirful, &thorn;e leeues of a gourde,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>gourde</I>, cucumer.  See <I>Prompt. Parv.</I>, 203, <I>Goord</I>, Cucumer, cucurbita,|colloquintida.</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;e rote of fenegrek, &thorn;e|gile<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>gile</I>, ne. gill.  See M&auml;tzner, <I>Dict</I>., p. 268.  The Latin has, <I>gluten</I>, glue.</NOTE> of fisch, &amp; amptyn I-stampid / &THORN;ese medicyns ben compound:|vreyne of a &yogh;ong man wi&thorn; nitre; ou&thorn;er mintis stampid<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>stampid</I>, in margin.</NOTE> wi&thorn; salt, &amp;|distemperid wi&thorn; vynegre, &amp; maad an enplaster.  Ano&thorn;er medicyn|compound: take floris eris &amp; salt, of ech .x. parties, &amp; &thorn;e fatte of|a calf, &amp; of a wolf &thorn;at suffici&thorn;, &amp; make a plastre / Ano&thorn;er: take|schepis talow &amp; buttere, &amp; make a plaster / &THORN;is wounde schal be|holden open at &thorn;e leeste fourty daies, &amp; &thorn;is schal be do aboute &thorn;e|place.  In ano&thorn;er maner regimen / Vndirstonde &thorn;at &thorn;e man &thorn;at is|biten, schal not be lete blood in &thorn;e bigynnynge, lest &thorn;e venym be|drawe abrood bi o&thorn;ere lymes; ne &thorn;ou schalt &yogh;eue him no laxatif,|lest it drawe &thorn;e venym to &thorn;e entrailis wi&thorn;inne; but &thorn;ou schalt sette
<PB N="61">|vpon &thorn;e place a strong ventuse, as it is seid tofore, <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="31a">&thorn;at it mowe|drawe miche of &thorn;e blood.  And whanne &thorn;at .iij. daies ben passid, it |is not yuele to lete blood &amp; to purge with a litil purgacioun, &thorn;at|purgi&thorn; &thorn;e malencolie, as with decoccioun epithimum,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Epithemum</I>.  See Notes.</NOTE> wi&thorn; gotis|whey; &amp; norischi&thorn; him with dieting, &thorn;at fatti&thorn; &amp; maki&thorn; him glad|&amp; bli&thorn;e; &amp; waische his heed with decoccioun of water, &thorn;at &thorn;e feet|&amp; &thorn;e heed of a we&thorn;er were soden ynne.  Ne late him not &thorn;irsten|ne hungren, suffren, ne traueilen; &amp; so if &thorn;at god wole, &thorn;ou maist|him kepe from perile / &amp; ech dai to a mon&thorn;is eende he schal take|o&thorn;ere symple medicyns or compounned / *&mdash; &mdash; Take &thorn;e ayschis of|crabbis I-brent in an ouene .iiij. parties, of frankencense vij.|parties, &amp; make hem into a poudre / &THORN;e pacient schal take ech dai|of &thorn;is poudre .ij .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>. / Ano&thorn;er medicyn: take &thorn;e pouder of crabbis|brent vj. parties, gencian .iij parties, terre sigillate oon partie,|make poudre / If &thorn;at &thorn;ou were not at &thorn;e bigynnynge, &amp; it bigynne|to haue yuel accidentis: as yuel &thorn;ou&yogh;tis, soruful metynge in his|sleep, &amp; &thorn;at he be wro&thorn; &amp; grucche, &amp; woot not whi; &amp; if men|aske him ony &thorn;ing, &amp; &yogh;eue&thorn; no good answere &thorn;erto, &amp; fley lith,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fley lith</I>, altered to <I>fleyntlith</I> with different ink.  Read: <I>fleyth li&yogh;t.</I></NOTE> &amp;|he ha&thorn; alle o&thorn;ere signes of malencolie, <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="31b">&thorn;anne &yogh;eue to him a 
<PB N="62">|medicyn maad of cantarides /  Take old grete cantarides, &amp; do|awei &thorn;e heed &amp; &thorn;e wyngis, .ij dragmis; lentis<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>docsnet</I> above <I>lentis</I>; meaning?</NOTE> I-clensid, .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j.;|safron, spikenard, clowis, canel, .ana .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> s'.; bete hem weel, &amp; make|of hem smale ballis, &thorn;at ech bal wei&yogh;e a dragme.  &amp; &yogh;eue o. bal at|&thorn;re tymes, at ech tyme &thorn;e wei&yogh;te of &thorn;re cornys of wheete, til &thorn;at|he pisse blood; &thorn;anne he schal be saaf /  For whanne &thorn;ou art sikir,|heele &thorn;e woundis after &thorn;at fourti daies ben passid, in &thorn;e same|maner.  If &thorn;at &thorn;e wounde were maad of bitinge of an eddre or of|ony o&thorn;er venemous beest, &thorn;e leche schal take heede to drawe abrod|&thorn;e wounde, &amp; sette aboue a uentuse, &amp; drawe out miche blood; &amp;|it is miche wor&thorn; to enuyrounne &thorn;e place aboute &thorn;at is biten wi&thorn;|brome I-stampid /  For if &thorn;at &thorn;e prickynge be in &thorn;e foot or in &thorn;e|hand, if &thorn;ou enuyrounne &thorn;e arme with brome, it letti&thorn; &thorn;e venym to|go vpward; &amp; &yogh;eue him &thorn;e medicyns writen aboue, &amp; also lete &thorn;e|wounde be open, til &thorn;e venym be excludid /</P>
</DIV4>
<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="8">
<HEAD>The .viij chapitle of &thorn;e &thorn;ridde techinge of &thorn;e firste|tretis of a wounde maad in a ioynt, &amp; is dislocate /</HEAD>
<P>Whanne &thorn;at a wounde is in a lyme, &amp; &thorn;e boon of &thorn;e same lyme| is to-broke <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="32a"><NOTE PLACE="foot">Heading to leaf 32 in a later hand: <I>Off woundes in Jintes.</I></NOTE>atwo &amp; dislocate&mdash;&thorn;at is to seie out of ioynte, &thorn;anne
<PB N="63">|it is good &thorn;at &thorn;ou putte in &thorn;e wounde whanne &thorn;e blood is staunchid,|&amp; also aboue &thorn;e wounde &thorn;e &yogh;olke of an ey wi&thorn; oile of rosis, &amp;|anointe al &thorn;e lyme aboute &thorn;e wounde with two parties of oile of|rosis, &amp; half oon partie of vynegre maad &thorn;icke wi&thorn; bole armoniak,|til &thorn;e quytture be engendrid, &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ou be sikir &thorn;at no postyme|schal come.  Ne take noon hede to brynge togidere &thorn;e parties of &thorn;e|boon &thorn;at is to-broken or dislocate, til viij. daies ben goon in &thorn;e|wyntir, &amp; v. in &thorn;e somer; for &thorn;anne it schal make quytture, and be|sikir from swellynge; &amp; &thorn;anne brynge togidere &thorn;e brynkis ei&thorn;er &thorn;e|disiuncture after &thorn;e techynge &thorn;at schal be seid in &thorn;e chapitle of|algebra.  &amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;e prickynge ei&thorn;er &thorn;e dislocacioun nedi&thorn; splentis,|make &thorn;at &thorn;e splentis &amp; byndynge faile aboue &thorn;e wounde.  &THORN;at &thorn;ou|may do if &thorn;at &thorn;ou kutte &thorn;e splentis &amp; &thorn;e bindynge aboue &thorn;e|wounde with a knyf or a rasour, &amp; in drawynge abrood &thorn;e hoole of|&thorn;e wounde<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wounde</I>, error for <I>bonde</I>.</NOTE> aboue &thorn;e wounde wi&thorn; a nedle, so &thorn;at &thorn;ou maist bi &thorn;at|hole ech day chaunge &thorn;i medicyn of &thorn;e wounde wi&thorn;oute choudynge<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>choudynge</I>, error for <I>chongynge</I>.</NOTE>|of &thorn;e boond &thorn;at &thorn;ou madist first aboute &thorn;e boonys<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="32b"> &thorn;at weren |broken ou&thorn;er dislocate; &thorn;e which boond &thorn;ou schalt nou&yogh;t remeuen|til tyme schal be teld in his place, but &thorn;ou schalt bynde aboue &thorn;ilke
<PB N="64">|boon a newe boond, which &thorn;ou schalt remeue as ofte as &thorn;ou|chaungist &thorn;i wounde.  &amp; whanne &thorn;at &thorn;ou art sikir fro &thorn;e enpostemynge,|&amp; whanne &thorn;at &thorn;ou hast sett togidere &thorn;e boonys &thorn;at|were sett togidere &amp; dissolate, &thorn;anne leie vpon &thorn;e wounde bi &thorn;e hole|&thorn;at &thorn;ou madist in &thorn;e boond, a mundificatif of mel roset colat, &amp; of|barli mele til &thorn;e wounde be clensid; &amp; leie on &thorn;at a<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a</I>, erroneously inserted.</NOTE> mundificatif,|&thorn;redis of oolde whi&yogh;t lynnen cloo&thorn;, til &thorn;at &thorn;e wounde be ful|clensid; aftirward regendre fleisch, &amp; aftirward consowde with|regeneratiuis &amp; consolidatiuis, whiche &thorn;at schulen be seid in &thorn;e|ende of &thorn;e book /</P>
</DIV4>
<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="9">
<HEAD>The nyn&thorn;e chapitle of &thorn;e .iij. techinge of &thorn;e firste|tretis is of fluxblood of a wounde /</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;er ben ij. maner of causis &thorn;at maki&thorn; blood to blede out of|a mannys body; &thorn;e oon cause is clepid&mdash;cause coniuncte; &amp; &thorn;e|to&thorn;er&mdash;cause antecedent / &THORN;e enchesoun of cause coniuncte is compounned|of &thorn;e mou&thorn;is of &thorn;e veynes and arteries, or ellis whanne|&thorn;at &thorn;e veynes ben kut atwo, or ellis corrosion of &thorn;e bodies of &thorn;e|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="33a"><NOTE PLACE="foot">Heading to leaf 33, <I>Off fflux off blode in woundes.</I></NOTE>same veynes &amp; arteries, or ellis to greet febilnes or to greet losenes|/ And &thorn;er ben manie enchesouns of cause antecedentis: as to
<PB N="65">|myche frelenes<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>frelenes</I>, mistake for <I>fulnesse</I>.</NOTE> of blood, or ellis to myche acute of blood, &amp; also|manye o&thorn;ere causis &thorn;er ben &thorn;at ben clepid cause of<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>of</I>, erroneous insertion.  See below.</NOTE> primitif: as|smytynge &thorn;at woundith, to greet lepinge, criyng; wra&thorn;e, chidynge,|&amp; so manye o&thorn;ere; &amp; ech of &thorn;ese causis tofore seid ha&thorn; his maner|heelynge by him-silf in fisik medicinal.  But it is not &thorn;e entencioun|of &thorn;is book to treten<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>but</I>, omitted.  Latin: Non est huius libri intentio tractare nisi de|fluxu sanguinis...</NOTE> of blood &thorn;at bledi&thorn; of wounde, &thorn;at is|maad with wounde, &thorn;e which may be restreyned with craft of|ciurgie.  In flux of blood &thorn;at come&thorn; of a wounde, &thorn;e leche muste|loke &thorn;e disposicioun, &thorn;e abitude, age, vertu, &amp; complexioun of him|&thorn;at is woundid; if &thorn;at &thorn;ese acorden, &amp; he be my&yogh;ty in vertu, he|schal blede myche blood at &thorn;e wounde, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at &thorn;e leche be clepid|at &thorn;e bigynnynge, but if it be so &thorn;at he be<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>be</I>, added in margin in same hand.</NOTE> feble ouer greetliche.|&amp; if &thorn;at nede constreyne &thorn;e leche to staunche blood, he muste loke|if &thorn;at &thorn;e blood go out at &thorn;e veynes capillares, &thorn;at ben smale veynes|as heeris of a mannys heed / &amp; &thorn;anne oonly &thorn;e whi&yogh;t <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="33b">of an ey leid |aboue with tow&yogh;e of flex suffisi&thorn; / whanne &thorn;at &thorn;e parties of &thorn;e|wounde ben brou&yogh;t togidere; &amp; if &thorn;ou caste aboue poudre of lym|aforeseid in &thorn;e chapitle of sowynge of woundes, it schal be &thorn;e|bettere; for &thorn;at poudre wi&thorn;streyne&thorn; &thorn;e blood &amp; consoudi&thorn; &thorn;erparties
<PB N="66">|of &thorn;e wounde togidere.  &amp; if &thorn;e blood come fro grete veynes he|mai nou&yogh;t so sumtyme be constreyned, but it nedi&thorn; a stronger|medicyn &amp; also a more cautele / &amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;e blood go out of|arterie, &thorn;ou schalt knowe it bi construccion &amp; dilatacion of &thorn;e|same arterie&mdash;&thorn;at is to seie, &thorn;at &thorn;e blood go out wi&thorn; lepinge &amp;|o&thorn;erwhile wi&thorn; wi&thorn;drawinge<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: quod sanguis exit cum saltu secundum constrictionem et dilatationem|ipsius arteri&aelig;.</NOTE>; &amp; &thorn;anne sette &thorn;i fyngir vpon &thorn;e mou&thorn;|of &thorn;e grete veyne or ellis on &thorn;e arterie, &amp; holde &thorn;i fyngir &thorn;eron bi|a greet hour; for &thorn;anne by grace sum greet drope of blood may be|congelid togidere &amp; &thorn;ere-bi vertu may be myche comfortid; aftirward|leie plenteuousliche of &thorn;is medicyn vpon &thorn;e veyne ei&thorn;er &thorn;e|arterie &thorn;at is kutt atwo / Take frankencense, whi&yogh;t gummis, &amp;|fatt .ij. &yogh;., aloes .&yogh;. j., make poudre &amp; distempere with &thorn;e white of|an ey as &thorn;icke as hony / after take heeris of an hare smal kutt,|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="34a">medle alle &thorn;ese togidere, &amp; &thorn;er is no medicyn so good as &thorn;is medicyn|is in streynynge of blood &amp; consowdynge of &thorn;e veyne / But|whanne &thorn;at &thorn;ou comest to chaunge &thorn;at medicyn of &thorn;e wounde, do|nou&yogh;t &thorn;e medicyn awey wi&thorn; strenk&thorn;e, but leie aboue of &thorn;e same|medicyn<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>medicyn</I>, repeated.</NOTE> moist, to neische &thorn;e firste medicyn, &thorn;at it my&yogh;te|falle awey bi him-silf / Ne&thorn;eles it is possible &thorn;at a medicyn|caustik, &thorn;at is to seie, a medicyn &thorn;at brenne&thorn;, sunner staunchi&thorn;
