E PLACE="foot">Corrupt passage.  Lat.: donec consumetur tertia pars.</NOTE> to .iij parties ben consumed, &amp; &thorn;anne lete him| drynke.  To asaye it softly<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>softly</I>, error for <I>so&thorn;ly.</I></NOTE> / <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="38b">&THORN;is drynke is alteratijf: &thorn;at is|to seie, chaunginge, ne it swelli&thorn; not, &amp; it letti&thorn; fumosite to arise
<PB N="75">|to &thorn;e brayn.  Of mete I seie: to him &thorn;at is of a moist complexicioun|&amp; hoot / bi no maner wey schulde not be &yogh;ouen fleisch,|fisch, mylk, eiren, ne no comfortable mete, but if &thorn;ei weren ouercomen|wi&thorn; to greet febilnes; but he muste holde him content wi&thorn;|ius of barli or ellis of ootis wi&thorn; almaunde mylk; outake<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>outake</I>, except.  See <I>Catholicon Angl.</I>, p. 264, Oute take, note.</NOTE> wounde|of &thorn;e heed, were<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>were</I>, error for <I>where</I>.</NOTE> I ne apreue nou&yogh;t almaundis ne noon o&thorn;er|vaperous fruyt: as notis ei&thorn;ir walnotis ei&thorn;er avellanes; for &thorn;ei han|a maner fumose properte greuynge &thorn;e heed / he may eten amidoun,|betis, letuse, &amp; breed I-waische wi&thorn; sugre if &thorn;at he were feble.  &amp;|if &thorn;at he my&yogh;te not absteyne him fro fleisch, &yogh;eue him fleisch of|smale chikenes &amp; of smale briddis &amp; kidis &amp; lambis &amp; calues|I-sauered with agresta ei&thorn;er wi&thorn; wiyn of pome garnatis; &amp; &thorn;ilke|dietynge he schal vse til he be sikir fro swellynge &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ou schalt|knowe whanne &thorn;at akynge swellynge &amp; extencioun of &thorn;e lyme ben|ceessid &amp; &thorn;e wounde almoost consowdid.  If &thorn;at it was a wounde|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="39a">&thorn;at was sowid ei&thorn;er brou&yogh;t togidere with byndinge, in whom |quytture was nou&yogh;t engendrid, &amp; if &thorn;at it was a wounde maad|wi&thorn; smytynge or ellis chaungid wi&thorn; &thorn;e eyr, in whom it is nedeful|engendrynge of quytture, &thorn;anne it is siker &thorn;at it schal not enpostyme,
