<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="11">
<HEAD>The .xj. chapitle of &thorn;e &thorn;ridde techinge of &thorn;e firste|tretis.</HEAD>
<P>is of olde woundis &thorn;at ben maad of kuttynge or of openynge|of a postyme, or ellis of a wounde &thorn;at is not heelid in|his tyme, or ellis of sum maner fleinge, or of brennynge, or|of to greet heete, or of to greet drouthe, or of to greet cold|constreynynge, or of to greet aboundaunce of mater corrumpinge /|For euery olde wounde hauynge rotnes or wire<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wire</I>, Lat. virus.</NOTE> &thorn;at is &thorn;inne|venymous quyttir or ony o&thorn;ir &thorn;ing &thorn;an good quytture is not clepid|a wounde, but it is clepid vlcus / Rowlond &amp; Rogerine &amp; &thorn;e|moste <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="40a">partie of men &thorn;at ben now, clepen it a festre<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>festre, fester</I> in M&auml;tzner <I>Dict</I>.; O.Fr. flestre, festre; Lat. flstula.|Comp. N. E. fester vb.</NOTE> or a cankre, |but it is nei&thorn;ir festre ne cankre, but festre &amp; cankre han difference|fro &thorn;is / &THORN;is vlcus as a propre &thorn;ing ha&thorn; difference from a &thorn;ing &thorn;at|is comoun / for ech festre &amp; ech cankre &thorn;at is woundid, is clepid|vlcus, but it ne schewi&thorn; not &thorn;at ech vlcus is clepid cankre or festre
<PB N="78">|as I schal telle openliche in ech chapitle bi him-silf / Auicen sei&thorn;,|&thorn;at &thorn;er ben .vj. maner of &thorn;is vlcus: summe &thorn;at ben venemous,|summe hore, summe depe, summe cauernose ei&thorn;er hid, summe|corosif, summe rotin, summe ambulatif &thorn;at is spredynge abrood, &amp;|summe harde to consowde / Of &thorn;ese maners tofore seid, summe<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>summen</I>.</NOTE>|han acordynge with festris in tokenes &amp; in foormes as venemous &amp;|holow&yogh; &amp; summe han acordynge with cankris as spredynge abrood|&amp; fretynge him-silf &amp; ne&thorn;eles &thorn;ei han difference, as it is conteyned|in &thorn;e chapitle of cankris I-woundid &amp; of festre. &amp; alle &thorn;ese tofore|seid han difference fro wounde / for in a wounde &thorn;er is whi&yogh;t|quytture &amp; euene in alle hise parties &amp; hole and nou&yogh;t departid &amp;|wi&thorn;oute stenche.  &THORN;is maner of quytture is engendrid of goodnes| &amp; kyndely heete, &amp; is perfi&yogh;tly defied / But venym rotynes <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="40b">&amp; a|cruste, &amp; al o&thorn;ere superfluyte of olde woundis ben engendrid of a|strong vnkyndly heete.</P>
<P>A uenym vlcus is in whom aboundi&thorn; venym sutil &amp; liquid.  If|&thorn;at it be reed or &yogh;elu, or oon partie redisch and scharp bitynge &thorn;e|lyme, it signifie&thorn; lordschipe of a strong heete.</P>
<P>An hori elde wounde &thorn;at ha&thorn; summe greete crustis, or ellis a|wroting, sum gret proud fleisch to hi&yogh;e.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>proud fleisch to hi&yogh;e</I>.  Lat.: carnem superfluam grossam.  Proud flesh,|Fungosity.  Dunglison.</NOTE></P>
<P>
<PB N="79">A deep vlcus is &thorn;at, &thorn;at ha&thorn; a greet depnes &amp; an holow&yogh; &amp;|perauenture crokinge.</P>
<P>A wroting vlcus is &thorn;at of his malice freti&thorn; bi cause &thorn;at &thorn;e|blood is sent to him so scharpe / Galion sei&thorn;: &thorn;at scharp blood not|oonli corrodi&thorn; [no&yogh;t]*&mdash;fleisch in woundis, but also hool fleisch /</P>
<P>A rotid vlcus is stynkynge, hauynge a strong heete in his|ground, &amp; out of him passi&thorn; a stynkynge smel, ei&thorn;er smoke, as|doi&thorn; out of fleisch &thorn;at is rotid / &thorn;ilke<NOTE PLACE="foot">This curious explanation of the word <I>stynk</I> is an insertion of the scribe.|Read: <I>ste her laddre.</I>  One letter half erased in <I>lacdre</I>.  <I>Ste</I>, see Stratm.|<I>Dict.</I>, O.E. st&icirc;gan.</NOTE> word 'stynk' I vndirstonde|it bi my maner witt: sich bree&thorn; &thorn;at come&thorn; out of a bodies ende,|whanne a bodi bre&thorn;i&thorn; wi&thorn; &thorn;e mou&thorn; in frosty wedir, &thorn;at men taken|a saumple, bifor to sle her lac dre / &thorn;anne whanne &thorn;ou my&yogh;t se &thorn;e|bree&thorn; of &thorn;in owne ende comynge out at &thorn;i mou&thorn; in &thorn;e eir.</P>
<P>A walkynge / vlcus is &thorn;at walki&thorn; hidirward &amp; &thorn;idirward, &amp;|ne&thorn;eles he profoundi&thorn; nou&yogh;t depe <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="41a">into &thorn;e ground. </P>
<P>An vlcus &thorn;at is hard to helin is he &thorn;at for his yuel propirte &thorn;at|is sent to him fro &thorn;e bodi letti&thorn; him to heele.</P>
<P>&amp; for to heelen ech maner of &thorn;ese vlcus, &thorn;er ben manye dyuers|rulis / &THORN;e firste rule is &thorn;at &thorn;ei moun not be heelid, but &thorn;e superfluytees|&thorn;at ben in hem ben I-dried / &THORN;e secunde rule / but if &thorn;at|bodi ou&thorn;er &thorn;e membre be oute of his naturel complexioun, or &thorn;an|&thorn;ou &thorn;enke to heele &thorn;ilke vlcus &thorn;ou muste brynge a&yogh;en to his diete
<PB N="80">|complexioun distemprid &thorn;ilke bodi ou&thorn;ir membre.  &THORN;e &thorn;ridde rule|is: &thorn;at if &thorn;e lyuere ei&thorn;ir &thorn;e splene ben I-greued, as it happi&thorn; ofte|tymes in olde woundis, &thorn;ou muste rectifien hem / &THORN;e .iiij rule is:|&thorn;at &thorn;e qualitees &amp; &thorn;e quantitees of humouris schulden be temperid|wi&thorn; blood-letynge &amp; purgaciouns &amp; with good gouernaile / &amp; if &thorn;at|&thorn;e eir be yuel, &thorn;e sike man schal be chaungid into good eyr / &amp;|whanne &thorn;at &thorn;e leche ha&thorn; tofore seen alle &thorn;ese &thorn;ingis, &thorn;anne he may|go to his cure /</P>
<P>&amp; if &thorn;e vlcus be virulent, &thorn;at is to seie venemi, loke if &thorn;at &thorn;e|venym &thorn;at goi&thorn; out be redisch or &yogh;elowisch, &amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;e lyme haue|ony maner heete; &thorn;anne waische it wi&thorn; water of rosis &amp; barlich.| alim<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>alim</I>, Latin: aluminis.</NOTE> &amp; balaustia &amp; lentiles with hony <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="41b">symple ei&thorn;er compouuned|ben soden yn, &amp; lete &thorn;is watir peersen to &thorn;e dep&thorn;e of &thorn;e wounde; &amp;|if &thorn;e virus be wi&thorn;oute heete &amp; &thorn;e membre haue noon heete, waische|it wi&thorn; watir or with wiyn &thorn;at mirre wormode,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wormode</I>, absinthium.  O.E. worm&ocirc;d, M.E. wormwood.</NOTE> horhone,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>horhone</I>, Marrubium vulgare.  See Britten, <I>Dict</I>.</NOTE> sauge,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sauge</I>, salvia.</NOTE>|pimpernelle<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>pimpernella</I>, Pimpinella.</NOTE> hony symple or compounned ben soden yn / Clense &thorn;e|wounde perfi&yogh;tliche &amp; engendre fleisch &amp; afterward consowde it|wi&thorn; &thorn;is propre oynement &thorn;at &thorn;i<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;i</I>, error for <I>in</I>.</NOTE> olde foule venym woundis, ei&thorn;er
<PB N="81">|vlcus, engendri&thorn; fleisch, clensi&thorn; &amp; heeli&thorn; as auicen &amp; rasis witnessen /|recipe litargium<NOTE PLACE="foot">"<I>Lithangyros</I>, Litharge or Silver-glet, the frothy Dross, or Scum that|arises in the purifying of Silver with Lead."&mdash;Phillips.</NOTE> as myche as &thorn;ou wolt &amp; stampe it in a morter<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>&amp; putte it in a morter</I>, scribal insertion.</NOTE> &amp;|putte wi&thorn; him good oile of rosis &amp; vynegre now on &amp; now &thorn;e o&thorn;ere,|alwey stiryng, til it be perfi&yogh;tly an oynement &amp; come into &thorn;e foorme|of an oynement.  &amp; &thorn;is oynement is clepid litargirum nutritum,|&thorn;at is to sai litarge nurschid, &thorn;at is profitable in manye causis /|afterward take of &thorn;ilke litarge norischid .vij. parties &amp; of alim,|&amp; of balaustie or ellis in &thorn;e stide of balaustie wormes of &thorn;e er&thorn;e|brent, bras brent, leed, gallis, sandragoun chathinie<NOTE PLACE="foot">"<I>Cathima</I> est minera de qua elicitur aurum vel argentum."&mdash;Sinonoma|Barth. p. 14.  <I>Cathimia</I>: argenti spuma, Cartelli <I>Dict</I>.</NOTE> argenti .ana.|as myche as is xij parties of al &thorn;e oynement; medle alle togidere |and <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="42a">make an oynement / &THORN;is oynement schal be leid wi&thorn;inne &thorn;e|wounde &amp; al aboue &thorn;e wounde; for it drie&thorn; &thorn;e wounde &amp; engendri&thorn;|good fleisch &amp; consowdi&thorn; / Take hede to &thorn;is rule, &thorn;at in heelynge|of alle olde woundis after &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben clensyd, aboue &thorn;e oynement|it is good to leie a lynnen cloo&thorn;, to distende abrood on of &thorn;e|mundificatiuis of ony which &thorn;at schal be told in &thorn;e antidotarie, &amp;|leie aboue aboute &thorn;ilke vlcus specialy from &thorn;e ouer partie fro whens|humouris fleen, a defensif of bole armonyak &amp; terra sigillata; &thorn;at
<PB N="82">|is maad on &thorn;is maner / take bole armoniak .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. terra sigillata. <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR><ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>|oile of rosis &amp; vynegre &thorn;at suffisi&thorn;, I-now&yogh; do in &thorn;e oon now in &thorn;e|o&thorn;er til &thorn;e oynement be ful maad &amp; liquide I-nou&yogh; / so &thorn;at of &thorn;e|oile of rosis be double as myche as of vynegre / &THORN;is defensi&thorn; a|membre fro corrupcioun &amp; also vlcus &thorn;at he sprede nou&yogh;t abrood /</P>
<P>An hory wounde shal be heelid, in remeuynge awey &thorn;e crust|ei&thorn;ere fil&thorn;e &thorn;at is in him wi&thorn; poudre of affodill, &thorn;at schal be said in|&thorn;e eende of &thorn;is book, ou&thorn;er wi&thorn; sum o&thorn;er mundificatiuis; aftir| consowde it wi&thorn; consolidaciouns /</P>
<P>A deep wounde is heelid <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="42b">wi&thorn; castynge into &thorn;e dep&thorn;e of &thorn;e|wounde with an instrument maad to &thorn;e lijknesse of a clisterie, ony|of &thorn;e waischingis &thorn;at ben seid in &thorn;e venemy wounde aboue, aftir|&thorn;at &thorn;e disposicioun of &thorn;e membre aski&thorn; of heete or of cold.  &amp;|aftir &thorn;at, he is clensid in castynge in watre ou&thorn;ir wiyn &thorn;at mastik|or frank encense is soden ynne &amp; in leggyng wi&thorn;outen oon of &thorn;e|mundificatiuis of hony &thorn;at schal be seid aftir.  &amp; also it is good to|ordeyne &thorn;e lyme so &thorn;at &thorn;e mou&thorn; of &thorn;e wounde hange dounward, &amp;|streyne &thorn;i ligature at &thorn;e ground of &thorn;i wounde, &amp; bynde it losely at|&thorn;e mou&thorn; of &thorn;e wounde; also it were good, if &thorn;at it my&yogh;te be, &thorn;at|&thorn;er were maad a newe wounde in &thorn;e place &thorn;at is moost hangynge,|&thorn;at &thorn;e rotynes &amp; &thorn;e quytture my&yogh;te &thorn;e bettere goon out; for so|&thorn;ilke vlcus my&yogh;te &thorn;e sunnere be heelid /</P>
<P>
<PB N="83">A wroting vlcus is heelid in leggynge specialiche aboute him|colde &thorn;ingis whiche &thorn;at ben<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ben</I>, erroneously inserted.</NOTE> obtunden or casten bach &thorn;e scharpnes|of &thorn;e same vlcus; &amp; also with amendynge, as with metis &amp; drynkis,|&thorn;e scharpnes of &thorn;e same blood, &amp; in purgynge &thorn;e reed colere; &amp;|wi&thorn; anoyntynge wi&thorn; colde oynementis &amp; consolidatiuis.  &amp; &thorn;erto|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="43a">is miche wor&thorn; vnguentum album rasis &thorn;at schal be told in &thorn;e|antidotarie / </P>
<P>A stynkynge wounde is heelid in remeuynge awey &thorn;e stinche &amp;|&thorn;e rotenes; &amp; &thorn;erto is myche wor&thorn; a waischinge of ydromel: &thorn;at is|hony &amp; watir soden togidere wi&thorn; mirre, &amp; a mundificatif maad wi&thorn;|ius of wormod &amp; barly mele &amp; hony &amp; mirre, &thorn;at is maad on &thorn;is|maner / take ius of wormod. <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iij. of hony. <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iij. barli mele <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij.|of mirre ana. <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. &amp; compounne hem togidere &amp; fille &thorn;e wounde|wi&thorn;innefor&thorn; with lynnet of lynnen cloo&thorn;.  &amp; if &thorn;at wormes ben|engendrid in &thorn;e wounde, sle hem wi&thorn; &thorn;e ius of calamynte ou&thorn;er wi&thorn;|&thorn;e ius of &thorn;e leeues of pechis, or ellis persicarie,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>persicarie</I> glossed <I>colorag</I>.  See Notes.</NOTE> ei&thorn;er wi&thorn; decoccioun|of elebre.  &amp; whanne &thorn;at a perfi&yogh;t mundificatif is maad, engendre|fleisch &amp; consowde as it is seid tofore /</P>
<P>A walkynge vlcus is heelid wi&thorn; fleobotomie &amp; formacie<NOTE PLACE="foot">O.Fr. farmacie = purgation.  See Littr&eacute;, <I>Dict</I>.</NOTE> &thorn;at is
<PB N="84">|laxatiuis purgynge &thorn;e colere &amp; brent humouris, &amp; in leggynge aboute|a defensif of bole &amp; terra sigillata &thorn;at is seid tofore in &thorn;is chapitle;|&amp; with oon of &thorn;e cold mundificatiuis, &amp; sumtyme &thorn;ou muste cauterise|&thorn;e vlcus aboue with an instrument of gold.  For &thorn;ilke maner of|brennynge rectifie&thorn; weel &thorn;e membre /</P>
<P>&THORN;e cause whi &thorn;at summe vlcus <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="43b">is hard to consowde is, for an|yuel disposicioun &thorn;at is hid in &thorn;e bodi, &amp; &thorn;erfore it nedi&thorn; to rectifien|&thorn;e membre &amp; &thorn;e bodi as I haue seid tofore.  &amp; if &thorn;e cause be vpon,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>vpon</I>, error for <I>open</I>.</NOTE>|oon o&thorn;er manye, do awei &thorn;ilke cause or ellis &thorn;e manye causis, or &thorn;at|&thorn;ou go to &thorn;is principal cure / &THORN;ese ben &thorn;e causis &thorn;at letten consowdynge|of olde woundis: an yuel disposicioun of al &thorn;e bodi as|ydropisie; or ellis an yuel disposicioun of &thorn;e lyuere as if &thorn;at he be|to feble, as to hoot or to cold, to moist or to drie, wi&thorn; mater or|wi&thorn;oute mater, as wi&thorn; to greet hardenes; or ellis &thorn;e splene is to|feble to purge &thorn;e malancolient blood; or ellis to myche blood or|ellis to litil blood; or ellis &thorn;e veynes ben to fulle of blood &thorn;at goon|doun to &thorn;e vlcus; or elles &thorn;at glandeles &thorn;at ben kirnelis &thorn;at ben in|&thorn;e ground<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ground</I>.  See <I>grynd</I>, page 41, note 3.</NOTE> &thorn;at senden doun mater to the vlcus &thorn;at is in &thorn;e &thorn;ies &amp;|in &thorn;e leggis; or ellis &thorn;e lippis of &thorn;e vlcus ben to grete; or ellis|myche fleisch; or ellis mys-ordynaunce of dietynge or ellis an
<PB N="85">|inconuenient medicyn to &thorn;at membre or ellis &thorn;e lyme &thorn;at is hirt|ha&thorn; an yuel discrasie; or ellis &thorn;ilke vlcus is in an yuel place as in|&thorn;e eende of &thorn;e <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="44a">elbow&yogh;e; or ellis &thorn;e vlcus is al round; or ellis &thorn;e |boon &thorn;at is vndir &thorn;e vlcus is corrupt / Alle &thorn;ase tofore seid letten|vlcus to be heelid / wherfore it nedi&thorn; &thorn;e, to take kepe to alle &thorn;ese|&thorn;ingis tofore seid, to amende al &thorn;e bodi &amp; namely &thorn;o lymes &thorn;at han|principalte in mannes body, &amp; kepen alle &thorn;e lymes &thorn;at ben in her|naturel disposicioun with &thorn;ingis &thorn;at ben acordinge to her naturel|disposicioun, &thorn;o / &amp; if &thorn;ei ben discrasid, remeue &thorn;ilke discrasie wi&thorn;|&thorn;at, &thorn;at is contrarie to &thorn;e discrasie / also tempre &thorn;e qualite &amp; &thorn;e|quantite of &thorn;e blood &amp; streyne &thorn;e veyne if &thorn;at &thorn;ou brynge &thorn;idir|blood, or ellis if &thorn;at it be possible latt &thorn;e blood awey; vndo &thorn;e|glandeles &thorn;at ben kirnels &thorn;at sendin &thorn;ider mater, &amp; remeue deed|fleesch, smale &thorn;e lippis of woundis &thorn;at ben greete &amp; kutte hem|awey if &thorn;at &thorn;ou my&yogh;t do noon o&thorn;irwise; amende his dietynge; &amp;|brynge a&yogh;en &thorn;e rondnes of &thorn;ilke vlcus into a long forme aftir &thorn;e|lenk&thorn;e of &thorn;e membre with a knyf hoot brennynge / but if a veyne|or a senewe lette.  &amp; &thorn;ou schalt remoue &thorn;e boon &thorn;at is corrupt on|&thorn;is maner: in kuttynge awey al &thorn;e fleisch &amp; &thorn;e boon &thorn;at is corrupt|with an hoot <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="44b">iren, or wi&thorn; a medicyn &thorn;at schal be seid in &thorn;e laste |eende of &thorn;is book, or ellis it is bettere to don it awey wi&thorn; hoot
<PB N="86">|iren.  &amp; whanne &thorn;at &thorn;e boon &thorn;at is corrupt<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>corrrupt</I>.</NOTE> is vnkeuerid, schaue it|not as manye men doon, but touche harde &thorn;at boon with hoot|iren; &amp; aftirward heelde on &thorn;ilke boon hoot oile of rosis, &amp; leie on|oon of &thorn;e mundificatiuis &thorn;at ben in &thorn;e antidotarie whiche &thorn;at wolen|remoue &thorn;e rotid boon wi&thorn;oute violence / For vndirstonde weel &thorn;ou&yogh;|&thorn;at &thorn;ou clense &thorn;e rotid boon wi&thorn; schauynge or wi&thorn; filynge with|violence, neuere &thorn;e lattere kynde wole afterward don awey a schelle|of &thorn;ilke same boon, nou&yogh;t a&yogh;enstondynge &thorn;i schauynge &amp; &thorn;i rasynge /|wherfore in remeuynge &thorn;ilke boon &thorn;ou multipliest &thorn;i traueile &amp;|makist newe<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>newe</I>, error for <I>no</I>.</NOTE> mundificacion to &thorn;e fulle<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to &thorn;e fulle</I>.  Lat.: ad plenum.  See <I>Polychr</I>., iii. 443, he forgaf him the|trespas <I>at the fulle.</I></NOTE> &amp; &thorn;erof may come ofte|tymes an yuel festre.  An inconuenient medicyn is amendid in|considerynge &thorn;e complexioun of al &thorn;e body &amp; &thorn;e complexioun of &thorn;e|lyme &amp; &thorn;e gre of &thorn;e medicyn; for if &thorn;at &thorn;e membre be drie as &thorn;e|eeris &amp; al bony &amp; gristly lymes, &amp; &thorn;ei han greet putride &amp; rotschipe,|&thorn;anne &thorn;ou nedist a ful drie medicyn / &amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;e bodi or &thorn;e lymes| <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="45a">ben mene bitwene fatnes &amp; lenenes &thorn;at is nei&thorn;er to fatt ne to|leene, &thorn;anne &thorn;ou nedist a medicyn &thorn;at is in kynde mesurabiliche|driynge / &amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;e bodi or &thorn;e membre be natureliche moist, &amp; if|&thorn;at he haue a litil putrede or rotschipe, &thorn;anne &thorn;ou nedist a medicyn
<PB N="87">|&thorn;at is litil driynge / &amp; if &thorn;at .ij. membris ben in complexioun|I-liche euene, &amp; &thorn;e toon haue myche quytture, &amp; &thorn;e to&thorn;er litil|quytture, he &thorn;at ha&thorn; &thorn;e more quitture nedi&thorn; &thorn;e driere medicyn / &amp;|*he &thorn;at ha&thorn; but litil quytture, him nedi&thorn; his medicyn I-maad nou&yogh;t|fulliche so drie / &THORN;erfore it nedi&thorn; bi mesure &thorn;at &thorn;ou kepe naturel|&thorn;ing wi&thorn; &thorn;ing &thorn;at is acordinge to &thorn;e same naturel &thorn;ing / &amp; also|remeue with mesurable contrariouste &thorn;ing &thorn;at is a&yogh;ens kynde / But|&thorn;e quantite of medicyns &thorn;at schulden be leid to &thorn;e soor as galion|witnessi&thorn; mai not wi&thorn; lettris be writen / ne&thorn;eles it suffici&thorn; &thorn;at a|man diuise &thorn;e medicyn after<NOTE PLACE="foot">N. E. Dict. s. v., "after C. 2. c" gives later references for the use of|<I>after</I> conj. = according as, without relative particle.</NOTE> &thorn;e complexioun mai bere / For kynde|&thorn;at is wondirful, fulfilli&thorn; &thorn;ing &thorn;at is absent, &amp; &thorn;at. &thorn;at is to myche,|casti&thorn; awey, but if &thorn;at it be to myche a&yogh;en kynde; &amp; &thorn;anne kynde|muste nede faile in his kyndely worchinge / A medicyn mundificatif|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="45b">&amp; exciccatif &thorn;at is nessessarie in ech old holowe wounde,&mdash;&mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot">Both MSS. omit the end of the passage.  Lat. "Medicina vero mundificatiua|&amp; exiccatiua &mdash; &mdash; aut est fortior, quam conuenit, aut debilior competenti."|Then, as a heading to the next passage: "Significatio si medicina|est magis sicca quam oportet."  The <I>&thorn;at</I> in <I>&amp; &thorn;at may be knowe,</I> refers to this|omitted heading.</NOTE> </P>
<P>&amp; &thorn;at may be knowe bi &thorn;is maner / if &thorn;at &thorn;e medicyn make|&thorn;inne quytture &amp; blodi &amp; make &thorn;e wounde holower, &thorn;anne he|schulde be, &thorn;anne is medicyn to scharpe / &amp; if &thorn;e quytture be &thorn;icke|&amp; tow&yogh;, &thorn;anne is &thorn;e medicyn to li&thorn;e / &amp; also ano&thorn;er signe &thorn;at &thorn;e
<PB N="88">|medicyn is to scharp, &thorn;at &thorn;e place aboute &thorn;e wounde is to grene,|blak, reed, ei&thorn;er &yogh;elow; &amp; &thorn;anne &thorn;e sike man schal fele to greet|heete &amp; brennynge, also &thorn;e venym of &thorn;e wounde multiplie&thorn; / and|whanne &thorn;e vnkunnynge leche see&thorn; &thorn;ese accidentis tofore seid, he|ordeyne&thorn; a drie medicyn; &amp; so ech day &thorn;e wounde apeiri&thorn;.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>apeiri&thorn;</I> intr.  See Prompt. Parv. <I>Appeyryn</I>, or make wors.  Pejoro,|deterioro.</NOTE></P>
<P>&amp; &thorn;e signe &thorn;at &thorn;e medicyn is of feble driynge is, &thorn;at &thorn;e quitture|&amp; &thorn;e rotynes &thorn;at goi&thorn; out &thorn;erof is greet in substaunce, ponderous|&amp; vneuene, wan ou&thorn;ir pale &amp; &thorn;e membre is cold &amp; is whi&yogh;t ou&thorn;ir|wan, ou&thorn;ir cleer in colour ou&thorn;er soft; &amp; &thorn;e sike man feli&thorn; cold in|his membre / &amp; whanne &thorn;at &thorn;ou knowist &thorn;ese &thorn;ingis in &thorn;e firste|cause make not &thorn;i medicyn so drie, &amp; in &thorn;e secunde cause make &thorn;i|medicyn more drie, &amp; also chaunge &thorn;i worchinge as condicioun of| kynde askith <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="46a">bo&thorn;e of bodi &amp; membre as weel symple as compound|medicyns / He &thorn;at knowi&thorn; not &thorn;es canones. wel yuele schal he heele|woundis / wherfore manye lechis bryngen li&yogh;tliche woundis with her|yuel worchinge into &thorn;e worste olde woundis &thorn;e whiche moun not|aftir ben I-heelid bi a good leche / &THORN;ese ben li&yogh;t medicyns whiche|&thorn;at drien olde woundis &thorn;at neden a litil driynge: mastik, frank|encense, barli mele.  &amp; &thorn;ese medicyns ben sumwhat more driere:|yrios,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>yrios</I>.  Lat. Iris.  See Prior, <I>Dict</I>., p. 123.</NOTE> aristologie rotunda, orabum<NOTE PLACE="foot">"<I>Orobus</I>, gall. uesche, anglice thare uel mousespese."&mdash;Alphita, p. 131.</NOTE> &thorn;at is wiilde tare, lupines,
<PB N="89">|&thorn;e rotynes ei&thorn;er &thorn;e drie poudre of trees; &amp; &thorn;ese medicyns ben|strongere: balaustie, psidie,<NOTE PLACE="foot">"<I>Psidia</I> cortex est mali granati."&mdash;<I>Synonoma Barthol</I>., p. 35.</NOTE> rose, notts of cipris et cetera / &amp; &thorn;ese|ben li&yogh;t mundificatiuis: sugre, hony, water of barlich, gotis whay,|watir of &thorn;e see, watir of brimstoon &thorn;at clensi&thorn; &amp; hete&thorn;, water of alym|&thorn;at clensi&thorn; &amp; coldi&thorn;.  &amp; &thorn;ou schalt haue greet plente of enplastris,|mundificatiuis, oyntmentis compounned in &thorn;e antidotarie of &thorn;is book /</P>
