<HEAD>Now bigynne&thorn; &thorn;e secunde tretis of particuler|woundis of membris of office from &thorn;e heed to &thorn;e|foot / and first bigynne at anotamie of &thorn;e heed /|<NOTE PLACE="foot">Heading to this page: <I>Anotemy off &thorn;e hed &amp; woundes off the same.</I> /|Compare Vicary's <I>Anatomie,</I> ch. iii. p. 24.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Al &thorn;ing <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="55b">brefly ordeyned aftir my symple will diuisynge, which|&thorn;at longi&thorn; to &thorn;e firste tretis of &thorn;is book which &thorn;at holdi&thorn; certeyn|rulis &amp; techinge of surgerie vndir general chapitlis as we han bihi&yogh;t /|now we wolen bigynne to treten of curis aftir &thorn;at &thorn;e lymes ben in|mannes bodi. &amp; first I wole bigynne at &thorn;e heed &amp; at his anotamie,|&amp; so procede for&thorn; to ech membre dyuysynge &thorn;e anotamie of ech|membre, &amp; in ordeynynge &thorn;e curis of woundis &thorn;at ben maad in ech|sengle membre.  I seie &thorn;at &thorn;e heed is maad of &thorn;re parties: of a|fleischi partie, of a bony partie, &amp; a brawni partie.  &THORN;e fleischi|partie is aboue &thorn;e brayn panne, &thorn;e which &thorn;at is maad of an hery|skyn; &amp; &thorn;ilke skyn is fulfillid wi&thorn; braynes in euery partie /
<PB N="107"></P>
<P>&THORN;e heeris of &thorn;e heed weren for greet profite ordeyned &thorn;at nei&thorn;er|cold ne hoot, ne schulde not sodeynli entre &thorn;e poris of the skyn,|&amp; neuer-&thorn;e-lattere &thorn;at &thorn;e fumosite of &thorn;e heed my&yogh;te go out bi &thorn;e|poris &thorn;ere as &thorn;e heer growi&thorn;; &amp; &thorn;e heed my&yogh;te be &thorn;e more semeloker,|&amp; &thorn;at &thorn;e colouris of &thorn;e heeris of dyuers men my&yogh;te schewen &thorn;e complecciouns|of &thorn;e heedis // </P>
<P>&THORN;e skyn &thorn;at is <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="56a">aboue &thorn;e brayn panne is lacertose, &amp; ful of &thorn;icke|fleisch, &thorn;at he my&yogh;te wrie &thorn;e brayn panne, &thorn;at he schulde not fele|sodeynliche to greet heete ne to greet cold.  &THORN;e which skyn is maad|of sutil &thorn;redis of senewis &thorn;at comen fro &thorn;e brayn, &amp; of veynes &amp;|of arteries sotilliche I-maad; &amp; so &thorn;e skyn of &thorn;e heed is sotilliche|ioyned wi&thorn; &thorn;e skyn of al &thorn;e bodi / &amp; also &thorn;e skyn of &thorn;e heed is more|&thorn;ickere &thorn;an &thorn;e brain sculle, &thorn;at it schulde ben more rare<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>rare</I>.  Lat. rarus.</NOTE> &amp; more|porose, &thorn;at is to seie, more ful of hoolis / &THORN;e lacertis of &thorn;e skyn proceden|aftir &thorn;at &thorn;e goynge procedi&thorn; of &thorn;e heeris /</P>
<P>&THORN;e brayn panne is maad of manye boonys / &THORN;e firste summe,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat. Prima nanque summa ..</NOTE> &thorn;e|whiche &thorn;at holdi&thorn; &thorn;e prouitis &thorn;at longen to &thorn;e brayn panne, ha&thorn; .ij.|helpingis; oon helpinge is: &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at an hurtynge come to oon boon,|neuere-&thorn;e-lattere he schulde not falle to alle &thorn;e boonys / &THORN;e secunde|help is, oon boon &thorn;at is to hard in oon partie ne schulde not be so
<PB N="108">|hard in ano&thorn;ir partie. / &THORN;e secunde summe, &thorn;e which &thorn;at wi&thorn;halt &thorn;e|helpingis &thorn;at ben vndir &thorn;e brayn panne, ha&thorn; wi&thorn;inne him. iiij.| helpingis; &thorn;e whiche helpingis ben ful maad by &thorn;e <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="56b">semis &thorn;at ben|of &thorn;e brayn panne; ne &thorn;e helpingis my&yogh;te not be maad, but if &thorn;at|&thorn;er were manye boonys / &THORN;e first help is, &thorn;at &thorn;e veynes my&yogh;ten go|doun bi &thorn;e semis of &thorn;e brayn panne berynge<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. inserts <I>&amp;</I>.</NOTE> norischinge to &thorn;e|same brayn<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>panne</I> after <I>brayn</I> cancelled.</NOTE> / &THORN;e secunde help is, &thorn;at &thorn;e senewis &thorn;at comen out of|&thorn;e brayn my&yogh;te haue wey in goynge out / &THORN;e &thorn;ridde help is, &thorn;at &thorn;e|fumes of &thorn;e brayn my&yogh;ten haue wey of smokyng out / &THORN;e four&thorn;e is,|&thorn;at nei&thorn;er dura mater, ne pia mater, &thorn;at as &thorn;ei ben hangid, ne my&yogh;te|not greue &thorn;e brayn.</P>
<P>So &thorn;at &thorn;e brayn panne is maad of ij. sme&thorn;e li&yogh;t tablis, &thorn;at oon|is aboue, &thorn;e to&thorn;ir is byne&thorn;e / &amp; &thorn;ei ben sumwhat spongious in &thorn;e|myddis, &amp; rare &thorn;at &thorn;e smoke of &thorn;e heete my&yogh;te bettere passe out &amp;|&thorn;ei ben sme&thorn;e &thorn;at &thorn;ei my&yogh;ten not greue &thorn;e brayn / Dyuers men &thorn;at|maken dyuers anotamie dyuyden &thorn;e brayn panne diuerslych / summen|noumbren mo boonys &thorn;an summe o&thorn;ir speken of / but so&thorn;enes|is, &thorn;at &thorn;er ben .vj. &amp; oon which &thorn;at susteyne&thorn; &thorn;e sixte.  &THORN;e firste|boon is clepid &thorn;e boon of &thorn;e forheed or ellis coronale, &amp; he bigynne&thorn;|from &thorn;e browis &amp; lasti&thorn; to &thorn;e seem &thorn;at departi&thorn; &thorn;e heed quarter.
<PB N="109">|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="57a">&amp; &thorn;ilke is clepid coronale / &THORN;is boon ha&thorn; in sum maner of men a |smal seem in foldynge of &thorn;e forheed, &amp; &thorn;erfore sum men seyn|&thorn;at &thorn;er ben .ij. boonis.  ij o&thorn;ir boonys ben ioyned with &thorn;ilke boon|coronable in &thorn;e myddis of &thorn;e heed ouer&thorn;wert ouer; &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at</I> insertion.</NOTE> &thorn;ei ben|bounde togidere bi oon ioynture, &thorn;e which &thorn;at strecchi&thorn; from bifore|to bihynde to &thorn;e lenk&thorn;e of &thorn;e heed, &thorn;e which is clepid sagittales,|by as myche as he is schape lijk an arowe / &amp; &thorn;ese .ij. boonys ben|clepid nerualia bi-cause &thorn;at &thorn;e figure of &thorn;e seem &thorn;at is with &thorn;e|coronable is &thorn;e figure of a senewe ei&thorn;er of a corde / &THORN;ese boonys ben|in &thorn;e hi&yogh;este coppe of &thorn;e heed &amp; byhynde in &thorn;e nolle &thorn;er is a boon|&thorn;e which is clepid alauda.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Latin: "Quartum os est ex parte posteriori in puppi; et conjungitur|cum pr&aelig;dictis nervalibus mediante una commissura ad modum liter&aelig; laud&aelig;|grec&aelig;."  The word <I>lauda</I> is a corruption of <I>lambda</I>.</NOTE> &amp; it is maad in &thorn;e symilitude of &thorn;is: <FIGURE></FIGURE>:|which &thorn;at is ioyned wi&thorn; &thorn;e boones nerualibus tofore seid bi &thorn;e mene|of oon &thorn;an I-made to &thorn;e lijknes of &thorn;e boon tofore seid. &amp; &thorn;ese &thorn;re|semes whiche &thorn;at ioynen togidere &thorn;e .iiij. boonys tofore seid, ben|maad as it were two sawis, &thorn;e whiche tee&thorn; ben ioyned, ech of hem|in o&thorn;ir in &thorn;is maner <FIGURE></FIGURE> / &amp; &thorn;is ioynynge togidere of oon|boon wi&thorn; ano&thorn;ir was maad bi-cause of iuvamentis &thorn;at I haue told|toforn;<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="57b"> &thorn;er is no boon ioyned with ano&thorn;er as &thorn;ese boonys ben. 
<PB N="110">|Vndir &thorn;e boon &thorn;at is clepid alauda, &thorn;er is a ful hard boon &amp; holid|in &thorn;e myddil, &thorn;e which boon susteyne&thorn; alle &thorn;e boonys of &thorn;e heed.|&THORN;e which boon is clepid passillus, &amp; he is ioyned byne&thorn;e wi&thorn; &thorn;e firste|boon of &thorn;e nake.  &THORN;e schap of &thorn;e coniunccioun of &thorn;e .v. boonis of|&thorn;e heed is in &thorn;is maner <FIGURE></FIGURE>.  Bo&thorn;e on &thorn;e ri&yogh;tside &amp; on &thorn;e lift side|of &thorn;e forseid boonys, whiche &thorn;at ben clepid nerualia *[whiche &thorn;at be&thorn;|in lengthe in &thorn;e heyest place of &thorn;e hed, &thorn;ere ben twey bonys on ei&thorn;ere|syde.] &amp; &thorn;o boonys &thorn;at vndir setten ben clepid ossa mendosa.  &amp; &thorn;ese|boonys in oon partie ben ful hard &thorn;ere as &thorn;e hole of &thorn;e eere passi&thorn; &thorn;oru&yogh;,|&amp; &thorn;ei ben clepid petrosa; &amp; summen seien &thorn;at &thorn;er ben .iiij. boonys ij.|on ei&thorn;ir side / &amp; whanne &thorn;at alle &thorn;e boonys of &thorn;e heed ben ioyned|togidere, &thorn;ou schalt fynde in so&thorn;fastnes &thorn;at &thorn;er ben but vj. boonys,|whanne &thorn;at &thorn;ou rekenest os<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>as</I>.</NOTE> coronale for oon boon, &amp; .ij. boonys|&thorn;at ben clepid mendose, ij. &amp; oon &thorn;at ben iij, &amp; o boon &thorn;at is clepid|alauda. &amp; ij. boonys &thorn;at ben clepid nerualia &thorn;at ben .vj.; &amp; &thorn;e|.vij. boon is clepid passillare, &thorn;e which is not of &thorn;e boones of &thorn;e|heed, but he susteyne&thorn; alle &thorn;e o&thorn;ere boonys of &thorn;e heed.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Add. MS. 10,440, fol. 2: <I>"&amp; he is vnterberynge in &thorn;e hynder partie al|&thorn;e bones of &thorn;e heued, &amp; &thorn;erfore he is clepid &thorn;e berere vp, or paxillus."</I></NOTE> &amp; iij. maner| of semes <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="58a">maki&thorn; coniunccioun of alle &thorn;e boonys in &thorn;is maner <FI