<PB N="121">|good disposicioun &thorn;ilke yuel accidentis fallen; but sumtyme in &thorn;e|bigynnynge &thorn;ese yuel accidentis fallen wickid, &amp; aftirward bi good|gouernaile &amp; good help of &thorn;e leche &thorn;ilke yuel accidentis ben|departid &amp; good come&thorn;, and &thorn;anne it is a [good]* signe, for it bitokene&thorn;|strenk&thorn;e of kynde, hauynge no drede of &thorn;e sijknes, &amp;|kunnynge of &thorn;e leche / O holi goost, al &thorn;ing fulfillynge, alle &thorn;ingis|sanctifiynge, &amp; alle &thorn;ingis li&yogh;tnynge, &amp; alle &thorn;ingis gouernynge, opene|&thorn;e y&yogh;en of hem &thorn;at loken &amp; reden on &thorn;is book, &thorn;at &thorn;ei moun vndirstonde|&thorn;at &thorn;ing &thorn;at is weel seid, &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ei moun demene<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>demene</I>, O.Fr. "demener," for <I>demen</I>.</NOTE> &thorn;oru&yogh; &thorn;i|cleernes &thorn;at, &thorn;at is yuel seid, &amp; specialy in &thorn;is caas<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>in &thorn;is caas.</I>  Lat.: in isto passu.  See below <I>pas</I>.</NOTE> where &thorn;at|oonly not I &thorn;at am vnwijs &amp; vnkunnynge, but also greete maistris|&amp; more kunnynge han writen sotilliche, &amp; han sett in &thorn;is caas|dyuers vndirstondynge.  Ne &thorn;ei ne I ne foond no wey in &thorn;is werk|&thorn;at my&yogh;te us make sikir, specialiche in scryuyngis of &thorn;e brayn|panne, in &thorn;e whiche cure<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>cure,</I> above line.</NOTE> dyvers men haue<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>have,</I> above line.</NOTE> I-wrou&yogh;t dyuersliche. </P>
