orn;ei casten him awey, &amp; aftirward &thorn;ei proceden
<PB N="127">|for&thorn; in o&thorn;ere maner &thorn;ingis as it is seid tofore / For whanne &thorn;ou|desirist way of<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;e</I> struck through after <I>of</I>.</NOTE> trepaninge [&thorn;is manere trepanynge]* suffici&thorn; to|&thorn;ee in &thorn;e rimelis of &thorn;e brayn panne.  &THORN;is schal be &thorn;e foorme of a|trepane [with &thorn;e whiche &thorn;e brayn scolle schal be trepaned wi&thorn;]*|<FIGURE></FIGURE>.  &amp; &thorn;is is &thorn;e foorme of a spatinam, wi&thorn; &thorn;e which a man|schal kutte from oon hole to ano&thorn;er hole <FIGURE></FIGURE>.  &amp; &thorn;ou schalt|smyte wi&thorn; a mal<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>mal</I>, Lat. malleus.</NOTE> ei&thorn;er an hamer on &thorn;e greet eende; &amp; whanne &thorn;ou|hast remeued of &thorn;e boon &thorn;at schal be remoued, euene &thorn;e brynkis|with schauynge, &thorn;at &thorn;ou mowe not leue no maner scharpnes in &thorn;e|brynkis.  &THORN;is is &thorn;e maner of &thorn;e schap <FIGURE></FIGURE>, <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="67a">&amp; &thorn;is schaue schal |kutte on &thorn;e side &thorn;at foldi&thorn; ynward, &amp; it schal be blunt on &thorn;e oon|side &thorn;at is outward.  &amp; &thorn;ei fulfillen &thorn;e wounde &thorn;at is wi&thorn;inne &thorn;e|fleisch wi&thorn;outfor&thorn;, as I haue seid, with &thorn;e cloo&thorn; expressid of &thorn;e|white of an ey &amp; lynet, til &thorn;at &thorn;e wounde be ful, &amp; also til &thorn;at|&thorn;e kynde haue regendrid a repeirement, &thorn;e which schal fulfille|&thorn;e place &thorn;ere as &thorn;e boon was don awey.  Aftirward &thorn;ei curen|&thorn;e wounde aftir comoun cure of woundis / Alle o&thorn;ere maner of|trepanacioun is comprehendid vndir o summe, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at summen|ordeyne particuler aftir her dyuyse, diuers maners.</P>
<P>But bi as myche as I haue not seen in &thorn;is caas no way &thorn;at
<PB N="128">|my&yogh;te remeue me from doute, bi as myche as I haue saied bi longe|tyme, bo&thorn;e bi summe auctouris experimentis, &amp; also bi myn experiment,|&amp; &thorn;at wei is not certeyn / &thorn;erfore here &thorn;ei Galien, &thorn;at sei&thorn;:|if we mowe remeue quytture wi&thorn;oute doynge awei of boonys &thorn;at|schulde be do awey, it is good / And auicen &amp; serapie<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Serapie</I>, probably Ser. the Elder, an Arab physician, cc. 900.</NOTE> acorden to|&thorn;e same sentence of cure of heed ak&thorn;e &thorn;at come&thorn; of smytynge or|ellis of fallynge, where &thorn;at he towchi&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>towchi&thorn;</I> for <I>techi&thorn;.</I></NOTE> &thorn;e worchinge of hurtis of| &thorn;e brayn <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="67b">panne, not bi trepanacioun, but bi emplastris &amp; medicyns /|&amp; also I took good hede &thorn;at manye mo men ben heelid bi maner|of medicyns &amp; emplastris, &thorn;an ben heelid bi trapanes, &thorn;at ben|peersynge or &thorn;rillynge / For I ne vse not instrumentis to remeue|the boon but in two causis / &THORN;e oon cause is if &thorn;at &thorn;e brayn panne|be so myche I-slend<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>islend</I>, Add. MS. <I>ysclend</I>.  See <I>slent</I>, to tear, to rend (Dorset).&mdash;Halliwell.</NOTE> &thorn;at &thorn;e part &thorn;at is broke, entre vndir &thorn;e partie|&thorn;at is hool / &THORN;e secunde caas is, if ony pece be departid from &thorn;e|brayn panne, &thorn;e which &thorn;at pricki&thorn; duram matrem / In &thorn;e firste|caas dura mater is compressid.  In &thorn;e secunde caas dura mater is|prickid, which is cause of ak&thorn;e, &amp; akynge is cause of drawynge|humouris, &thorn;ere engendri&thorn; an empostyme vpon &thorn;e same pannicle, &thorn;e|which is cause of a crampe, &amp; of o&thorn;ere accidentis tofore seid; &amp;
<PB N="129">|at &thorn;e laste &thorn;ei bryngen dee&thorn; to &thorn;e pacient /  In &thorn;ese .ij. causis|I leeue hem<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hem</I> for <I>am; leeue</I> is erroneously added in margin.</NOTE> constreyned to remeue a boon wi&thorn; handely<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>handely</I> ne. handy.</NOTE> instrumentis.|In alle o&thorn;ere maners of brechis ei&thorn;er in creueis, in what|maner &thorn;at &thorn;ei happen, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at I be not siker of &thorn;e pacientis lijf,|ne&thorn;eles I procede in &thorn;is maner with more trist, bisekynge alwey|help of god, &thorn;e which &thorn;at <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="68a">ha&thorn; heelid mo men bi myn hondis, &thorn;at |am his instrument, &thorn;an haue ben deed, nou&yogh;t a&yogh;enstondynge alle|my cautels &amp; helpinge.  For so&thorn;e &thorn;at I haue biholde so&thorn;liche resonis|&amp; &thorn;e proces of o&thorn;ere auctouris, I holde &thorn;is wey lasse dredeful &thorn;an|ony o&thorn;ere / for I folowe &thorn;e sentence of Galien, which &thorn;at sei&thorn;:|if &thorn;at a man haue but o wei to his hele,<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>ixele</I>.</NOTE> it is good &thorn;at he holde|&thorn;ilke wey, &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at it be yuel.</P>
