<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="2">
<HEAD>The secunde chapitle of woundis of &thorn;e face &amp;|anotamie of &thorn;e same.</HEAD>
<P>Woundis &thorn;at ben maad in &thorn;e face, or &thorn;ei be maad wi&thorn; a swerd|or wi&thorn; sum dinge<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>dinge</I>, in margin.</NOTE> ellis &thorn;at woundi&thorn;, or &thorn;ei ben maad wi&thorn; pricknyge|of a knyf, arowe, ei&thorn;er spere.  It is necessarie &thorn;at a surgian haue|more diligence in &thorn;e woundis of &thorn;e face, for it is a place &thorn;at is|myche seen, &amp; it is wel to do make<NOTE PLACE="foot">Compare: <I>&thorn;is instrument may &yogh;e do make wi&thorn;oute grete cost.</I> Quinte|Essence, p. 62.</NOTE> a sotil<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a sotil</I>, in margin.</NOTE> cicatrice / A wounde
<PB N="142">|&thorn;at is maad wi&thorn; a swerd or wi&thorn; sum&thorn;ing semblable &thorn;at is alwei in|lenk&thorn;e, a man muste sotilliche sowen &amp; gaderen &thorn;e parties of &thorn;e|wounde togidere / &amp; for &thorn;at manye men li&yogh;en of &thorn;e wounde of &thorn;e|nose, &thorn;ei seien &thorn;at oon bar his nose kutt of in his hond, &thorn;e which|nose was afterward sett a&yogh;en in his owne kynde; &thorn;e which is an open lesynge / For &thorn;e spirit of lijf of felynge &amp; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="75a">|<NOTE PLACE="foot">Heading to this page: <I>Off wondes off the fface &amp; Anotumy off &thorn;e|same ffrom the face to the ffote.</I></NOTE>meuynge passi&thorn;, whanne|a membre is depertid from &thorn;e bodi / I wole bigynne at a wounde of &thorn;e|nose &thorn;at is kutt in lenk&thorn;e, &thorn;e which cure is li&yogh;t to hele / Brynge &thorn;e|parties togidere of &thorn;e wounde &amp; sowe hem, &amp; worche aboute &thorn;e wounde|as I haue seid tofore in &thorn;e chapitle of woundis / &amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;e nose|were kutt ouer&thorn;wert doun to &thorn;e ouer lippe, &amp; ne&thorn;eles &thorn;at &thorn;e ouer lippe|&amp; &thorn;e nose were kutt al awey, but &thorn;at it held faste at bo&thorn;e &thorn;e eendis|of &thorn;e eendis of &thorn;e wounde, &thorn;anne sette a&yogh;en &thorn;e nose in his propre place,|&thorn;e nose&thorn;rillis ech a&yogh;en o&thorn;ir as &thorn;ei weren toforn, &amp; make two smale|tentis of wex &amp; putte on ei&thorn;ir nose&thorn;rille aboue &thorn;e wounde, if &thorn;at &thorn;ou|maist, &amp; &thorn;anne make a poynt bi &thorn;e space of a litil fyngre from &thorn;e oon|eende of &thorn;e wounde, &amp; ano&thorn;er poynt at &thorn;e o&thorn;ere eende of &thorn;e wounde,|&amp; ano&thorn;ir poynt in &thorn;e myddil of &thorn;e nose a&yogh;en &thorn;e forheed; and aftirward|a poynt on ei&thorn;er side of &thorn;e nose, aftirward make [a poynt]*|bitwene eueri poynt, so &thorn;at &thorn;ou haue in noumbre of alle &thorn;e poyntis
<PB N="143">|whanne &thorn;ei ben ful maad, .ix.  Caste &thorn;e poudre &thorn;at is tofore seid|vpon &thorn;e wounde, &thorn;at is maad of <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="75b">lime, frank encense, &amp; sandragoun|/ &amp; take &thorn;e white of an ey &amp; oile of rosis, &amp; bete hem togidere, |&amp; wete &thorn;erinne a lynnen cloo&thorn; &amp; leie aboue &thorn;e wounde / Aftirward|bynde* &thorn;erto &thorn;re plumaciols, oon vndirne&thorn;e, ano&thorn;er on &thorn;e oon side,|ano&thorn;ir on &thorn;e to&thorn;ir side / &amp; &thorn;anne bynde &thorn;e nose wi&thorn; two bandis /|&THORN;e toon schal holde vp &thorn;e nose &thorn;at he may not discende dounward /|&thorn;e to&thorn;ir schal be leid aboue &thorn;at he mowe kepe &thorn;e plumaciols, poudre,|&amp; &thorn;e sowynge / &amp; &thorn;ilke boond &thorn;at is vnder &thorn;e nose &thorn;at halt &thorn;e nose|vpward, schal be knytt<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>kutt</I>.</NOTE> aboue vpon &thorn;e heed, &amp; aftirward he schal be|turned ouertwert ouer &thorn;e forheed, &thorn;at he mowe holde &thorn;e boond, &thorn;at|&thorn;e nose decline to nei&thorn;ir<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>&thorn;e ne&thorn;ir.</I></NOTE> side. &amp; &thorn;e boond &thorn;at is leid aboue &thorn;e nose,|schal be bounden bihynde in &thorn;e nolle / &amp; aftirward he schal turne a&yogh;en|aboue &thorn;e nose, holdynge &thorn;e plumaciols &thorn;at &thorn;ei moun not wagge to|nei&thorn;ir side aboute &thorn;e sowynge; &amp; aboute &thorn;e forheed, &thorn;ou schalt leie|&thorn;e defensif of bole, &amp; aftirward &thorn;ou schalt worche on &thorn;e wounde of|&thorn;e nose, as I haue seid in a wounde of fleisch in &thorn;e four&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>four&thorn;e</I> for <I>firste</I>.</NOTE> tretis / </P>
<P>&THORN;e woundis &thorn;at ben maad in o&thorn;ere parties of &thorn;e face <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="76a">as wi&thorn;|a swerd or ony &thorn;ing semblable, brynge hem togidere &amp; sowe hem &amp;|cure hem, as it is conteyned in general chapitlis of woundis, takynge
<PB N="144">|hede herto &thorn;at &thorn;e sowynge &thorn;at is maad in &thorn;e face schal be more|sotil &amp; fairer &thorn;an in ony o&thorn;ere partie of &thorn;e body / &amp; &thorn;ou maist|make a sowynge in &thorn;e face, if &thorn;at &thorn;e wounde be not to myche, on|&thorn;is maner / Take mastik, sandragoun &amp; poudre hem &amp; tempre hem|togidere wi&thorn; &thorn;e white of an ey to &thorn;e &thorn;ickenesse of hony, &amp; wete|&thorn;erinne two pecis of lynnen cloo&thorn; as longe as &thorn;e wounde / &amp; leie &thorn;e|toon on &thorn;e oon side of &thorn;e wounde, &amp; &thorn;e o&thorn;er on &thorn;e to&thorn;ir side &amp; lete|hem drien / &amp; aftirward make &thorn;e wounde sumwhat to blede, &amp;|&thorn;anne brynge &thorn;e parties of &thorn;e wounde togidere; &amp; sowe &thorn;ilke .ij.|pecis togidere, &amp; caste aboue poudre of lyme, frankencense, sandragoun|tofore seid, &amp; wete a clo&thorn; in &thorn;e white of an ey &amp; oile of|rosis, &amp; leie aboue al togidere, &amp; kepe &thorn;e partiee wi&thorn; ligature &amp;|prosede for&thorn; in alle &thorn;ingis as I haue tofore seid /</P>
<P>&amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;e wounde be maad wi&thorn; a dart or wi&thorn; an arewe &amp; &thorn;e|arowe be drawe out &amp; &thorn;e wounde be myche sene, &thorn;anne &thorn;e cure is| <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="76b">&thorn;e same &thorn;at was seid in &thorn;e same chapitle or elles in &thorn;e firste tretis,|whe&thorn;er &thorn;at &thorn;er be a senewe prickid ei&thorn;ir noon.  But if &thorn;e arowe|heed were entriged in ony priuy place of &thorn;e face, so &thorn;at it my&yogh;te|not be seen, &thorn;anne euery man bisie him to knowe bi his witt how|&thorn;at &thorn;e sike man stood, whanne &thorn;at he was smyte, &amp; whens &thorn;at &thorn;e|arowe cam, &amp; to what partie &thorn;e wounde strecchi&thorn;, &thorn;at he mowe loke
<PB N="145">|if &thorn;at he mowe fynde ony maner wey how he may drawe out &thorn;ilke|arowe-heed; &amp; &thorn;anne drawe him out &thorn;e best maner wey &thorn;at he|may / &amp; if he may not, heelde he in &thorn;e wounde oile of rosis &amp; &thorn;e|&yogh;elke of an ey togidere medlid; &amp; wi&thorn; &thorn;is medicyn worche in &thorn;e|wounde, til &thorn;at kynde schewe sum maner wey / Manye men han|born an arowe-heed in &thorn;e parties of her face bi longe tyme; &amp;|after longe tyme kynde ha&thorn; cast out &thorn;e arowe heed, or ellis he ha&thorn;|schewid sum wey bi &thorn;e which wey &thorn;ilke arowe-heed my&yogh;te be taken|out.  &amp; &thorn;ou must take hede bi al &thorn;i mi&yogh;t &thorn;at, whanne &thorn;at &thorn;ou|sowist &thorn;e woundis of &thorn;e face, &thorn;at &thorn;e mou&thorn; be not crokid, but make|so sli&yogh;ly &thorn;i sowynge &thorn;at &thorn;ilke accident may <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="77a">not fallen; &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ou|maist do weel, if &thorn;at &thorn;ou cowdist ordeyne weel &thorn;i sowynge / &amp; if |&thorn;at &thorn;ou canst, kepe weel &thorn;i sowynge wi&thorn; plumaciols and wi&thorn;|byndyngis //  //  //</P>
</DIV4>
<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="3">
<HEAD>The &thorn;ridde chapitle of &thorn;e secunde tretis is of|woundis of &thorn;e necke &amp; anotamie of the same.</HEAD>
<P>Bi &thorn;e necke is conteyned al &thorn;e place &thorn;at is bitwene &thorn;e heed &amp;|&thorn;e schuldris, &thorn;e which anotamie I wole telle as I haue bihi&yogh;t /|Summen maken difference bitwene &thorn;e necke &amp; &thorn;e wesaunt<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>wesaunt</I> gula; <I>wesande</I>, ysophagus.  Wright W., page 676, XV. cent.|See <I>Vicary</I>, page 47, note 4.</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;e
<PB N="146">|&thorn;rote-bolle, &amp; alle &thorn;ese ben comprehendid vndir &thorn;e name of &thorn;e|necke.  In &thorn;e necke &thorn;er ben .vij. spondelis &thorn;at is to seie whirlboonys|/ whirlboonys of &thorn;e rigge.  &THORN;e firste of &thorn;e boonys is bounde|wi&thorn; a boon of &thorn;e heed &thorn;at is clepid passillare<NOTE PLACE="foot">See <I>Vicary</I>. page 44, note 2.</NOTE> with manye smale|feble ligamentis; &amp; &thorn;ei were feble bi-cause &thorn;at &thorn;ilke ioynt next to|&thorn;e heed my&yogh;te meue many weies.  &amp; &thorn;e cause whi &thorn;at &thorn;er were|smale ligamentis multiplied in &thorn;at ioynt, &thorn;at manye smale my&yogh;ten|susteyne a greet bur&thorn;un as weel as a fewe greete; &amp; if &thorn;at &thorn;er were| a fewe greete, &thorn;ei weren not so able to be meued / &THORN;e firste spondile|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="77b">is bounde to &thorn;e secunde / &thorn;e secunde to &thorn;e &thorn;ridde, &thorn;e &thorn;ridde to|&thorn;e four&thorn;e / &thorn;e four&thorn;e to &thorn;e fif&thorn;e, &thorn;e fif&thorn;e to &thorn;e sixte / &thorn;e sixte to &thorn;e|seuen&thorn;e / &thorn;e seuen&thorn;e is bounde loseliche to &thorn;e firste spondile of &thorn;e|rigge, &thorn;at &thorn;e necke my&yogh;te more li&yogh;tliche meuen, which &thorn;at is clepid|&thorn;e .viij. spondile / whanne &thorn;at &thorn;ou rekenest [from &thorn;e hed dunwarde]*|Seuene peire of senewis proceden out [by &thorn;ese .vii. spondelis.|&THORN;e firste peire of synwe procede&thorn; out]* bitwene &thorn;e firste|spondilis and<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>of</I>.  Add. MS. 10,440, fol. 2: <I>"&amp; he is vnterberynge in &thorn;e hynder|partie al &thorn;e bones of &thorn;e heued, &amp; &thorn;erfore he is clepid &thorn;e berere vp|or paxillus."</I></NOTE> &thorn;e boon of &thorn;e heed &thorn;at is clepid passillare / &THORN;e secunde|peire of senewis is bore bitwene &thorn;e firste spondile &amp; &thorn;e secunde, &amp;|so euery peire passen out bitwene ech spondile / &THORN;ese senewis ben
