<PB N="152">|greet, wet in &thorn;e &yogh;elke of an ey &amp; oile of rosis hoot, &amp; so holde &thorn;e|wounde open, til &thorn;at he &yogh;eue quytture, &amp; aftir clense him &amp; aftir|consowde him / Vndirstonde &thorn;e perilis &thorn;at comen for [wondys]* &thorn;at|ben maad in &thorn;is place / &THORN;e firste perel is: if &thorn;at &thorn;e necke be kutt|ouer&thorn;wert wi&thorn; a swerd, so &thorn;at &thorn;e necke-boon &amp; &thorn;e marie of &thorn;e|necke-boon be al atwo, it is deedliche.  &amp; if &thorn;at nucha, &thorn;at is|mary of &thorn;e necke boon, is not kutt al atwo but is hurt, it is perile|of lesynge, felynge &amp; meuynge,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: est periculum amissionis sensus et motus.</NOTE> &amp; at &thorn;e laste be deed, but if &thorn;at|medicyns &thorn;at I schal telle moun helpe / &amp; if &thorn;at ony veyne or ony|greet senewe be kutt ouer&thorn;wert, I suppose &thorn;at he be heelid, &thorn;e|necke schal neuere haue<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>haue</I>, in margin.</NOTE> his free meuynge; &amp; if &thorn;at ony of &thorn;e|veynes organik, &thorn;e whiche &thorn;at ben clepid guydes, or ellis ony of &thorn;e|arteries &thorn;at ben vndir hem be kutt, it is drede of sodeyn dee&thorn;, for| sodeyn exalacioun of &thorn;e spiritis &amp; also for affinite of &thorn;e herte; &amp;|also if &thorn;at &thorn;e cane of &thorn;e lungis be kutt ouer&thorn;wert<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="81a"> al atwo, for &thorn;e|more partie it is deedliche / Also it is seid, &thorn;at if &thorn;e veynes &thorn;at|ben bihynde &thorn;e eeris bee kutt al atwo, he ne schal neuere engendre.|And also sumtyme it is kutt ei&thorn;ir prickid &thorn;e senewe &thorn;at is clepid|reuersif, &thorn;at is vndir bo&thorn;e sidis of &thorn;e eere, of &thorn;e whiche kuttynge|or prickynge euermore is maad hosnesse<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hosnesse.  Prompt. Parv</I>., p. 248.  "<I>hoorsnesse</I>, Rancor."</NOTE> / And if &thorn;at &thorn;e places
<PB N="153">|ben peersid with an arowe, &amp; &thorn;ou&yogh; &thorn;at trache arterie be peersid or|ellis ysophage, so &thorn;at nucha be nou&yogh;t prickid bi &thorn;e mydle, &thorn;anne|&yogh;itt he may be heelid wi&thorn; gode medicyns &amp; acordynge.</P>
<P>&THORN;ou schalt helpe nucha &thorn;at is hurt in &thorn;is maner: &thorn;ou schalt|helde into &thorn;e wounde, in &thorn;e bigynnynge, oile of rosis, &amp; aftirward|do yn oile of rosis &amp; &yogh;elke of an ey medlid togidere, and &thorn;ou schalt|be bisy in al maner to aswage ak&thorn;e; &amp; whanne &thorn;at quytture is|maad, &thorn;anne leie a mundificatif wi&thorn; medicyns comfortatiuis &amp; incarnatiuis|maad in &thorn;is maner / Take oile of rosis colate <ABBR EXPAN="[dram]">&yogh;</ABBR> .iiij., wex,|rosyn of ech two dragmis, terbentine .iij. &yogh;, frankencense, mastik|of ech .i. &yogh;, mirre, sarcocol,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Sarcocolla</I>, Gr.<GAP DESC="Greek">, "is the Gumme or liquore of a tre growyng|in Persia."  Halle, <I>Table</I>, p. 109.</NOTE> mummie<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>mummie</I>, mumia.  See Halle, <I>Table</I>, p. 72, and Notes.</NOTE> of ech <ABBR EXPAN="[dram]">&yogh;</ABBR> .<ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>., barly mele <ABBR EXPAN="[dram]">&yogh;</ABBR> <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>.,|streyne it on a cloo&thorn; &amp; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="81b">leie it on &thorn;e nucha &thorn;at is hurt.  &amp; &thorn;ei &thorn;at |hereof<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>of here.</I></NOTE> pronosticacioun schulde go tofore, &thorn;e which schulde schewe|to yuel, ne&thorn;eles bi &thorn;is medicyn &thorn;er come&thorn; a rectificacioun to &thorn;e|nucha, &amp; melioracioun of meuynge of lymes, &thorn;at ben byne&thorn;e &thorn;e|place of &thorn;e nucha &thorn;at is hurt, more helpinge, &thorn;at seme&thorn; possible to|&thorn;e leche. For &thorn;er is no &thorn;ing vnpossible to stalwor&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>stalworthe</I>.  See Skeat, <I>Et. Dict.</I>, s. v. Stalwart.</NOTE> nature; namely,|whanne &thorn;at it is holpen wi&thorn; a good leche &amp; wi&thorn; &thorn;ingis, &thorn;at ben
<PB N="154">|helpinge &amp; acordynge to a good intencioun / Here vndirstonde &thorn;at|al maner wounde &thorn;at peersi&thorn; to &thorn;e substaunce of &thorn;e brayn or ellis|to &thorn;e nucha, so &thorn;at bi &thorn;er hurtynge of &thorn;e nucha &thorn;e meuynge &amp; &thorn;e|felynge of summe lymes ben lost, nameliche from &thorn;e whirle-boonys|of &thorn;e rigge, of &thorn;e reynes vpward, &amp; al maner wounde &thorn;at is maad|in &thorn;e extremitees of<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>as</I>.  Lat. in extremitatibus lacertorum.</NOTE> &thorn;e lacertis<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lacertis</I>, the sinewy part of the arm.  See <I>Vicary</I>, p. 57, note 1.</NOTE> as .iij. fyngir mele<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>iij fyngir mele brede</I>.  Lat. tribus digitis.</NOTE> brede vndir &thorn;e|schuldris, ei&thorn;er .iii. fyngir mele brede aboue &thorn;e elbowe ei&thorn;er byne&thorn;e,|ei&thorn;ir .iij. fyngir mele aboue &thorn;e kne or byne&thorn;e / &amp; ech wounde &thorn;at is| in a senewe place with strengest ak&thorn;e &amp; hardnes, <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="82a">schal be deemed|deedlich, for &thorn;e nobilte of &thorn;ilke brayn, &amp; for &thorn;e affinite of &thorn;e nucha|wi&thorn; &thorn;e brayn, of &thorn;e which nucha passi&thorn; as a reuere<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>r&emacr;uere.</I></NOTE> from a welle,|&amp; for &thorn;e affinite of &thorn;ilke senewe wi&thorn; &thorn;e brayn bi mene of nucha, of|&thorn;e whiche &thorn;ei passen out as a flood / Wherfore &thorn;ou schalt euermore|in sich maner woundis pronosteken deth, &amp; euermore fle as miche|as &thorn;ou my&yogh;t from vnresonable curis, but if &thorn;ou be with &thorn;e more|instaunce y-preied / Ne&thorn;eles sumtyme nature wi&thorn; good helpinge|worchi&thorn; &thorn;at seme&thorn; to &thorn;e leche vnpossible, neuer-&thorn;e-lattere loue noon|sich [cures]* but if &thorn;ou be greetliche preied &amp; &thorn;anne entermete of|&thorn;e cure of &thorn;e sike man //</P>
