<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="2">
<PB N="254">
<HEAD>Of &thorn;e passioun of eeris.</HEAD>
<P>As it is aforseid &thorn;at nerues comen fro &thorn;e brain to &thorn;e i&yogh;en / in|&thorn;e same maner nerues comen from &thorn;e brain &amp; goi&thorn; into &thorn;e| eris &amp; maki&thorn; heerynge &amp; ben instrumentis of witt.  <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="173b">&THORN;e|hoolis in a|mannes eeris ben maad in a deep holowe boon, &amp; it was bi &thorn;is|skille &thorn;at it schulde vndirstonde sownynge, &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;e sowne schulde|not come into &thorn;e brayn anoon, but alitil &amp; alitil bi degree, &amp; also|for &thorn;is skille &thorn;at &thorn;e coold eire ne &thorn;e hoot eire schulde not sodeinly|entre yn; &amp; &thorn;e wei &thorn;at goi&thorn; into a mannes eere, ne goi&thorn; not ri&yogh;t|for&thorn;, but hidir &amp; &thorn;idir, for if &thorn;e weie were ri&yogh;tfor&thorn;, it wolde &thorn;e|ra&thorn;ere be hurt of al maner &thorn;ing /  &THORN;e eere was maad of cartilaginis|&thorn;at is hardere &thorn;an fleisch &amp; neischer &thorn;an boon, &thorn;at it mi&yogh;te be|pliaunt.  &amp; if &thorn;ei schulde be maad oonly of fleisch, &thorn;ei schulde|haue noon sustentacioun for to bere hem vp.  &amp; if &thorn;ei hadden be|maad oonly of hard boon, &thorn;ei mi&yogh;ten not haue be meued, &amp; &thorn;erfore|itt was moost nede &thorn;at &thorn;ei weren cartilaginous: &thorn;at is as miche to|seie as maad of gristle &thorn;at is neischer &thorn;an boon &amp; hardere &thorn;an|fleisch.  To &thorn;is lyme &thorn;er come&thorn; manie sijknessis, &amp; summe &thorn;erof|falli&thorn; for cirurgie as apostimes &amp; vlcera, &amp; summe falli&thorn; to phisik|as greet sownynge in &thorn;e eeris &amp; sibillus, &amp; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="174a">defaute of heeringe &amp;| deefnes.<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>deesires</I>.</NOTE>  Akynge of &thorn;e eeris sumtyme is an yuel, &amp; sumtyme|harme fallynge &thorn;erto / &amp; &thorn;erfore it is mi purpos for to speke bo&thorn;e|of sirurge and of phisik in &thorn;is chapitre.  &para; Alle &thorn;e sijknessis of|&thorn;e eeris moun be take in &thorn;is maner, as akynge of eeris.  Ou&thorn;er it|is apostym &amp; without vlcera, or it is wi&thorn; enpostym &amp; vlcera; &thorn;an|it is of yuel complexioun &amp; hoot;<NOTE PLACE="foot">The translation is corrupt.  Lat.: aut est sine apostemate vel ulcere|aut cum apostemate et ulcere.  Si sine apostemate et ulcere: tunc aut est|propter malam complexionem calidam &mdash; &mdash; aut propter malam complexionem|frigidam.</NOTE> &thorn;at &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t knowe bi scharp|akynge &amp; reednes of &thorn;e place.  &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt cure it wi&thorn; castynge|into &thorn;e eere oile of rosis, boylid hoot as he mai suffre, wi&thorn; &thorn;e|.iiij. part of vinegre / &amp; if &thorn;e akynge go not awei in &thorn;is maner,|&thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt do &thorn;eron a litil of opium / And if it come of yuel|complexioun &thorn;at it be coold, as coold wynd or of coold eire entrid|&thorn;eron, &thorn;is &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t knowe bi greet cooldnes in &thorn;e place, &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou|schalt cure him wi&thorn; &thorn;ingis &thorn;at schal be cast into &thorn;e eere, watir of|maiorana, or oile of lilie, &thorn;at &thorn;ou schalt fynde &thorn;e composicioun in|&thorn;e antidotarie.  &amp; in &thorn;is maner hoot oile schal be putt in his eere &amp;
<PB N="255">|no coold &thorn;ing, &amp; &thorn;ou schalt stuwe &thorn;e pacient<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="174b"> / Sumtyme it come&thorn; |of sum &thorn;ing &thorn;at falli&thorn; in his eere as a worme or a corn or a stoon,|or watir; &thorn;is &thorn;ou schalt knowe bi &thorn;e tellinge of &thorn;e pacient; for if|&thorn;er be ony &thorn;ing wi&thorn;inne, me mai se it.  If it so be &thorn;at &thorn;er be|falle yn ony stoon, &thorn;an caste into his eere oile of rosis, or oile of|almaundis, &amp; if &thorn;er be falle yn ony corn, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt do noon|oile in his eere; for it wole make &thorn;e corn wexe greet.  Make a|litil instrument of tree or of sum o&thorn;er &thorn;ing &amp; wete it in terbentyn|&amp; putte it into his eere, &amp; touche &thorn;erwi&thorn; &thorn;e stoon, ou&thorn;ir &thorn;e greyn, &amp;|&thorn;an it wole cleue &thorn;erto, &amp; &thorn;an drawe it out / &para; Also smite his eere|wi&thorn; &thorn;e pawme of &thorn;in hand, &amp; bi hap it wole falle out &thorn;erwi&thorn; / Also|sette a ventuse wi&thorn; fier vpon &thorn;e hoole of his eere, for &thorn;is sumtyme|wole drawe out a corn ou&thorn;er a stoon.<NOTE PLACE="foot">The translator has omitted the case when water is in the ear.  Sl. 2463,|fol. 83 b.: "<I>And yef be water enterid into &thorn;e ere, doo Galyenys experyment.|&para; Take a rodde of wilowe othyr a twigge of &thorn;e vyne and putte &thorn;e tone ende|in &thorn;e patientis ere, &amp; lappe wex aboute &thorn;e tother ende and sette hit on fyre,|ffor by &thorn;e vertu of &thorn;e fyre &thorn;e water schal be clene dried vppe.</I>"</NOTE>  &para; If &thorn;er entri&thorn; ony worme|into a mannes eere, &thorn;an fille his eere ful of flact watir,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>flact watir</I>.  Lat. flaccidus.  O.Fr. flaccide.  N.E. flat water.  Compare|<I>flaccid</I>.  Skeat, <I>Et. Dict.</I>, and <I>flaisch</I>, p. 265, note 1, <I>flasch</I>, p. 266,|note 3.  O.Fr. flasque, Lat. flaccidus, another form of flaccidus.</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;an drie|it / And if &thorn;is suffisi&thorn; not, fille his eere ful of oile of almaundis|&thorn;at ben bittir; &amp; if &thorn;is suffisi&thorn; not, &thorn;an do in his eere iuys of|calamynte.</P>
