<PB N="257">|drijnge &thorn;ingis, he sei&thorn; fals; for drijnge &thorn;ingis constreine&thorn;, &amp; apostym|is constreynyng / And summen han now newe rulis: &thorn;at wi&thorn; contrarijs|contrarie &thorn;ingis schulen be curid / In &thorn;is maner &thorn;ou schalt|worche.  Make poudre of mirre, &amp; of aloe, &amp; olibani, &amp; sanguis|draco ana, &amp; take oon tent &amp; wete it in hony, &amp; folde &thorn;e tent in|&thorn;e poudre, &amp; putte &thorn;e tent in his eere anoon to &thorn;e botme / &amp; if &thorn;e|tent mai not come to &thorn;e botme &thorn;erof, &thorn;an dissolue &thorn;e forseid poudre|wi&thorn; watir &amp; hony, &amp; caste it yn / If it so be &thorn;at vlcus be swi&thorn;e|cold, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt cure him in &thorn;is maner / Take &thorn;e rust of iren,|&amp; grinde it smal, &amp; leie it in an er&thorn;en vessel with vinegre, &amp; boile|hem togidere, til &thorn;e rust bicome drie.  &amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ou muste do ofte tyme.|&amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou muste poudre it a&yogh;en, &amp; se&thorn;e it in vinegre a&yogh;en til it|bicome &thorn;icke as hony, &amp; &thorn;an do &thorn;is in his eere, for &thorn;is wole hele|vlcera, &amp; &thorn;is wole drie &thorn;e moistnes &thorn;erof, &amp; &thorn;is wole do awey &thorn;e|akynge / And take hony .&yogh;. .x., vinegre &yogh;. viij., &amp; boile hem li&yogh;tly|at &thorn;e fier til it be wel skymed,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>skymed</I>.  Compare <I>scume</I>, p. 242, note 6.</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;an do &thorn;erto <ABBR EXPAN="[dram]">&yogh;</ABBR> .ij. of vert de|grece, and <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="177a">medle hem wel togidere, &amp; wete herynne a tent, &amp; |putte it in his eere, &amp; &thorn;is is good for vlcera &thorn;at ben oold.</P>
<P>&para; If a man be deef, &thorn;an it come&thorn; of summe of &thorn;e forseid causis,|&amp; principali of longe akynge; also it come&thorn; of child bering, &amp;|&thorn;anne it is incurable / Also if it come&thorn; of humours &thorn;at stoppi&thorn;|nerues, &amp; &thorn;e cure herof is for to purge him wi&thorn; cochijs &amp; pigra, &amp;|caste in his eere oile of bittir almaundis &amp; o&thorn;ere medicyns &thorn;at ben|openynge.  &amp; oon &thorn;erof is &thorn;is / Take pulpe colloquintide .&yogh; .j.,|castor, aristologia rotunda, succi absinthij ana &yogh;. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, euforbij .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>. j,|costi grana .xv, &amp; make herof smale pelottis, &amp; dissolue oon herof|wi&thorn; oile of almaundis &thorn;at ben bittir, &amp; do it in his eere; saue &thorn;ou|schalt make him a fumigacioun tofore wi&thorn; a decoccioun of sanbuci,|absinthij, sticados / Also take whit oile .&yogh; .j., &amp; grynde hony &amp;|oile togidere / If &thorn;e passioun come&thorn; of defaute of spiritis, &thorn;anne|putte herof in his eere, &amp; &thorn;anne he schal be ba&thorn;id &amp; haue reste, &amp;|vse metis &thorn;at engendri&thorn; good blood, &amp; he schal heere sotil voicis for|to make him haue heerynge / &amp; summe seien &thorn;at &thorn;e fatnes of grene |<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="177b">froggis, &thorn;at lyuen among trees;<NOTE PLACE="foot">Some words like <I>is good</I> are wanting.</NOTE> take hem &amp; se&thorn;e hem, &amp; gadere|&thorn;e fatnes of hem &amp; caste in his eere, for &thorn;is ha&thorn; vertu for to make|men heere.  &para; Also take a litil garlek &amp; make it clene, &amp; do &thorn;erto|&thorn;e .iij. part of tartre, &amp; grinde hem smal togidere, &amp; boile hem in|vinegre, &amp; whanne it is coold &thorn;an coole it, &amp; of &thorn;is vinegre leie|hoot to his eere /
