<PB N="276">|ache ana <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>. j, se&thorn;e hem alle togidere til &thorn;e .iij. part be consumed|awei, &amp; &thorn;an cole hem &amp; do &thorn;erto l&imacr;. x of sugre, &amp; &thorn;an clarifie it &amp;| se&thorn;e it <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="192b">&amp; kepe it for &thorn;in vss // The vss of &thorn;is sirip wole suffise for|to do it awei; but if &thorn;e mater be &thorn;e more greet, &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t do|&thorn;erto if &thorn;ou wolt oximel squilliticum, or &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t ordeine &thorn;e sirip|wi&thorn; modicis<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>modiu's</I>.</NOTE> erbis diureticis.  &para; &THORN;er is no &thorn;ing so good for to|purge mater of &thorn;e reines as is castynge / for whi castinge curi&thorn;|vlcera of &thorn;e reynes / In &thorn;e somer &thorn;ou schalt make him oonys in &thorn;e|mone&thorn;e sich a maner of vomet / Take &thorn;e seed of raphani &amp; make|it clene &amp; kutte it ouer&thorn;wert in rollis, &amp; lete &thorn;is lie in &thorn;e forseid|sirup .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iiij. adai &amp; any&yogh;t / &amp; &thorn;an lete &thorn;e pacient ete diuers metis,|as chese, oynouns, salt fisch &amp; &thorn;ingis &thorn;at mai make him drinke|wel; &amp; lete him drinke diuers wynes, saue the while he is fastinge,|lete him ete 3 notis of &thorn;e forseid rollis of raphani &thorn;at lay in &thorn;e|forseid sirup, &amp; whanne he hath ete his saule &amp; drunke, &thorn;an binde|vpon his i&yogh;en neische lynet or flex, &amp; streyne &thorn;ou not it to harde|but meneli.  &amp; &thorn;an take watir in which has been soden anetum|til it bicome reed, &amp; take &thorn;erof l&imacr; .j., &amp; medle it wi&thorn; &thorn;e sirup &thorn;at| radix raphani lay &thorn;erinne, &amp; make him <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="193a">drinke vp al togidere, &amp;|&thorn;an he schal caste vp al his mete &amp; al his drink, &amp; manye wickede|humours &thorn;erwi&thorn;.  &amp; &thorn;an make him gadere out &thorn;e f