<PB N="277">|&amp; scharpe it wi&thorn; benedicta,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>benedicta</I>.  Lat. cum benedicta Nicolai.</NOTE> and make &thorn;erof a clisterie, &amp; &thorn;e|pacient schal holde it wi&thorn;inne him longe tyme, &amp; after &thorn;is clisterie|do him in to a particular ba&thorn;, &amp; lete him sitte &thorn;eron anoon to &thorn;e|nauele, &amp; in his ba&thorn; schulen be soden leeues of malue, peritorie,|viole, senacion, scutella panici pistati &amp; cortice mundati; &thorn;is maner|ba&thorn; as I haue ofte preued, it aswaged akinge / &amp; whanne he goi&thorn;|out of his ba&thorn;, make an enplastre of mele, oile &amp; watir, as &thorn;ou|schalt fynde in &thorn;e antidotarie in &thorn;e co. of maturatiuis, &amp; leie vpon|&thorn;e place &thorn;ere &thorn;e passioun is / If &thorn;ou knowist wel &thorn;at &thorn;e stoon|falli&thorn; adoun of &thorn;e reynes toward &thorn;e bladdre bi &thorn;e weie of &thorn;e vrine,|sette &thorn;an vndir &thorn;e place &thorn;ere it aki&thorn;,<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>maki&thorn;</I>.  Lat. sub loco doloris.</NOTE> sichiam<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sichiam</I>.  Lat. syciam G. <GAP DESC="Greek">, the common cucumber.  "A figur&aelig;|vel form&aelig; similitudine Cucurbit&aelig; vel cucurbitul&aelig; medicis dicuntur vascula|illa, qu&aelig; cuti cum flamma affigi solent, cum vel sine scarificatione."  Castelli,|Lex. medicum.</NOTE> wi&thorn; fier wi&thorn;out ony|kuttynge, for &thorn;is wole drawe adoun &thorn;e stoon.  &amp; as &thorn;e stoon|discendi&thorn; adoun to sichiam to sette it lower til he come anoon to &thorn;e|bladdre, &amp; &thorn;an al &thorn;e akynge wole go awei.  &para; Tofore alle &thorn;ingis|fildonium<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>fildonium</I>.  Lat. philonium romanum.  Matth. Sylv.: "Filonium i.|nouus amicus &amp; est confectio quedam sic uocata."  Galen, ed. Kuehn, vol.|xvii. B. 331, <GAP DESC="Greek">. An electuary with Opium, so called from|Philo of Tharsus.</NOTE> is good, &thorn;at &thorn;ou schalt fynde in &thorn;e antidotarie of auicen,|for &thorn;at is a sure medicyn in &thorn;is caas.  &para; Ano&thorn;er medicyn &thorn;at|auicen made, &amp; I haue preued it, and it <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="194a">doi&thorn; awei akynge &thorn;at is|in vlceribus renum.  &rx;, seminis iusquiami albi .&yogh;. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, opij, grana |.iiij, seminum citruli, lactuce, portulace, ana .&yogh;. j., medle al togidere|&amp; &yogh;eue herof .&yogh;. ij. wi&thorn; sugre.  &para; And &thorn;is &thorn;ou muste wite &thorn;at &thorn;ou|schalt &yogh;eue &thorn;e pacient no &thorn;ing for to make him pisse whan his|akinge is strong, &amp; whanne his vrine is stoppid; for &thorn;at wole make|&thorn;e more akinge / It is perel of &thorn;is passioun, for &thorn;e akynge is so|greet sumtyme &thorn;at &thorn;e pacient ha&thorn; &thorn;e spasme &thorn;erwi&thorn; &amp; is deed &thorn;erwi&thorn;,|saue &thorn;ou schalt do awei his akynge wi&thorn; ba&thorn;inge &amp; enplastris|&amp; anoyntyngis, &amp; &thorn;ane aftirward &thorn;ou schalt make him medicyns|for to breke &thorn;e stoon &amp; putte him out wi&thorn; &thorn;e vryne / &rx;, cretani|marini,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Crithmum maritimum, L.</NOTE> scolopendrie, capillis veneris, spice celtice, ana .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>. ij., radix|fenicli, apij, petrosilij, spergi, brusci, cicore, graminis, filipendule,|genciane, saxifrage, squille, asse, ana .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j., iiijor semina frigidorum,|seminum fenicli, apij, coriandri, scariole,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Sin. Barth.: "Scariola, lactucella, lactuca agrestis idem, an. sowe-thistel."</NOTE> granorum iuniperi, nucleum
