io" N="195a">&amp; o&thorn;ere strong medicyns &thorn;at pili&thorn; &thorn;e reynes.  &amp; if &thorn;e pacient|haue drie reynes &amp; he be leene of bodi, &thorn;an in &thorn;is caas .&yogh;. j. of|Rasis makynge is good / &rx;, semina melonum mundatorum .&yogh;. xxx,|seminis citruli, seminis portulace, seminis cucurbite, seminis papaueris|albi ana .&yogh;. iij, seminis iusquiami albe .&yogh;. ij., &yogh;ucari pondus|omnium,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat. ad pondus omnium.</NOTE> saue I do &thorn;erto &thorn;e double wei&yogh;te of sugre /</P>
<P>If &thorn;e stoon be in his bladdre, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt worche in &thorn;is|maner / First &thorn;ou schalt take kepe wher he haue stranguria.  &THORN;at|&thorn;ou mi&yogh;t wite if he maki&thorn; watir droppynli &amp; a litil at oonys, &amp;|ha&thorn; greet penaunce in his bladdre.  &THORN;an &thorn;e stoon is in &thorn;e necke of|&thorn;e bladdre; &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt make him a clisterie mollificatif &thorn;at &thorn;ou|mowe avoide his bowels, &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt frote his nose&thorn;rillis with|watir,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: faciendo egrum leuare nates.  The translator read: lauare nares.</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;ou schalt presse li&yogh;tly &thorn;e place of his ars &thorn;ereaboute &thorn;at|&thorn;ou supposist &thorn;at &thorn;e stoon sitti&thorn;.  &amp; if he remeue not in &thorn;is maner,|&thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt putte in siryngam li&yogh;tli in &thorn;e condijt of his &yogh;erde til|he come to &thorn;e stoon.  &amp; if &thorn;ou my&yogh;t not putte it awei in &thorn;is maner,
<PB N="279">|&thorn;an putte &thorn;i fyngir in <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="195b">his ers, &amp; &thorn;ere &thorn;ou schalt fele &thorn;e stoon, &amp; |helpe wi&thorn; &thorn;i fyngir for to putte it awey.  Whanne &thorn;e stoon is|remeued, &thorn;an &thorn;e pacient mai make watir, &thorn;an his akinge wole ceesse,|&amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt go to &thorn;e cure.  First &thorn;ou schalt make him a|clisterie of duritikis / in which schulen be medicyns &thorn;at haue propriete|for to breke &thorn;e stoon, &amp; &thorn;an sette &thorn;e pacient in a ba&thorn; &thorn;at is|forseid.  &amp; a litil tofore or he go out of his ba&thorn;, &yogh;eue him of &thorn;e|poudre of &thorn;e hare &thorn;at is forseid.  &amp; whanne he come&thorn; out of &thorn;e|ba&thorn;, leie &thorn;is enplastre vpon &thorn;e place &thorn;at is clepid pectinis.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: supra locum pectinis.  Os pectinis, the share-bone.</NOTE> &rx;, foliorum|nasturcij aquatici,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Nasturtium aquaticum, watercress.</NOTE> &amp; foliorum apij .ana. <ABBR EXPAN="[handful]"><GAP></ABBR> j, &amp; grinde hem|wel wi&thorn; grese.  &amp; whanne &thorn;ei ben medlid togidere in &thorn;e morter, &thorn;an|hete hem a litil ouer &thorn;e fier &amp; leie it vpon, &amp; eueri dai in &thorn;re daies|contynuely &thorn;ou schalt sette him in &thorn;e forseid ba&thorn;, &amp; leie vpon &thorn;e|forseid plastre, &amp; &yogh;eue him of &thorn;e forseid poudre.  &THORN;is cure is good|&amp; I haue preued it //</P>
<P>If alle &thorn;ese medicyns availi&thorn; not, &thorn;an &thorn;ou muste drawe out &thorn;e|stoon wi&thorn; kuttynge or &thorn;e patient falle into etikis.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>etikis</I>, Lat.: antequam &aelig;ger incurrat hecticam.  O.Fr. &eacute;tique.  Med.|Lat. Ethica uel Ethica febris.  Dufr.</NOTE>  &amp; if &thorn;ou wolt|drawe <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="196a">out a stoon of &thorn;e bladdre wi&thorn; kuttynge, &thorn;an &thorn;ou muste apparaile<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>apparaile</I>.  See <I>N. E. Dict</I>., s. v. apparel, v. 1., to make ready, prepare.</NOTE> |alle &thorn;ingis &thorn;at ben necessarie for &thorn;ee: as sirupis &amp; ligaturis,|&amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt binde his hipis &amp; his leggis faste, &thorn;at he mowe|not meue, for to lette &thorn;ee whanne &thorn;ou wolt kutte him.  &amp; &thorn;anne|&thorn;ou schalt anoynte &thorn;i longist fyngir of &thorn;i lift hond &amp; &thorn;i &thorn;ombe wi&thorn;|oile, &amp; &thorn;ou schalt putte hem in &thorn;e pacientis ers, saue first &thorn;ou schalt|avoide him wi&thorn; a clisterie mollificatif, &amp; &thorn;ou schalt sette<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sette</I>, above line.</NOTE> &thorn;i ri&yogh;t|hond vpon his ers, and grope softli, where &thorn;e stoon be, &amp; putte him|to &thorn;e hedis of &thorn;i fyngris.  &amp; whanne &thorn;ou my&yogh;t take &thorn;e stoon wi&thorn; &thorn;i|.ij. fyngris, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt putte him to &thorn;e necke of &thorn;e bladdre|toward &thorn;e ballokis as myche as &thorn;ou my&yogh;t.  &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt fele &thorn;e|hardnes of &thorn;e stoon bitwixe his ers, &amp; &thorn;e ballokis &thorn;at is in &thorn;e necke|of &thorn;e bladdre.  &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt wi&thorn; &thorn;i ri&yogh;t hond take a rasour, &amp;|kutte faste by &thorn;e &thorn;reed &thorn;at goi&thorn; bitwixe &thorn;e ers &amp; &thorn;e ballokis endelongis,|saue &thorn;ou schalt take &thorn;e stoon wi&thorn; &thorn;i .ij. fyngris &thorn;at &thorn;e stoon |mowe come out.  &amp; &thorn;anne ioyne wel &thorn;e lippis of <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="196b">&thorn;e wounde togidere,|&thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt sewe [not]<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>not</I>, wanting.  Lat.: et labia vulneris optime conjungas <I>non</I> solum in|superficie.</NOTE> oonly &thorn;e skyn aboue, but &thorn;ou
<PB N="280">|schalt sewe al &thorn;e depnes of &thorn;e wounde togidere, &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt|springe &thorn;eron poudre &thorn;at is aforseid to woundis.  &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt|binde it with boondis &amp; lynt til &thorn;e wounde be perfitli hool / In &thorn;is|caas &thorn;ou muste take kepe of manye &thorn;ingis / First &thorn;ou muste take|kepe of &thorn;e age of &thorn;e pacient, for children &thorn;at ben xiiij. wintir oold|ben moost able for &thorn;is cure,<NOTE PLACE="foot">De propr. rer. Add. 27,944, fol. 96: "<I>&amp; somtyme &thorn;ey schal be take to|surgerye and namelich children and &thorn;an &yogh;ongelinge.  For in elde keruynge|is perilous, for aftir fourty &yogh;ere &thorn;is euel is incurable as it is i-said in|amphor.:</I><NOTE PLACE="foot">Rhazes, Aphorismi.</NOTE> <I>aftir fourti &yogh;ere he &thorn;at ha&thorn; &thorn;e ston is nou&yogh;t i-saued.</I>"</NOTE> for her lymes ben tendir ynow&yogh;, &amp; in|&thorn;at elde &thorn;ei ben strong ynow&yogh; for to be maad hool, &amp; her complexioun|is hoot &amp; moist.  &YOGH;onge children &amp; olde men ben not able|to be kutt, for in &thorn;e kuttynge of hem enpostyms wolen engendre|hastili, &amp; &thorn;at wole lette &thorn;e vrine &amp; make more akynge, &amp; so &thorn;ei|mi&yogh;ten falle in-to &thorn;e spasme, &amp; so wi&thorn; &thorn;e spasme &thorn;ei mi&yogh;t be deed /|Summen seien &thorn;at olde men ben able to be kutt, for her blood is|miche laskid<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Celsus</I> Lib. VII. Cap. 26, ed. Daremberg, p. 307: "As neque omni tempore,|neque in omni &aelig;tate, neque in omni vitio id experiendum est: sed solo|vere; in eo corpore, quod jam novem annos, nondum quatuordecim excessit."</NOTE> &amp; her hete, &amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei ben not able to take an|enpostym; &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei ben moost able to be kutt of &thorn;e stoon /|Summen seien &thorn;at her lymes ben to drie &amp; her vertues ben to feble /| <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="197a">&amp; &thorn;erfore &thorn;ei ben not able to be kutt, &amp; herwi&thorn; I acorde / &THORN;ese .ij.|&thorn;ingis: engendrynge of an enpostym, &amp; if &thorn;e place &thorn;at is kutt|wole not soude, &thorn;ese .ij. bringi&thorn; perel of dee&thorn; / Also &thorn;ou muste|take kepe of &thorn;e schap of &thorn;e stoon, &amp; what quantite &thorn;at he be, for|if &thorn;e stoon be .ij. forkid<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ij forkid</I>, diffurcatus.</NOTE> or cornerid, or so greet &thorn;at he may not|be brou&yogh;t into &thorn;e necke of &thorn;e bladdre, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt in no maner|kutte him, but if &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t first wi&thorn; &thorn;in hond breke &thorn;e stoon. &amp;|&thorn;an if &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t not bringe it out at oonys, &thorn;an in diuers tymes|&thorn;ou schalt gadere him out.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: "pluribus vicibus educatur."</NOTE>  &para; And if &thorn;e stoon be so greet &thorn;at he|mai not be brou&yogh;t into &thorn;e necke of &thorn;e bladdre, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt in no|maner kutte him, forwhi he mai not be brou&yogh;t out, but if &thorn;ou|woldist kutte &thorn;e substaunce of &thorn;e bladdre &amp; &thorn;at were mortal; but|&thorn;ou schalt put him to &thorn;e botme of &thorn;e bladdre wi&thorn; instrumentis, &amp;|teche &thorn;e patient for to kepe him in &thorn;at maner &thorn;at &thorn;e stoon falle not|into &thorn;e necke of &thorn;e bladdre / Also if he be so sutil &thorn;at he mai not|be felid wi&thorn; &thorn;in hond, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt not kutte him nei&thorn;er.  &amp; if &thorn;e| patient mai be hool in ony <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="197b">maner, [n]or kutt wi&thorn;outen passioun, it
<PB N="281">|is better &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>&thorn;an.</I></NOTE> he be nou&yogh;t kutt &thorn;an he be kutt.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&amp; if &thorn;e patient ... &thorn;an he be kutt,</I> an insertion.</NOTE> for men &thorn;at ben so|kutt schulen neuere gete children, but if it be &thorn;e more hap<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: "Considera quoque quod s&aelig;pe per loci nominati incisionem generatio|prohibetur."</NOTE>; &amp;|also it is perilous for to kutte / &amp; &thorn;erfore I rede &thorn;ee take &thorn;at wynnynge<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;at wynnynge</I>, Lat.: sed aliis cupidis chirurgis dimitte illa lucrari.|<I>Cath. Angl</I>., p. 420, "<I>Wynninge</I>, Emolimentum, lucrum."</NOTE>|to o&thorn;ere cirurgians.  &para; Ful ofte tyme men leie me to scorn,|for I wolde not entermete me of sich curis, &amp; seide &thorn;at I lefte siche|maner curis, for I coude not do it, &amp; &thorn;e same &thorn;ei seide of men &thorn;at|weren filme broke,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>of men &thorn;at weren filme broke</I>, Lat. de ruptorum incisura.</NOTE> &amp; of men &thorn;at weren in &thorn;e dropesie.  &amp; I lefte|&thorn;e curis &thorn;erof for perels &thorn;at mi&yogh;te folowe / ffor if a kunnynge man|entermetid him of sich a cure, &amp; if &thorn;er fil ony yuele happis to &thorn;e|patient, &thorn;an wolen vnkunnynge lechis seie &thorn;at &thorn;ei han do &thorn;at cure|ful ofte, &amp; so he mai be brou&yogh;t into an yuel looss &thorn;erbi; for blame|&amp; for perels I wolde not vse kuttyngis / &THORN;ese ben yuele happis &thorn;at|falli&thorn; to a man &thorn;at is kutt: as greet akynge vndir &thorn;e nauele, &amp; hise|lymes bicomith coold, &amp; atach of &thorn;e feuere,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>atach of &thorn;e feuere</I>, attack of fever.  See later references in <I>N. E. Dict</I>.,|s. v. attach, sb.</NOTE> &amp; greet akinge in &thorn;e|place &thorn;at was kutt, alle &thorn;ese signes ben signes of dee&thorn; / Good signes|herof ben &thorn;ese: strenk&thorn;e of vrine, &amp; &thorn;at he mowe go to priuy wel|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="198a">&amp; &thorn;at he haue good appetit to mete.  &para; Sumtyme it falli&thorn; bi |strenk&thorn;e, &thorn;e stoon is putt into &thorn;e &yogh;erde.  &amp; &thorn;at I say [in] a man,|&thorn;at his vryne was stoppid .v. daies in &thorn;e same maner, &amp; I drowe|him out wi&thorn; instrumentis wi&thorn;outen ony kuttynge.  &amp; if &thorn;e stoon|sitte in &thorn;e canel of &thorn;e &yogh;erde, &amp; &thorn;ou maist not bringe him out wi&thorn;|&thorn;i fyngris, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt binde his &yogh;erde bihinde &thorn;e stoon, &thorn;at &thorn;e|stoon mowe not go into &thorn;e bladdre a&yogh;en.  &amp; &thorn;an grope &thorn;e stoon softli|wi&thorn; &thorn;i .ij. fyngris, &amp; kutte endelongis, as it is aforseid, a litil hole,|as miche as &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t drawe out &thorn;e stoon, &amp; &thorn;ane cure &thorn;e wounde|as it is aforseid /<NOTE PLACE="foot">The translator has omitted one chapter:  De clauso hermaphrodito &amp;|additione panniculi mulieris doctrin&aelig; terti&aelig;, tractatus tertii, Cap. IX.</NOTE></P>
