<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="10">
<HEAD>ffor to drawe out watir of men &thorn;at han &thorn;e dropesie /<NOTE PLACE="foot">The four kinds of dropsy are mentioned in De propr. rerum, Lib. VII.,|Cap. 52, Add. 27,944, fol. 94 b.: "<I>&THORN;e firste dropesye hatte leucofleuma, and|come&thorn; of distemperaunce of coldenesse and drinesse, &amp; ha&thorn; &thorn;at name of|white fleume for leucos is white.  &para; &THORN;e secounde hatte yposarca o&thorn;ir anasarca,|and come&thorn; of distemperaunce of coolde and of drynes.  The &thorn;ridde hatte|aschites and come&thorn; of distemperaunce of hete &amp; moisture.  &THORN;e fer&thorn;e hatte|tympanytes &amp; come&thorn; of distemperaunce of hete &amp; drinesse.</I>"</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Thou&yogh; &thorn;is book be maad oonli of cirurgie, &yogh;itt it is myn entencioun|to speke of &thorn;e dropesie, &amp; principaly &thorn;at ben wrou&yogh;t
<PB N="282">|wi&thorn; mannes hond.  &para; I seie &thorn;at &thorn;e dropesie is a sijknes compound|in which superflue mater &thorn;at is coold swelli&thorn; &thorn;e body / Men of|salerne seiden &thorn;at &thorn;ere weren .iiij. maner spicis of dropesie, &amp; iiij.| maner dropesies.  But auctours of arabie acorden alle at <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="198b">oonys,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>acorden alle at oonys</I>, Lat. in una conveniunt.  Comp. <I>Reliqu. Antiqu</I>.|I. 233, <I>accorde in one</I>.  (<I>N. E. Dict.</I>, s. v. accord v. 5.)</NOTE>|&amp; seien soo&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;er ben but .iij. maner dropesies,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lanfranc follows <I>Avicenna</I>, Lib. III, Fen. 14, Tract. 4, Cap. 4, ed. Ven.|1527, fol. 238 b.</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;at oon|come&thorn; of rawe blood, of raw fleume medlid wi&thorn; blood, &amp; is bore into|al &thorn;e bodi, &amp; swelli&thorn; al &thorn;e bodi, &amp; is clepid yposarca.  &THORN;at o&thorn;er is|of mater of &yogh;elow&yogh; water &amp; falli&thorn; into &thorn;e holownes of &thorn;e wombe,|&amp; is clepid aschites / &THORN;e .iij. is engendrid of greet wynd resolued|of coold mater, &amp; falli&thorn; into &thorn;e holownes of &thorn;e wombe, &amp; is clepid|tympanites / Of &thorn;is ydropesie summen iugi&thorn; li&yogh;tli, &amp; seien &thorn;at|yposarca come&thorn; of coold alwei, &amp; tympanites come&thorn; sumtyme of|wynd &amp; of hete, but moost comounli of cooldnes / Aschites comith|moost of hete, &amp; ful selden of cooldnes / but for to seie &thorn;e so&thorn;e,|alle &thorn;e spicis ben medlid with coold mater, &amp; &thorn;erfore he sei&thorn; soo&thorn;|&thorn;at clepi&thorn; eueri ydropesie coold mater,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: omnem egritudinem ydropicam appellant materialem frigidam.</NOTE> for euery spice of &thorn;e dropesie|mai come of hete or of cooldnes goynge tofore.  &para; &THORN;er is no &thorn;ing|&thorn;at defendi&thorn;, &thorn;at whanne &thorn;e lyuere is hoot out of hir propir hete, or|if al &thorn;e bodi is distemp[er]id in hete, as in feueris, &thorn;e patient mai so|miche be feblid &thorn;erwi&thorn;, &thorn;at it may engendre coold mater &amp; fleumatik|/ Ful ofte I haue had &thorn;is caas / <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="199a">&THORN;erfore auctouris seien &thorn;at| &thorn;e dropesie comith of &thorn;e febilnes of &thorn;e lyuere / &thorn;erfore men of|salerne seien &thorn;at it come&thorn; of defaute of digestioun of &thorn;e lyuere.|&amp; it come&thorn; of takinge of yuele metis &amp; drinkis, &amp; of febilnes of|o&thorn;ere lymes, as of &thorn;e stomak, &amp; of &thorn;e reynes, &amp; of &thorn;e maris, &amp; of|&thorn;e lungis, &amp; of diafragma.  &amp; whanne &thorn;ese lymes ben enfeblid, &thorn;an|&thorn;e lyuere enfebli&thorn; // Therfore it is necessarie for a leche to wite<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>to wite</I>, above line.</NOTE>|wher it come&thorn; of causis goinge tofore hoot or coold / And summe|lechis halden hem paid for to haue a si&yogh;t of &thorn;e vrine, &amp; iugi&thorn; &thorn;e|dropesie hoot &amp; coold bi &thorn;e si&yogh;t of &thorn;e vryne / for if &thorn;e vrine be|reed, &thorn;ei wolen iuge &thorn;at &thorn;e cause is hoot, &amp; in &thorn;is maner &thorn;ei ben
<PB N="283">|disseyued / &para; Forwhi, in what maner so &thorn;e lyuere be enfeblid of|coold cause or of hoot, it wole make his vrine reed / For sumtyme|a man mai not &yogh;eue a discrecioun<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&yogh;eue a discrecioun</I>, discernere.</NOTE> of blood fro vrine, for a litil|blood colourid miche vrine, ri&yogh;t as a litil saffron colouri&thorn; miche|water / &THORN;erfor of what cause so it be &thorn;at his lyuere be enfeblid,|his vrine mai schewe reed.  &para; Also &thorn;e signes of yposarcha &amp; aschites|&amp; tympanite ben open ynow&yogh;.  <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="199b">In &thorn;is maner &thorn;ou schalt knowe hem / |In yposarcha al &thorn;e bodi swelli&thorn;, as his face, &amp; his armis, &amp; his riggeboon,|&amp; his necke, &amp; alle his lymes, so &thorn;at in what partie of his|bodi &thorn;at &thorn;ou pressist &thorn;i fyngir &thorn;ere wole be a pitt.  &amp; whanne &thorn;e|fyngir is aweie it wole arise a&yogh;en / &amp; it is a greet maistrie for to|knowe whe&thorn;er yposarcha come of coold cause tofore goynge or of|hoot cause / If it come&thorn; of coold goinge tofore, &thorn;an his i&yogh;en wolen|be discolourid as it were &thorn;e colour of askis, or pale<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: coniunctiva oculi est valde discolorata, cinericia vel pallida.</NOTE> / If it come of|hete goinge tofore, &thorn;an his i&yogh;en wolen be &yogh;elow&yogh; or sumwhat reed /|&amp; &thorn;ou muste wite, whe&thorn;er he had a feuere tofore or haue &thorn;e feuere|fortis &thorn;erwi&thorn; / or if he hadde &thorn;ere tofore an hoot enpostym &thorn;erwi&thorn;,|ou&thorn;er he haue enpostym &thorn;erwi&thorn; / &THORN;ese ben &thorn;e propre signes of|aschites, &thorn;at his face, &amp; his necke, &amp; his brest, &amp; his armis|bicomith smal, &amp; his vois schal bicome smal, &amp; his wombe schal|oonli swelle.  &amp; sumtyme in &thorn;e firste bigynnyng his feet &amp; his|leggis wolen swelle in &thorn;e firste bigynnynge, for &thorn;e greet strenk&thorn;e of|&thorn;e mater &thorn;at maki&thorn; it falle adoun.  &amp; if &thorn;ou <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="200a">smite his<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>his</I>, twice.</NOTE> wombe, he |wole sowne as it were a tou&yogh;t le&thorn;er ful of wynd<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: auditur quasi sonus vtris de corio vino pleni.</NOTE> / &THORN;ese ben &thorn;e|propre signes of tympanites: his wombe &amp; &thorn;e regioun of his stomac|schulen oonly be to-swolle, &amp; alle his o&thorn;ere lymes, bo&thorn;e his feet, &amp;|his leggis, &amp; his necke, &amp; his armis wolen bicome smal, &amp; if &thorn;ou|smitist him vpon his wombe, it wole soune as it were a tympan /|&amp; in &thorn;is passioun &thorn;er is lasse agreuaunce &thorn;an in aschite &amp; more|swellynge.  &amp; if &thorn;ou pressist his wombe, &thorn;ou schalt fynde it streite|as it were a corde.  &amp; &thorn;ou schal fele no meuyng of water, whanne|&thorn;e pacient turne&thorn; him from o side to ano&thorn;er / Curis herof &thorn;ou schalt|fynde ynowe in bokis of phisik / For I nyle telle but fewe medicyns|&thorn;erfore, I haue longe tyme vsid.</P>
<P>&para; Whanne &thorn;ou wolt ordeine regimen on yposarcha, &yogh;eue him
<PB N="284">|trociscus de lactea<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>lactea</I>, Lat. lacta.  "Lacca, a red transparent Substance made as some|say, by winged Arts; as Hony by Bees, and gather'd from a Tree of that|Name, in Bengala, Malabar &amp;.c.  Also a kind of red Gum issuing from|certain Trees in Arabia, of which the best Sealing hard Wax is made; often|us'd in Painting and Varnishing."  Phillips.</NOTE> cum apo&yogh;imate<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Apozima</I>.  "Apozeme, a Physical Decoction, a Diet-Drink made of|several Roots, Woods, Barks, Herbs, Drugs, Flowers, Seeds, &amp;.c., boil'd together."|Phillips.</NOTE> de radicibus fro &thorn;e firste dai to|&thorn;e .iiij., &amp; &yogh;eue him pelottis de agarico.  &amp; whanne &thorn;e swellinge|bigynne&thorn; to go awey, if it be in somer, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt hele al his|bodi in hoot grauel &thorn;ere &thorn;e sunne mai &yogh;eue greet hete, or lete him| sitte vpon an hi&yogh; hil &thorn;ere &thorn;e <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="200b">sunne schine&thorn; hoot, &thorn;at he mai swete|wel, &amp; &thorn;at his bodi mai wexe hoot wi&thorn;oute &amp; wi&thorn;inne.  &amp; if it be|in winter, putte him in a drie stewe, so &thorn;at &thorn;e watir come not ni&yogh;|him.  &THORN;us &thorn;ou schalt make apo&yogh;ima of rotis / &rx;, corticis fenicli,|apij, [ana drac.]<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>&amp;.</I></NOTE> .x., seminum [apii] squinantum, ameos, ana. <ABBR EXPAN="[dram]">&yogh;</ABBR> .v.,|rosarum rubiarum, spicenarde ana .&yogh; .iij, se&thorn;e hem in l&imacr; .ij. of|watir til &thorn;ei come to l&imacr; .j., cole hem &amp; kepe &thorn;e colature.  &amp; if &thorn;ou|doist &thorn;erinne a litil hony it wole be &thorn;e better / Trocisci de lacte ben|maad in &thorn;is maner / &rx;, rubarbe, lacte, ana [drac iii.], seminis apij,|spice, ameos, amigdalum amarum, masticis, squinante, seminis iunip[er]i,|costi amari,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Two kinds of <I>costus</I> are mentioned in <I>Alphita</I>, p. 46: c. indicus, and|c. arabicus.</NOTE> rubee succi, eupatorij,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>eupatorium</I>.  Add. 15,236, fol. 3 b. (cc. 1300), "<I>Eupatorium. saluia|agrestis idem. G. eupatorie. A. wyldesage. i. hyndehale.</I>"</NOTE> aristologi&aelig; rotund&aelig;,|gencian ana .&yogh;. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, make herof gobetis, &thorn;e wei&yogh;te of <ABBR EXPAN="[dram]">&yogh;</ABBR> .j., &amp; he schal|take oon &thorn;erof wi&thorn; .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iiij. of &thorn;e forseid pelottis de agarico / &rx;,|agarici .&yogh; .x., succi eupatorij, rubarbarum, aristologia rotund&aelig; ana|&yogh; .ij, &yogh;ucare albe .&yogh; .v, &amp; make herof pelottis.  &amp; &thorn;ou schalt &yogh;eue|herof .&yogh; .ij.</P>
<P>If &thorn;ou seest &thorn;at &thorn;e cause &thorn;at &yogh;ede tofore &thorn;is passioun was hoot,|&amp; he make litil vrine &amp; reed, &amp; if his vertu be feble of &thorn;e hete, &amp;| &thorn;ou hast dispeir of him,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;ou hast dispeir of him</I>, Lat. de tali &aelig;gri salute desperes.  Comp. <I>&thorn;ou|schalt neuere &thorn;e lattere be in despeir of cauteriis.</I>  Lat. nec propter hoc|desperes, p. 311, note 3.</NOTE> &amp; if he haue &thorn;e feuere &thorn;erwi&thorn;, it is so|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="201a">myche &thorn;e worse // If his vrine schewe &thorn;at &thorn;e cause is coold, &amp; if|&thorn;e patient be strong ynow&yogh;, loke if his wombe be hard.  &amp; &thorn;an|make him vse sirup acetose maad wi&thorn; seedis &amp; sugre, &amp; &yogh;eue him &thorn;e|pelottis of rubarbe &thorn;at ben maad in &thorn;is maner / &rx;, rubarberi, succi|eupatorij, seminis endiuie ana. &yogh;. iij, agarici &yogh;. v., make &thorn;erof
<PB N="285">|pelettis wi&thorn; &thorn;e iuys of endiue.  &THORN;ou schalt &yogh;eue him herof at|oonys. .&yogh; .ij, &amp; euery wike &thorn;ou schalt &yogh;eue it oonys / If it so be &thorn;at|he be feble, &amp; if he mai not take so miche, &thorn;an in &thorn;e place of &thorn;ese|pelottis he schal take gobetis &thorn;at ben maad in &thorn;is maner / &rx;, seminis|endiuie <ABBR EXPAN="[dram]">&yogh;</ABBR> .x, esule,<NOTE PLACE="foot">"<I>Esula</I>, quedam species est titimalli, gallice yesele."  <I>Alphita</I>, p. 50.</NOTE> succi eupatorij, agarici, ana. <ABBR EXPAN="[dram]">&yogh;</ABBR> .ij, &amp; .<ABBR EXPAN="[scruple]"><GAP></ABBR> .j,|rosarum, seminis citrulorum, ana <ABBR EXPAN="[dram]">&yogh;</ABBR> .ij, &amp; make herof .x. gobettis|wi&thorn; a decoccion of fenel in water: &yogh;eue him oon &thorn;erof wi&thorn; sirupo|acetoso de seminibus.  Enplastre<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>enplastre</I>, Lat. venter enplastretur.  O.Fr. emplastrer.  Sl. 277, fol. 1:|"<I>be &thorn;e place emplastred wi&thorn; a plastre maad &thorn;us.</I>"  Comp. <I>plasteren</I>, Prompt.|Parv.</NOTE> his wombe wi&thorn; enplastre maad|wi&thorn; .ij. partis of oxis dounge, &amp; oon part of gotis dounge, boli|armoniaci, sulphuris, &amp; salis, &amp; distempere hem wi&thorn; strong vinegre /</P>
<P>&THORN;is is &thorn;e cure of tympaniti &thorn;at is ful selde curid / &amp; specialy|whanne it is entrid into diafragma &amp; is confermed &thorn;ere / ffirst &thorn;ou|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="201b">schalt make him electuari de baccis lauri, &amp; &thorn;ou schalt make him |suppositorijs for to distrie<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>distrie</I>, Lat. dissoluere, destroy.</NOTE> wynd, &amp; he schal suffre hungir as|miche as he mai, &amp; he schal absteyne him fro &thorn;ingis &thorn;at engendri&thorn;|wijnd, &amp; &thorn;ou schalt frote his wombe ofte wi&thorn; a scharp cloo&thorn; /|Electuari de baccis lauri / &rx;, foliorum rute .&yogh; .x., ameos, seminum,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: cimini.</NOTE>|nigille,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>nigilla</I>.  Add. 15,236, fol. 10, "<I>Nigella i. lollium. G. neel. A. cokel,</I>"|fennel flower.</NOTE> leuistici,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ibid</I>., fol. 4 b., "<I>Leuisticum. G. luuache,</I>" lovage.  See <I>E. P. N.</I>, p. 43,|<I>luvestiche, luvesche.</I></NOTE> petrocilij macedonici,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Alphita</I>, p. 108, "<I>macedonia vel macedonicum, petrocillinum idem,|g</I><SUP>e</SUP><I>. alisandre, a</I><SUP>e</SUP><I>. stamerche.</I>"</NOTE> origani,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Add. 15,236, fol. 5 b., "<I>Origanum. G. Origane. i. pulegium. A. puliol|reale.</I>"  See <I>Alphita</I>, p. 150. "<I>Pulegium. gallire puliol, a</I><SUP>e</SUP><I>. Brotheruurt.</I>"</NOTE> carui, amigdalarum|amarum, piperis longi, mentastri,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ibid</I>., fol. 7 b., "<I>Sisimbrium. mentastrum.  G. mentastre. A. hors.|minte.</I>"</NOTE> dauci, acori, baccarum lauri,|castore ana .&yogh; .iij., serapini .&yogh; .iiij., appoponac .&yogh; .iij., make herof a|lectuarie wi&thorn; .iij. so miche of hony, &thorn;is electuarie wi&thorn; consume&thorn;.|&para; &THORN;us &thorn;ou schalt make suppositorijs for to distrie wijnd / &rx;, ciminum,|foliorum rute viridis<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Ibid</I>., fol. 7, "<I>Ruta bissara. puganum vel pucanum. hermola idem. G.|Rue. A. smalrede.</I>"</NOTE> ana. <ABBR EXPAN="[handful]"><GAP></ABBR> .j., radicis brionie, radicis mali|terre, radicis rafani ana .&yogh; .ij., sal nitri .&yogh; .j., &amp; make herof suppositorijs|wi&thorn; hony.  &para; Whanne &thorn;ou knowist wel &thorn;at &thorn;e dropesie is of|hoot cause, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt not forgete to helpe &thorn;e side &thorn;at is hoot;|&amp; also if &thorn;e mater be coold, &thorn;ou schalt helpe him wi&thorn; hote &thorn;ingis.
<PB N="286">|&para; &THORN;is &thorn;ing is necessarie for to &yogh;eue a man &thorn;at ha&thorn; &thorn;e hote dropesie,| a decoccion of solatrum &amp; endiue; &amp; in &thorn;at watir he <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="202a">schal se&thorn;e|chikenys for to ete, &amp; first he schal drinke sirupum acetosum wi&thorn;|seedis / And I wole telle &thorn;ee a cure, &thorn;at I curide in my tyme .ij.|men &thorn;at weren in aschite of hoot cause, &thorn;at it mowe be ensaumple|to &thorn;ee / I made hem a sirupe of platearie<NOTE PLACE="foot">Matth&aelig;us <I>Platearius</I> belonged to the school of Salerno about the|middle of the 12th century.  He wrote: "Liber de simplici medicina,"|commonly called "Circa instans."</NOTE> in &thorn;is maner / &rx;, succi|scariole <ABBR EXPAN="[pound]">li</ABBR> .ij., succi apij &amp; petrosilij, ana. <ABBR EXPAN="[pound]">li</ABBR> .j., &amp; boile hem wi&thorn;|.<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iiij. of esule, masticis, seminis fenicli, apij, ana. <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, se&thorn;e hem in|watir til &thorn;ei come to .li .ij., &amp; &thorn;an cole hem &amp; do &thorn;erto .li .j. &yogh;ucare,|&amp; boile hem til &thorn;ei be perfit.  &amp; whanne &thorn;ow doist adoun fro &thorn;e|fier, do &thorn;erto rubarbe .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>., &amp; lete it boile a litil, &amp; &thorn;an kepe it for|&thorn;in vss.  &amp; &thorn;ou schalt &yogh;eue it him in &thorn;e morowe wi&thorn; a decoccion|of fenel seed, .ij. in &thorn;e wike.  &amp; &thorn;ou schalt enplastre al his wombe,|saue &thorn;e regioun of his lyuere, wi&thorn; &thorn;e forseid plastris &amp; dounge &amp;|vinegre.  &amp; vpon his lyuere leie an enplastre maad of .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .ij. of|barli mele, &amp; rosis, &amp; sandalis albi &amp; rubei ana. <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, camphore|.&yogh; .ij., &amp; distempere hem wi&thorn; water of rosis &amp; wi&thorn; vinegre.  &amp; if|he haue not &thorn;e feuere, &thorn;an &yogh;eue him gotis milk fasting.  And whan|&thorn;e patient bicome&thorn; smal in his wombe, &thorn;an sette him in a ba&thorn;, &thorn;at| be soden &thorn;erinne sulphur <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="202b">&amp; salt, &amp; he schal be &thorn;erinne but a litil|while.  &para; Herof &thorn;ou muste be war: whanne water is dried in a|man wi&thorn; drijnge wi&thorn; medicyns, &thorn;an his lymes leeue&thorn; swi&thorn;e drie;|wherfore &thorn;ei falli&thorn; in etik &amp; dien.  &THORN;erfore &thorn;ou muste in alle &thorn;es|&thorn;ingis be wel war /</P>
<P>&THORN;e cure &thorn;at is wi&thorn; iren falli&thorn; oonli in aschite, &thorn;at manie men|doon hardili, &amp; taki&thorn; no kepe of &thorn;e particuleris &thorn;erof, for &thorn;ei|knowen not &thorn;e science, for &thorn;ei doon al oon maner to &yogh;onge &amp; to|olde, to stronge &amp; to feble; &thorn;ei kutti&thorn; &thorn;e skyn vnder &thorn;e nauel, &amp;|alle men &thorn;at &thorn;ei kutten ou&thorn;er &thorn;e mooste weren perischid / Saue &thorn;ou|schalt take kepe of kunnynge, &amp; worche bi resoun / for &thorn;ow schalt|take kepe wher he be strong or no; &amp; if he be not strong, &thorn;ou|schalt do no cure to him.  &para; Also &thorn;ou schalt do no cure to olde|men &thorn;at ben to-broke, for &thorn;ou schalt not leeue &thorn;e strenk&thorn;e of an|oold man, for it is impossible for to fynde an oold man strong,|whanne &thorn;e dropesie is confermed on him / If it so be &thorn;at he be|&yogh;ong &amp; strong, &thorn;an &thorn;ow schalt haue good trust for to helpe him.| &para; Thanne &thorn;ou muste enquere sotilly wher <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="203a">&thorn;e principal vijs be of
<PB N="287">|&thorn;e lyuere, for &thorn;an &thorn;ou muste kutte him in &thorn;e splene side / And if it|so be &thorn;at &thorn;e splene be &thorn;e principal of &thorn;e dropesie, &thorn;an &thorn;e kuttynge|muste be in &thorn;e ri&yogh;tside.  And if &thorn;e cause come of lymes aboue, as|of &thorn;e stomac or of diafragma, &thorn;an &thorn;ou muste kutte him vpon|pecten.  &amp; if it be in a womman, &amp; come of &thorn;e vijs of &thorn;e maris,|&thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt kutte hir aboue &thorn;e nauele.  Whanne &thorn;ou knowist in|what place &thorn;ou schalt kutte &thorn;e pacient, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt opene &thorn;e|place of &thorn;e pacient, &amp; &thorn;ou schalt presse his wombe adounward as|miche as &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t, &amp; make him ete a litil of breed tostid<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>breed tostid,</I> Lat. panem tostum.  <I>Prompt. Parv.</I></NOTE> vpon|coolis, &amp; wet in wijn; &amp; &thorn;an lete him sitte tofore &thorn;ee bitwene a|strong mannes armys, &thorn;at mai holde him faste, &thorn;at he mowe not|meue in &thorn;e tyme whanne &thorn;ou wolt worche.  And &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt|take &thorn;e skyn &thorn;at is clepid mirac, wi&thorn; &thorn;i lifthond in &thorn;e place &thorn;ere &thorn;ou|wolt make &thorn;i kuttynge, &amp; &thorn;at skyn &thorn;ou schalt peerse endelongis|wi&thorn; an instrument &thorn;at is competent &thorn;erfore / And be wel war &thorn;at|&thorn;ou touche not siphac in no maner; and <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="203b">whanne &thorn;ou hast kutt &thorn;e |skyn aboue &amp; mirac, &thorn;an opene &thorn;e place &thorn;at &thorn;ou mowe se siphac.|&amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt peerse a litil hole in siphac &amp; sette &thorn;erto a canel,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>canel</I>, Lat. cannula.  See <I>N. E. Dict</I>., s. v. canal 1.</NOTE>|&amp; drawe out &thorn;erof as miche watir as &thorn;ou seest good for to saue his|vertu / &amp; &thorn;an drawe out &thorn;e canel, &amp; lete &thorn;e skyn &thorn;at is clepid|mirac goon ouer &thorn;e openynge of siphac, for &thorn;at wole suffre no &thorn;ing|to go out / In &thorn;e morowe opene &thorn;e same skyn a&yogh;en &thorn;at was kutt|first, &amp; putte in &thorn;e canel, &amp; kepe his vertu as miche as &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t.|&amp; &thorn;us &thorn;ou schalt do til &thorn;ou haue drawe out &thorn;e watir; saue &thorn;ou|schalt not drawe out al, for &thorn;ou schalt consume it afterward with|propre medicyns / Herof &thorn;ou schalt take kepe in &thorn;e tyme, &thorn;e whilis|&thorn;ou drawist out &thorn;e water, as it is forseid: &thorn;e patient schal ete good|metis, &amp; drinke good drinkis &amp; swete, &thorn;at mowe engendre in him|good spirits &amp; good blood: as good bro&thorn;is maad of hennys &amp; of|capouns.  &amp; di&yogh;t wi&thorn; swete &thorn;ingis, for eueri avoidinge laski&thorn; miche|&thorn;e spiritis; &amp; whanne &thorn;e spiritis falli&thorn;, &thorn;an a mannes vertues|failen /</P>
