<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="19">
<HEAD>Of &thorn;e cure of brennyng wi&thorn; fier ou&thorn;er with hoot watir|or with oile.</HEAD>
<P>A Mannes lymes ben brent wi&thorn; fier, watir, ou&thorn;ir wi&thorn; oile / In|&thorn;is caas &thorn;is is &thorn;e firste entencioun: or &thorn;e place bigynne to|bladdre,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>bladdre</I>, vesicari.</NOTE> &thorn;ou muste haue medicyns &thorn;at ben colde / And if it so be|&thorn;at &thorn;e place be vlceratus, &amp; &thorn;ou were not at &thorn;e firste bigynnyng,|or if &thorn;e brennyng be so miche &thorn;at &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t not defende, &thorn;at|vlcera ne come not &thorn;eron, &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou must haue medicyns &thorn;at  ben|lasse coold, &amp; medicyns &thorn;at ben clepid stiptica not fretynge / &THORN;ese| ben symple medicyns <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="227a">in &thorn;e firste caas / Take marbil stoon &amp; grinden|smal, &amp; alle &thorn;e sandalis,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat. omnes sandali.</NOTE> &amp; solatrum, &amp; watir of rosis, &amp; watir of|cucurbita, &amp; water of virga pastoris, &amp; of alle &thorn;ese &thorn;ingis make|a &thorn;ing for to leie &thorn;eron / Also oile of rosis, &amp; &thorn;e &yogh;elke of an ey|ben good &thorn;erfore / Also bole armoniac temperid wi&thorn; vinegre is|good &thorn;erfore.  And it muste ofte be remeued &amp; ofte leid to a&yogh;en,|for &thorn;e cooldnes of ofte remeuyng schal defende it fro bladdring /|Naturel medicyns &thorn;at ben gode in &thorn;e secunde caas: / But vnguentum|de calx maad in &thorn;is maner / &rx;, calcis viue bene cocte &thorn;at ben|maad of an hard stoon, and waische it wi&thorn; coold watir til it lete al|his scharpnes, &amp; &thorn;an wi&thorn; oile of rosis &amp; wex make an oynement /|Also vnguentum album Rasis &thorn;at is maad in &thorn;e antidotarie is good|&thorn;erfore / I nyle for &thorn;is cure sette no mo medycyns.  &THORN;oru&yogh; &thorn;e grace|of god almi&yogh;ty &thorn;e &thorn;ridde tretis is fulfillid //</P></DIV4></DIV3>
