<DIV3 TYPE="chapter" N="2">
<HEAD>Of &thorn;e maner of resolutiuis.</HEAD>
<P>Whanne oon strong, or<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>of</I>.</NOTE> manye feble of .x. causis letti&thorn;|repercussiuis, ou&thorn;ir whanne &thorn;ou hast a repercussif, &amp; &thorn;ou|ne mi&yogh;t not putte awei &thorn;e mater, &thorn;an &thorn;ou muste leie &thorn;erto resolutiuis.|&amp; as it is aforseid of repercussiuis, in &thorn;e same maner I|seie of resolutiuis: whanne a man ha&thorn; akynge ou&thorn;ir greet swellynge,|&thorn;ou schalt leie &thorn;erto no resolutiuis, or &thorn;ou haue maad him a|competent purgacioun.  &para; fforwhi, as it is aforseid, enpostym ou&thorn;er|greet akynge come&thorn; of causis wi&thorn;innefor&thorn;, &thorn;an it mote <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="247a">nedis come |of repleccioun of &thorn;e bodi.  &amp; &thorn;an if &thorn;ou leist &thorn;erto resolutiuis, &thorn;at|wolde drawe to &thorn;e place more mater / for &thorn;er is no resolutif, &thorn;at ne|it is hoot / &amp; eueri &thorn;ing &thorn;at is hoot, is attractif / What schal we|do in &thorn;is caas?  &para; ffirst &thorn;ou schalt lete him blood, ou&thorn;ir make him|a medicyn laxatif, ou&thorn;ir bo&thorn;e two, as &thorn;ou seest &thorn;at it wole spede /|And &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt bigynne for to resolue wi&thorn; medicyns resolutiuis|&thorn;at been hoot &amp; sotil<NOTE PLACE="foot">Some passages are omitted, in which Lanfranc quotes from his "Chirurgia|parva."</NOTE> // This is &thorn;e difference bitwixe resolutiuis &amp;|maturatiuis: &para; Resolutiuis haue&thorn; tempere hete wi&thorn; sotilnes &amp; openynge.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat. cum subtilitate aperitiua.</NOTE>
<PB N="334">|&para; Maturatiuis haue&thorn; tempere hete wi&thorn; viscosite / &THORN;erfore it|falli&thorn; ofte tyme, &thorn;at whanne &thorn;ou leist resolutiuis vpon miche mater|&amp; greet, it maki&thorn; &thorn;e mater sotil &amp; hoot, &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;e kindely hete|wi&thorn;inne is comfortid wi&thorn; &thorn;e hete wi&thorn;outfor&thorn;, &amp; it bifalli&thorn; ofte tyme,|&thorn;at medicyns resolutiuis in &thorn;is caas maki&thorn; &thorn;e mater maturatif /|Also if &thorn;ou leist medicyn maturatif vpon litil mater &amp; sotil it|heti&thorn; &thorn;e mater, &amp; &thorn;e natural hete wi&thorn;inne is comfortid &thorn;erwi&thorn;, &amp; so| &thorn;e heete multiplie&thorn;, &amp; in &thorn;is maner &thorn;e heete <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="247b">mai be resolued.|&para; The maner of resoluing: Make a decoccioun of herbis of whiche|&thorn;ow wolt make &thorn;i medicyn, &amp; kepe &thorn;e watir &thorn;at &thorn;e herbis ben|soden yn, &amp; wi&thorn; &thorn;e same watir &thorn;ou schalt waische &thorn;e lyme, til it|bicome reed, &amp; &thorn;an leie &thorn;ervpon &thorn;e medicyn resolutif.  &para; Herof|&thorn;ou muste be war, &thorn;at ofte tyme a medycyn resolutif resolue&thorn; &thorn;e|sotil mater, &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;at is greet, bicome&thorn; hard, &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;e more &thorn;at|&thorn;ou art aboute to resolue, &thorn;e more it wole bicome hard / &thorn;erfore|&thorn;ou muste be bisi in &thorn;is caas &amp; leie &thorn;erto mollificatiuis, &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou|schalt go to resolutiuis, &amp; in &thorn;is maner &thorn;ou schalt worche it til it|be al resolued.  &para; Of medicyns resolutiuis, summe ben simple: as,|camomilla, Mellilotum, paritaria, malua siluestris &amp; alia,<NOTE PLACE="foot">The Prints read "siue <I>alba</I>."  Add. 26,106, siue <I>alba</I> corrected to <I>alia</I>.|The correct reading is either <I>alta</I> or <I>altea</I>.  Add. 15,236, lf. 5: "<I>Malua|viscus. bismalua. Altea idem. G. Wymauve A. mersmauve.</I>"  <I>Alphita</I>, p. 110:|"Malva silvestris, malva viscus, altea ... alta malva idem."</NOTE> volibilis,<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. volibilis.  <I>Alphita</I>, p. 192: "<I>Volubilis, corrigiola idem, arbores|parvas et herbas ligat. gall. [corrigi]ole, angl. berebinde.</I>"</NOTE>|fumus terre, caulis, anetum, vrtica, enula, borago, sambucus, kebulus,|valeriana, &amp; alle herbis &thorn;at ben hoot in tempere,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat. temperate calida.</NOTE> wi&thorn; sotilnes.|&para; De seminibus / Semina caulium, aneti, vrtice, malue.  Semina|diuretica: cantabrum,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>cantabrum</I>, bran.  Add. 15,236, lf. 3: "<I>Cantabrum .i. grossum furfur|tritici vel frumenti .G. la grose brene.</I>"</NOTE> omne,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: omne amilum de ordeo.</NOTE> farina ordei, orobi, &amp; fabe / Pinguede| porci &amp; anseri, anatis, galline, aquile.  &para; De gummis / <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="248a">Mastix,|olibanum, opoponac, asa fetida, mirra, serapinum, armonicum, bdellium,|galbanum, &amp; alle maner sotil gummis: lapdanum, ysopus|humida, terbentina, cera, swetynge of bestis, &amp; buttir.  &para; Medicyns|resolutif &amp; compound of &thorn;e forseid, simple &thorn;ou schalt fynde in &thorn;e|nexte chapitre here tofore / &THORN;is is an oile resoluinge / &amp; maki&thorn; hoot|&amp; aceessi&thorn; akynge / &rx;, florum camomille recencium, fenigreci seminis|ana .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij., leie hem in xx .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. of oile of oliue in a glasen vessel,|&amp; lete it stonde to &thorn;e sunne .xl. daies in somer, &amp; &thorn;an kepe it for
<PB N="335">|&thorn;in vss.  If &thorn;ou haddist nede herof &amp; if it<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>if it</I>, above line.</NOTE> were in winter, &thorn;an|take &thorn;e flouris of camomille dried &amp; fenigrec &amp; oile, as it is aforseid,|&amp; sette &thorn;is glasen vessel in a caudroun ful of watir, &amp; make fier|vndir, &amp; loke &thorn;at &thorn;e water ne boile not, &amp; so it schal stonde al a|dai in hoot water / &amp; whanne it is coold cole it, &amp; kepe &thorn;e oile for|&thorn;in vss / And in &thorn;is maner &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t make oile of rosis, if &thorn;ou hast|nede, &amp; oile of absinthium, &amp; of rue, &amp; of o&thorn;er mo &thorn;at &thorn;ou hast|nede of // Ano&thorn;er oile &thorn;at is resolutif / &rx;, olei antiqui .l&imacr;. j.,|seminis aneti nouiter in vmbra siccati .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j., putte him in a viol|fourti daies to &thorn;e sunne, ou&thorn;er sette it in hoot water <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="248b">as it is aforseid. |&para; Ano&thorn;er oile &thorn;at is resoluyng and maki&thorn; hoot &amp; accessi&thorn; akynge,|&amp; is good for to achaufe a mannys reynes &amp; a wommans maris, &amp; it|is clepid olium de lilio compositum / &rx;, olij antiqui .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>. xx., florum|liliorum alborum, &amp; kutte awei &thorn;erof al &thorn;at is &yogh;elowe, cassilaginis,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Add. 15,236, lf. 3: "<I>Cassilago, Iusquiamus idem G. geliner A. henebel.|vel heneban.</I>"  The Lat. has <I>Cassio lignea</I>, see <I>Alphita</I>, p. 35.</NOTE>|costi, masticis, carpobalsami ana .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> i.,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>carpobalsamum</I>, "balsames bloed."  Wr. W&uuml;., 199, 41 (X cent.).</NOTE> cinamoni ana .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>., putte alle|&thorn;ese in a glasen vessel, &amp; lete hem stonde in &thorn;e schadowe al a|mone&thorn;e, &amp; &thorn;an do awey &thorn;e lilie flouris of &thorn;e oile, &amp; kepe &thorn;e oile|for &thorn;in vss.  &para; Ano&thorn;er oile &thorn;at is clepid olium mastice, &amp; is swi&thorn;e|resolutif, &amp; is good for febilnes of &thorn;e stomac, &amp; it is good for|akynge of a mannes stomac / &rx;, olium oliuarum mediocriter maturarum|.l&imacr;. ij., masticis .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>. vj., boile hem togidere in a double vessel,|til &thorn;e mastix &amp; &thorn;e oile be dissolued, &amp; kepe it for &thorn;in vss.  &para; This|&thorn;ou muste knowe, &thorn;at whanne &thorn;ou wolt make &thorn;at, &thorn;at schal be|repercussif &amp; coold &amp; comfortyng for &thorn;e lyme, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt chese|oile &thorn;at is not to ripe, as for to make olium rosis, olium mirtinum,|&amp; o&thorn;ere mo.  If &thorn;ou wolt make oile &thorn;at schal be resoluyng, ou&thorn;er|persyng, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt chese oile &thorn;at is ripe / And in &thorn;is maner|&thorn;ou schalt <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="249a">knowe, whe&thorn;er &thorn;e oile be ripe or no.  Oile &thorn;at is not |ripe, wole be grene, &amp; &thorn;at is ripe wole be whit, &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;at is in &thorn;e|meene, wole be meene colour bitwixe &thorn;e two.  &para; Oynementis &thorn;at|ben resolutif ben maad in &thorn;is maner: of iiij .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> of<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>of</I> twice.</NOTE> oile of camomille|ou&thorn;er of sum o&thorn;er oile &amp; <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. of wex in somer, &amp; <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>. in|winter, &amp; <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. of poudre of seedis of aneti, caulium, flouris of|camomille.  &para; Ysopus humida is a good oynement resolutif, &amp; is|maad in &thorn;is maner: / Take of &thorn;e smal wolle &thorn;at is bitwixe &thorn;e|schepis leggis, &amp; take &thorn;erof a good quantite, &amp; take as miche water,
<PB N="336">|&amp; lete &thorn;e wolle ligge in &thorn;e watir adai &amp; any&yogh;t, &amp; &thorn;an boile hem a|litil wi&thorn; lent fier, &amp; &thorn;an cole hem, &amp; whanne &thorn;ei ben coold, wrynge|hem &thorn;oru&yogh; a cloo&thorn;, &amp; do &thorn;e water &thorn;erof into a leden vessel, &amp; boile|it wi&thorn; lent fier, &amp; algate meeue it wi&thorn; a spature til it bicome &thorn;icke|as it were an oynement.  &para; Of enplastris &thorn;e beste &thorn;at is diaculon|Rasis &thorn;at resolue&thorn; scrophulas &amp; glandulas, &amp; maki&thorn; carbunculis maturatif|&amp; is swi&thorn;e comoun / &rx;, olij antiqui de oliuis maturis vncias|quinque, litargiri .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j., &amp; &thorn;ou schalt poudre &thorn;e litarge in a morter &amp;| do &thorn;erto <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="249b">&thorn;in oile &amp; medle hem togidere, &amp; &thorn;an do hem in a vessel &amp;|boile hem togidere, &amp; meeue hem algatis wi&thorn; a spature, &amp; do &thorn;erto|de muscillagine seminis lini, fenigreci, ana .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij, &amp; muscillaginnem|malue visci .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j, &amp; &thorn;an boile hem til &thorn;ei bicome &thorn;icke, &amp; make &thorn;erof|gobetis &amp; kepe hem to &thorn;in vss, &amp; if &thorn;ou wolt worche &thorn;erwi&thorn;, take|&thorn;erof as miche as &thorn;ou wolt, &amp; plane it vpon le&thorn;er or vpon lynnen|cloo&thorn;, &amp; leie vpon &thorn;e place.  &para; Diaculon Iohannis Mesue is better|&thorn;an &thorn;is / &amp; worchi&thorn; more strongli.  &THORN;at &thorn;ou schalt finde in paruo|compendio.  &para; Also ano&thorn;er plastre &thorn;at is resolutif / &rx;, maluarum|siluestrum, paritarie, flouris of camomille, Melliloti ana @. j.,|boile hem in watir til &thorn;ei be wel soden, &amp; &thorn;an stampe hem, &amp; take|of &thorn;e same watir .iij. partis, &amp; of sum oile &thorn;at is resolutif oon|parti, seminis caulium, aneti partem <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>., furfuris, farine ordei, ana|partem j., boile hem alle togidere &amp; make &thorn;erof as it were pultes,|&amp; &thorn;an do &thorn;erto of &thorn;e herbis &thorn;at ben soden as miche as of al &thorn;e|remenaunt, &amp; leie it vpon &thorn;e place &thorn;at &thorn;ou wolt, sumdel hoot as| it is aforseid, &amp; seke medicins resolutiuis <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="250a">&thorn;at ben in paruo compendio,|&amp; do it to, &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t haue medicyns resolutiuis|ynowe /</P>
