<DIV3 TYPE="chapter" N="3">
<HEAD>Of &thorn;e tretis of &thorn;e foure maturatiuis.</HEAD>
<P>Whanne &thorn;ou hast resolued mani daies ou&thorn;er leid &thorn;erto repercussiuis,|&amp; ne is nou&yogh;t worth, saue &thorn;e mater wole bicome|maturatif, &thorn;an if his bodi be avoidid as it is aforseid, &thorn;an [begynne]<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: "Quando pluribus resoluisti diebus aut forte repercussisti, nec|valet, sed materia desiderat maturari, tunc premissis evacuationibus necessariis|vel possibilibus, <I>incipe</I> maturare."</NOTE>|for to leie &thorn;erto maturatiuis / Eueri medicyn &thorn;at is maturatif is|hoot in tempere wi&thorn; a maner viscosite &thorn;at wole not suffre &thorn;e vapour|to goon out, but it holdi&thorn; him wi&thorn;inne til it be maturid; &amp; ben|&thorn;ese: Malua viscus, branca vrcina, radix brionie, radix lappacii
<PB N="337">|acuti,<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>lappa acuta</I>.</NOTE> baucie<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>baucia</I>.  <I>Alphita</I>, p. 21: "pastinaca, angl. widleskirwit."</NOTE> Radix, farine frumenti, semen lini, fenigreci, ficus|sicce, &amp; alle &thorn;at ben forseid in &thorn;e nexte chapitre tofore, if &thorn;at &thorn;ei|be&thorn; medlid herwi&thorn;.  &para; This is a good maturatif compound of|manie &thorn;ingis &thorn;at maki&thorn; hoot mater maturatif.  &rx;, foliorum|malue nigre, id est comoun malue pinguis seu ortolane, brance vrcine,|radix brioni, radicis malue visci ana. <ABBR EXPAN="[handful]"><GAP></ABBR> .j., se&thorn;e hem alle in watir|&amp; stampe hem, &amp; &thorn;an do &thorn;erto malua visci, &amp; &thorn;an take of &thorn;e same|watir a pound <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="250b">&amp; freisch grese .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij., &amp; sotil mele of whete .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iij., |&amp; sotil mele of lynseed &amp; of fenigrec ana .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. &amp; <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>., medle hem|togidere &amp; boile hem perfi&yogh;tli, &amp; make &thorn;erof cataplasma, &amp; &thorn;an do|&thorn;erto of &thorn;e foreseid herbis &amp; rootis wel grounde, &amp; medle hem|togidere, &amp; loke &thorn;at &thorn;ei be not to &thorn;icke / for it schal be algate &thorn;in|entencioun, &thorn;at cataplasma, &thorn;at schal be resolutif or maturatif or|mundificatif, ne schal not be hard; for if it be hard, it wole make|akynge to &thorn;e lyme, &amp; &thorn;an it wole anoie more &thorn;an profite.  &para; Item,|if &thorn;ou dredist woodnes of mater, &thorn;an &thorn;ou ne schalt do &thorn;erto no|fenigrec; for it is swi&thorn;e hoot, &amp; &thorn;erwi&thorn; &thorn;e mater wole be as it were|a feuere.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: et cito per illum inflammatur materia.</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;erfore I counseile &thorn;ee &thorn;at &thorn;ou do no fenigrec &thorn;erto /|If &thorn;ou dredist, &thorn;at &thorn;e mater is swi&thorn;e hoot / if &thorn;er be wi&thorn; &thorn;at|mater ony gretnes or ony coold mater, &thorn;an make of &thorn;e forseid cataplasma|.ij. partis, fermenti de frumento<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>fermento</I>.</NOTE> partem j., &amp; medle hem|togidere. &amp; Isaac sei&thorn;: &thorn;at &thorn;is is good for mater &thorn;at is medlid wi&thorn;|hoot cause &amp; coold cause togidere.  &para; Also a good maturatif / Take|hony &amp; butter ana, &amp; medle hem with mele til &thorn;ei be as &thorn;icke as|it were pultes.  <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="251a">&para; Item embrocaciouns in resoluciouns &amp; maturacioun, |&amp; is good for akynge of woundis of concussioun in &thorn;e heed /|concussioun is as miche to seie as smiten wi&thorn; a staf / &rx;, olij <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij.,|cere albe <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j., cimini, rute, arthemesie ana. <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>
<ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>., absinthi, paritarie,|brance vrcine, ana <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij., grinde wel &thorn;e herbis &amp; &thorn;e grese|togidere in a morter, &amp; &thorn;an do &thorn;erto poudre of comyn, &amp; oile, &amp;|medle hem wel togidere.  &para; Also pultes &thorn;at wole make an enpostym|maturatif: &rx;, foliorum malue, bismalue, paritorie, volubilis maioris,|iusquiami ana <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij., se&thorn;e hem in a litil watir, &amp; &thorn;an presse hem &amp;|staumpe hem wel, &amp; &thorn;an medle hem wi&thorn; <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iij of &thorn;e same watir &thorn;at|&thorn;ei weren soden ynne, &amp; medle &thorn;erwi&thorn; <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. of grese, &thorn;at it be cold,|&amp; barli mele &thorn;at suffisi&thorn; / In &thorn;is maner &thorn;ou schalt make a coold
<PB N="338">|mater maturatif / &rx;, cepe unum<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>vinum</I>.  Add. 26,106, fol. 103 <I>b</I>.: "cepe unum album."</NOTE> album, item de capitibus allij,|&amp; sette hem vndir askis, &amp; distempere hem wi&thorn; &thorn;e .iij. part of|buttir, &amp; do &thorn;erto mele of fenigrek, &amp; of lynseed, &amp; make &thorn;erof an|enplastre. &amp; do &thorn;erto .ij. &yogh;elkis of eiren soden hard, &amp; <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. off|malui visci preparati, &amp; <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij. of fermenti.  &para; Also a maturatif of|greet mater &amp; coold &amp; hard.  &rx;, bdellij, serapini ana <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. &amp; <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, &amp;| dissolue hem in vinegre / <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="251b">&amp; stampe hem wel, &amp; do &thorn;erto .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. of|terbentyne, &amp; dissolue hem to &thorn;e fier / But loke &thorn;at it ne boile|not, &amp; do &thorn;erto oile of lilie .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij., &amp; make it &thorn;icke wi&thorn; sutil mele|of lupinis, &amp; of fenigrec / Item <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>. of olibani, &amp; fenigrec maad to|poudre sotili poudrid, &amp; medle hem wi&thorn; .l&imacr;. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR> of hony; &thorn;is wole be|a good maturatif for coold causis.  &para; Also vnguentum tetrafarmacum,<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>cetrafaro&yogh;atum</I>.</NOTE>|&amp; it is clepid of Auicenne basilicon,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Phillips: "<I>Basilicon</I>, a Royal Ointment or Plaister, otherwise called|Tetrapharmacon, because it is made up of four Ingredients, viz., Pitch, Rosin,|Wax, and Oil."</NOTE> &amp; &thorn;us manie men|preisi&thorn; &thorn;is medicyn.  Galen, Auicen, Serapion, Iohannes Mesue, &amp;|Haly &thorn;e abbot; &amp; it maki&thorn; enpostyms maturatif, &amp; it is good for|woundis, &amp; for vlcera &thorn;at ben bicome hard / &rx;, cere, resine, picis,|cepi vaccini,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: sepi vaccini.</NOTE> ana, &amp; olij quod suffisi&thorn; / Summen in stide of cepum,|&thorn;ei putten buttir, &amp; summen in winter &thorn;ei doon &thorn;erto oon parti of|bdellium, &amp; summen taken oonli ceram, picem, &amp; rasinam ana, &amp;|olium; &amp; &thorn;is is basilicon minus.  &para; Also a good maturatif for|antracem / &amp; is good for to make a wickid enpostym maturatif, as|I haue aforseid in his place / &rx;, ficus siccas bene pingues, numero|.vj., vue passe<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>vue passe</I>, dried grapes, i. e. raisins.</NOTE> de corinthio .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j., duas spicas allij mundatas, piperis|grana .xij., salis nitri .&yogh; .ij., stampe alle &thorn;ese &amp; do &thorn;erto oold oile| <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij., aceti <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="252a"><ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j., fermenti acerimi as miche as is &thorn;e half|of alle togidere.|&para; Also a maturatif for antracem / but if he be swi&thorn;e|hard &amp; malicious, an enplastre maad of hony is good &thorn;erfore &amp;|of oile of violet.  &para; Also for to make antracem &amp; carbunculum|maturatif / &rx;, fermenti acris, lactis mulieris, mellis, vitellorum|ouorum ana, medle hem togidere.  If &thorn;ou wolt worche more|strongeli, do &thorn;erto galbanum dissolued as myche as &thorn;e haluendel of|oon.  &amp; if &thorn;ou wolt make it more strong, for to make it maturatif,|&amp; for to make it breke, &thorn;an do &thorn;erto culueris doung &amp; of hennis|ana, as miche as wole be .iiij. part of oon, as it is aforseid / baurac,
<PB N="339">|vj. part of oon &amp; <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>.; &thorn;ese .iij. maturatiuis suffisi&thorn; &thorn;ee / &para; Also &thorn;is|is a rule &thorn;at is ful profitable for &thorn;ee / whanne &thorn;ou wolt leie ony|maturatif to a place: first &thorn;ou schalt make embrocam<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: prius locum embrocas.  Matth. Sylv.: "<I>Embroca</I> id est infusio|quam nos dicimus fomentum &amp; embrocatio id est infusio sed quando ab alto|infunditur."  See p. 331, note 5.</NOTE> to &thorn;e lyme|wi&thorn; a decoccioun of herbis maturatiuis, soden in watir, &amp; wi&thorn; &thorn;at|hoot watir &thorn;ou schalt ba&thorn;e &thorn;e lyme til &thorn;e lyme bicome reed, &amp; &thorn;an|leie &thorn;eron a plastre of maturatiuis &thorn;at ben forseid oon &thorn;erof, for &thorn;ou|hast sufficiently ynowe, &amp; loke &thorn;at &thorn;e enplastre be not to hard, <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="252b">&amp; |as hoot as he mai suffre it &thorn;ou schalt leie it &thorn;erto / &para; Thou hast|herd sufficientli of maturatiuis, ynow it is nede to speke of mundificatiuis.|For whanne an hard matir is maad maturatif, it is nede|for to leie &thorn;erto mundificatiuis as it is forseid in &thorn;e worchinge of|enpostyms /</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="chapter" N="4">
<HEAD>&para; Of &thorn;e tretis of mundificatiuis /</HEAD>
<P>Mundificatum is as miche to seie as clensyng, &amp; doi&thorn; awei|hore. &amp; eueri &thorn;ing &thorn;at doi&thorn; awei hore in woundis &amp; superfluite,|may be seid a mundificatif / A mundificatif may be seid in|.ij. maners / As a medicyn &thorn;at is taken bi &thorn;e mou&thorn;, ou&thorn;er &thorn;at is|putt in bine&thorn;e wi&thorn; a clisterie, ou&thorn;er wi&thorn; a pessarie<NOTE PLACE="foot">Traheron, Vigo. Interpret.: "<I>Pessarie</I>.  Pessus is woll tossed, and|made rounde after the fassyon of a fynger wherewith medicines are receyued|and conueyed into the matrice."</NOTE> for to make clene|a mannes lymes wi&thorn;inne.  &amp; of &thorn;is kinde ben sirupis maad of|seedis &thorn;at maki&thorn; clene a mannes lymes, &amp; weies of &thorn;e vrine / And|&thorn;er ben summe medicyns &thorn;at maki&thorn; clene a mannes blood as cassia|fistula, manna,<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>manci</I>.</NOTE> tamarindi; &amp; al medicyns laxatiuis mowen be|clepid mundificatiuis, &amp; herof is not entencioun in &thorn;is caas /|&para; Ano&thorn;ir.  I wole speke of medicyns mundificatif in cirurgie.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: Alio modo loquimur de medicina mundificatiua in cyrurgia.</NOTE>|&amp; &thorn;at is propirli seid a medicyn, &thorn;at doi&thorn; awei greet superfluite|ou&thorn;er gret greuance <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="253a">of quitture, ou&thorn;er remeue&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>remeued</I>.</NOTE> awei harde crustis |in woundis, ou&thorn;ir in vlceribus, &amp; maki&thorn; clene woundis &amp; vlcera of|&thorn;at superfluite / ffor as it is seid in ano&thorn;er place: In eueri wounde|&thorn;at is holow, &thorn;at is as miche to seie as whanne it ha&thorn; lost substaunce|of fleisch &thorn;eron, &thorn;an bi skille<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat. necessario.</NOTE> &thorn;er schulde be engendrid|&thorn;eron .ij. superfluites, &thorn;at oon schal be greet, &amp; &thorn;at o&thorn;er schal be|sotil.  &amp; &thorn;ese wollen lette &thorn;e souding of a wounde, &amp; &thorn;ei wolen
<PB N="340">|lette &thorn;at &thorn;e fleisch mai not wexe.  &para; &THORN;an medicyn mundificatif|remeue&thorn; greet superfluite.  Of driynge medicyns, we wolen speke|in &thorn;e chapitre next / This maner medicyn schal go bifore regeneracioun|&amp; consolidacioun, of whiche we wolli&thorn; speke herafter;|&thorn;ou&yogh; aggregatiua or conglutinatiua come sumtyme for to soude wi&thorn;outen|&thorn;at, &thorn;at &thorn;is medicyns ne goi&thorn; not tofore, as whanne woundis|ben sewid &amp; ben maad hool wi&thorn;outen regeneracioun of quitture.|&THORN;is medicyn maki&thorn; clene, &amp; drie&thorn; sumwhat, as water &amp; hony|whanne vlcera virulenta be&thorn; waischen &thorn;erwi&thorn;, ou&thorn;ir woundis in|which agendri&thorn; miche quitture; &amp; sumtyme it is more strong, as| whanne &thorn;er be&thorn; medlid &thorn;erwi&thorn; poudris corosiuis &thorn;at han litil <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="253b">vertu|of corosiuis, &amp; helpi&thorn; for to make clene, &amp; whanne corosiuis ben|seid for to take awey yuel fleisch &thorn;at ne mai not be taken awei|with medicyns /</P>
<P>Therfore I wole sette medicyns bi rule, &amp; first I wole speke of|medicyns &thorn;at ben simple / ffor as me sei&thorn; .x. si&thorn;is rehersid liketh a|man.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Add. 26,106, fol. 104: "et quum medicine simplices raro ponuntur ad|mundificandum, ideo ponam medicamina composita per ordinem, denumerando|medicinas simplices, non curando, quoniam decies repetita placebunt."</NOTE>  &para; Thou schalt wite &thorn;is &thorn;at woundis &thorn;at ben freisch, &thorn;er it|is no nede for to engendre quitture whanne &thorn;er is noon concussioun,|nei&thorn;er of nerues, ne of boon, ne prickynge, ne &thorn;er is noon akynge|&thorn;erwi&thorn; / &thorn;an it is no nede for to leie &thorn;erto mundificatiuis, but oonli|consolidatiuis / But whanne a wou[n]de is chaungid wi&thorn; &thorn;e eir or|enpostymed, or greet akynge, &thorn;an &thorn;ou muste leie &thorn;erto maturatiuis;|&amp; whanne &thorn;e akynge &amp; &thorn;e o&thorn;ere accidentis ben awei, &thorn;an &thorn;ou schalt|bigynne for to leie &thorn;erto mundificatiuis as it is aforseid in his|chapitre / This is a coold mundificatif for to make clene woundis|&thorn;at ben freisch in which is good quitture.  &rx;, mellis rosati colati|.<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>. iij., farine subtillissime ordei .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j., &amp; do &thorn;erto a litil water, &amp;| se&thorn;e hem softli &thorn;at &thorn;ei ne brenne not, &amp; algate &thorn;ou schalt <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="254a">meue it|wi&thorn; a spature, &amp; &thorn;an make it abrood vpon a cloo&thorn;, &amp; leie it vpon|&thorn;e wounde / This maki&thorn; clene &amp; comforti&thorn; / If it so be &thorn;at a|wounde be in nerues placis, &thorn;an it is good for to do &thorn;erto a litil|terbentyn waischen, whanne it is doon adoun fro &thorn;e fier / for terbentyn|schal not boile, whanne itt schal be putt into enplastris,|for it wole lese his worching in &thorn;e boilyng.  &para; Ano&thorn;ir mundificatif|&thorn;at maki&thorn; clene duram matrem whanne a man is hurt in &thorn;e|heed, &amp; whanne dura mater is bicome blac / &rx;, mellis rosati|colati <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j., olij <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>., medle hem togidere.  &para; Ano&thorn;er mundificatif
<PB N="341">|&thorn;at maki&thorn; woundis maturatif &thorn;at ben to-swolle &amp; ben not to brennyng|hoot, but sumwhat toward cooldnes / &rx;, mellis rosati colati|.l&imacr;. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>., farine fenigreci .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij., farine ordei .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j.  &para; Ano&thorn;er mundificatif|for vlcera &thorn;at be&thorn; newe in enpostyms / Take &yogh;elkis of eiren|rawe, &amp; medle &thorn;erwi&thorn; whete mele as miche as wole suffise; &thorn;is wole|make clene &amp; do awei &thorn;e akynge, &amp; make &thorn;e place coold / &para; Also|ano&thorn;er mundificatif &thorn;at wole make maturatif &thorn;erwi&thorn;, &amp; is good|whanne a man wole <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="254b">kutte an enpostym tofore his tyme.  &amp; it is |a propre medicyn for to make clene antrasem &amp; carbunculo &amp; alle|maner pustulis &thorn;at ben venymous aftir &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at &thorn;ei ben opened,|&amp; it is good for to make clene, vlcera &thorn;at ben oold / &rx; mellis albi|boni .l&imacr;. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>., farine subtilissime tritici .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iij, medle hem togidere in|a panne.  &amp; whanne &thorn;ei ben wel medlid, &thorn;an do &thorn;erto iuys of|apium .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> vij., &amp; &thorn;an medle hem wel togidere vpon lent fier, &amp; boile|hem til &thorn;ei bicome as it were pultes.  &amp; &thorn;an do hem adoun of &thorn;e|fier &amp; stire hem wel, &amp; kepe hem for &thorn;in vss / If it so be &thorn;at &thorn;ou|dredist of a cancre or of a festre in vlceribus &thorn;at ben oold, &amp; if|&thorn;ou wolt make a mundificatif &thorn;erfore, &thorn;an in &thorn;e stide of apium do|absinthium, &amp; it wole be good.  &para; Ano&thorn;er mundificatif in vlceribus|&thorn;at ben rotid, &amp; whanne &thorn;er engendri&thorn; &thorn;ervpon greet rotyng / &rx;,|mellis l&imacr; .j., farine siliginis .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iiij., farine fenigreci, orobi, lupinorum,|mirre, ana <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j., succi absinthij l&imacr; .j., medle hem alle togidere, &amp;|poudre &thorn;ingis &thorn;at schulen be poudrid, &amp; boile hem sotilli til &thorn;ei be|perfi&yogh;tli boilid; &amp; whanne &thorn;ou doist hem adoun of &thorn;e fier, &thorn;an do|&thorn;erto of terbentyn .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iiij., <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="255a">&amp; medle hem wel togidere / Alle &thorn;ese |mundificatiuis schulen be maad abrood vpon a cloo&thorn; of lynnen, &amp;|leid vpon vlcus for to make it clene aftir &thorn;e tyme &thorn;at &thorn;ei be&thorn;|waische, as it is aforseid in &thorn;e chapitre de vlceribus / &para; A poudre|&thorn;at is mundificatif of crustis &amp; greet fleisch &thorn;at is engendrid in|oold vlceribus, &amp; wi&thorn;oute greet violence of fretyng / &rx;, succi affodillorum|.<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> vj., calcis viue .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> ij., auripigmenti .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j., medle hem|togidere, &amp; sette hem in &thorn;e sunne in &thorn;e mone&thorn;e of august, &amp; on|ny&yogh;tis do it out of &thorn;e eir, &amp; in &thorn;is maner &thorn;ou schalt do til it be|drie, &amp; make herof gobetis, &amp; &thorn;an drie hem in &thorn;e schadowe.  &amp;|&thorn;ou schalt kepe hem in a vessel of tree in a place &thorn;at be not to|drie, ne to moist. &amp; whanne &thorn;ou hast nede &thorn;erto, grinde oon &thorn;erof,|&amp; leie it vpon &thorn;e place.  &para; Also a good mundificatif for vlcera is|vnguentum viride, &thorn;at is maad of oon part of vert de grece, &amp; .ij.|partis of hony, medlid wel togidere.  &para; Also a good oynement for|to make clene, vlcera &thorn;at ben hori, &amp; festri, &amp; polipum, &amp; wickid
<PB N="342">|vlcera, &amp; is clepid vnguentum veneris, ou&thorn;er vnguentum apostolorum.| &amp; it is good for to remeue awei fleisch in vlceris / <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="255b">&rx;, cere|albe, rasine albe, armoniaci ana .&yogh;. xiiij., bdellij, astrologie, olibani|gummosi ana .&yogh;. vj., galbani, mirre ana .&yogh;. iiij., litargiri .&yogh;. viij.,|opoponac, floris eris ana. &yogh;. iij.; &thorn;e gummys schulen be maad neische|in vinegre, &amp; dissolued wi&thorn; fier &thorn;at be lent, &amp; &thorn;an do &thorn;erto wex|dissolued wi&thorn; l&imacr;. ij. of oile in somer, &amp; iiij. in winter. &amp; whanne|&thorn;ei ben molten, do &thorn;erto &thorn;i poudris, &amp; make &thorn;erof an oynement.|&para; Ano&thorn;er oynement clensi&thorn; wel nerues &amp; drawi&thorn; out &thorn;e quitture, &amp;|it is clepid mundificatiuum rasina<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: mundificatiuum de rasina.</NOTE> / &rx;, rasine, mellis, terbentyn|ana .l&imacr;. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>., mirre, sarcocolle, farine fenigreci, seminis lini ana
<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j.,|dissolue &thorn;e rosyn, hony &amp; wex togidere, &amp; &thorn;an do &thorn;erto &thorn;i poudris,|&amp; make &thorn;erof pultes.  &para; Also we moten vse medicyns &thorn;at ben|more strong, &amp; ben clepid medicine cauteri&yogh;antes, for to make clene|vlcera &thorn;at ben yuel in neruous place.  &amp; &thorn;e teching herof &thorn;ou|schalt fynde in &thorn;e chapitre de medicinis facientibus opus cauterij.</P>
