<DIV3 TYPE="chapter" N="5">
<HEAD>Of medicyns regeneratiuis &amp; consolidatiuis.</HEAD>
<P>It &thorn;inki&thorn; bi &thorn;e maner of speche &thorn;at &thorn;e medicyns &thorn;at ben seid|in &thorn;is chapitre ben al oon, but &thorn;er is miche difference bitwixe| / ffor <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="256a">of summen alle &thorn;ei ben clepid consolidatiuis.|But aggregatiue &amp; consolidatiue ben al oon / And regeneratiue,|&amp; incarnatiue, &amp; facientes carnem nasci, ben oon to seie; &amp;|&thorn;er is greet difference bitwixe hem &thorn;at ben forseid &amp; &thorn;ese / And|sigillatiuis, &amp; cicatri&yogh;atiuis, &amp; consolidatiuis ben al oon; ne&thorn;eles|alle &thorn;ese names ben not propirli take of alle auctouris / But oon|herof is taken for ano&thorn;er ofte tyme / But for to seie &thorn;e so&thorn;e, a|medicyn &thorn;at is clepid aggregatum or conglutinatum, &amp; A. in diuers|placis taketh diuersli &thorn;ese names of medicyns: &amp; I suppose &thorn;at it|were for defaute of men &thorn;at translatid &thorn;e science / But for to seie|&thorn;e so&thorn;e, aggregatiua or consolidatiua is a drie medicyne, &amp; ha&thorn;|gummosite in him; &amp; whanne it is leid to &thorn;e lyme, it wole resolue|wi&thorn; his drienes.  It drie&thorn; vp superfluite of moistnes &thorn;at is bitwixe|&thorn;e lippis of a wounde, wi&thorn; a litil ligature or sewing it soudi&thorn;|togidere.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Add. 26,106, fol. 105: "superfluam siccat humiditatem que inter duo|vulneris labia, per medicum ligatura sola vel sutura conducta, reperitur."</NOTE>  &amp; A. clepi&thorn; &thorn;is incarnatiuam, &amp; summen clepen it consolidatiuam,|&amp; ben &thorn;ese / Sanguis draconis, calx, thus masculinum
<PB N="343">|folia pirorum, pomorum, porri, lilij cortices, palme,<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>pullme</I>.</NOTE> arnaglossa,|caulis, folia cipressi, folia vitis <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="256b">albe, nux recens, folia acetose, |puluis molendini, ordeum vstum, flos sorbe, lac acetosum, &amp; o&thorn;ere|manie &thorn;at ben vnknowen for us / Sumtyme men maden grete|woundis &amp; leiden &thorn;ervpon manie herbis, &amp; weren hool in &thorn;e same|dai; &amp; &thorn;ei camen for to take of &thorn;e same herbis, &amp; ne mi&yogh;ten noon|fynde &thorn;at wolde do so more / A good medicyn for &thorn;is entencioun:|&rx;, frankencense partem vnam, sanguis draconis partes duas, calcis|viue partes tres, &amp; make herof poudre; &amp; leie ynow&yogh; vpon &thorn;e .ij.|lippis of &thorn;e wounde &thorn;at is sewid togidere, as it is aforseid in &thorn;e|chapitre of woundis.  &para; Ano&thorn;er poudre &thorn;at is good for &thorn;is entencioun;|but in placis &thorn;at is myche fleisch aweie, it is nede for to|leie &thorn;erto &thorn;ingis to regendre fleisch, &thorn;at we wolli&thorn; speke &thorn;erof soone|heraftir.  &rx;, olibani lucidi, aloes, sanguis draconis ana, make &thorn;erof|poudre.  &para; Ano&thorn;er comoun for to streyne blood, &amp; for to soude|woundis: &rx;, sarcocolle partes duas, sanguis draconis, balaustie ana|partem vnum,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sic</I>.</NOTE> olibani lucidi partem <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, &amp; make herof poudre.</P>
<P>&para; Medicyns forto regendre fleisch haue&thorn; propriete forto congile|blood, &thorn;at come&thorn; to &thorn;e place wi&thorn; tempere drienes, &amp; maki&thorn; &thorn;erof|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="257a">fleisch, &amp; maki&thorn; clene superfluite &thorn;at wexi&thorn; &thorn;eron.  &amp; &thorn;is is in |diuers maner / ffor whi, if a lyme be woundid in &thorn;at maner &thorn;at it|be nede for to regendre fleisch &thorn;eron, &amp; &thorn;e place is drie, &amp; &thorn;er is|miche quitture in &thorn;e wounde, &thorn;an it is nede &thorn;at &thorn;ou haue swi&thorn;e|drijng medicyns.  &para; If &thorn;at he haue litil quitture &amp; his bodi be|moist, &mdash; &mdash; alle &thorn;ese techingis &thorn;ou hast had tofore.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: si vero pauca fuerit sanies, &amp; membrum &amp; corpus fuerint humida,|medicina tunc indiges minus sicca, sicut superius habuisti.</NOTE>  &para; Medicyns|&thorn;at ben li&yogh;t &thorn;at &thorn;ou schalt vse &thorn;ere, &thorn;at &thorn;er is litil quitture yn|moist bodies: &rx;, thus minutum, mastix, farina ordei, fenigreci.|And &thorn;ese be&thorn; sumwhat more drier: aristologie, yreos, &amp; orobum,|aloes, mirra, pix greca, farina fabarum; &amp; more strong &thorn;at &thorn;ou|schalt vse in bodies: astrologia, yreos, farina lupinorum, dragantum|adustum, vitriolum adustum; for if it be brent it wole be &thorn;e lasse|bityng, &amp; his drienes ne schal not be alaskid.  &para; For .vij. causis|diuers &thorn;ingis ben brent: Summe ben brent, for sum vertu in hem|schulde wexe / And summe &thorn;at &thorn;e malice &thorn;erof schulde goon awei:|as mirabolani, &thorn;at haue&thorn; vertu of laxatif, &amp; virtutem stipticam, for|whanne it is brent his vertu laxatif is maad lasse; &amp; his vertu &thorn;at|is clepid stiptica, is neuer &thorn;e lasse, but it is &thorn;e more.  In &thorn;e same
<PB N="344">| maner <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="257b">vitriolum lesi&thorn; his scharpnes, &amp; his drienes is not lost /|The .ij. is &thorn;is, &thorn;at his greet substaunce mowe be maad sutil, as|cancri id est crabbis &thorn;at ben brent / The .iij. cause is &thorn;is, &thorn;at it mowe|gadere scharpnes, as stoonys, oistris, &amp; schellis of eiren, &thorn;at ben|brent &thorn;at me mai make lyme of hem / The .iiij. is, &thorn;at it mowe be|aparailid for to be grounden, as seta sericum<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: sicut seta aut sericum.</NOTE> / &amp; among alle|medicyns &thorn;at ben for &thorn;e herte &thorn;at mowe be grounde, ben &thorn;e beste|as gold &amp; siluir<NOTE PLACE="foot">Add. 26,106, fol. 105, bk.: quod inter medicinas cordiales fit, quod assatur|ut teri possit, et aurum &amp; argentum, que decoquuntur cum sulphure ...</NOTE> / In &thorn;is maner &thorn;ou schalt di&yogh;te hem for to grinde /|Se&thorn;e hem in sulfur in leed, &thorn;at &thorn;ei mowe &thorn;e bettir be grounde /|The .v. cause is &thorn;is, &thorn;at &thorn;e wickidnes &thorn;erof mowe be take awei:|as of scorpiouns &thorn;at ben brent, &thorn;at we mowe vse hem in medicyns,|&thorn;at ben for &thorn;e stoon.  The .vj. cause is &thorn;is, &thorn;at his vertu mowe be|maad &thorn;e more, as squillis whanne &thorn;ei ben brent, her vertu wole be|&thorn;e more / The .vij. cause is &thorn;is, &thorn;at his vertu mowe be take fro|him: as psillium, whanne it is brent / his vertu wole be &thorn;e lasse //|In what maner &thorn;ou schalt go fro medicyn to medicyn, &thorn;ou hast it| pleynerli ynow&yogh; in &thorn;e first tretis, <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="258a">bo&thorn;e simple medicyns &amp; also|compound / &thorn;e whiche &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t vse as &thorn;ou seest best to done / If|&thorn;ou wolt regendre fleisch in a deep put &thorn;at vlcus is, take poudre|of thuris, whanne vlcus is<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>is</I>, above line.</NOTE> maad clene, &amp; fille ful &thorn;e hole &thorn;erof, for|it wole engendre fleisch wel.  &para; In &thorn;es vertues, &amp; it is moost|competent to consolidatif medicyns.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.; Et nota quod de thure tria sunt, sive cortex, &amp; illud est siccius|omnibus, &amp; convenit plus in consolidatiuis medicinis facientibus pellem &amp;|cicatrizantibus, quas ita habebis.</NOTE> &amp; his gummosite &thorn;at is clepid|thus masculinum ou&thorn;er olibanum, &amp; &thorn;at is best for medicyns &thorn;at is|conglutinatif, &thorn;at ben forseid in &thorn;e bigynnyng of &thorn;is chapitre.  &amp;|&thorn;e poudre of him, whanne it is maad smal &amp; falli&thorn; adoun of a|sarce, is clepid minutum thuris, &amp; &thorn;at is best to regendre fleisch.</P>
<P>Bi &thorn;is maner distinccioun &thorn;ou schalt gadere &thorn;e difference of &thorn;re|medicyns &thorn;at ben in &thorn;is chapitre, &amp; of summen &thorn;ei ben clepid alle|[consolidatiues].  &para; The .j. &thorn;erof &thorn;at is seid conglutinatif, &thorn;at|maki&thorn; &thorn;e lippis of a wounde soude togidere / The .ij. it drie&thorn; &amp;|maki&thorn; clene, &amp; helpi&thorn; blood for to turne into fleisch / The .iij. it|drie&thorn; wi&thorn; vertu &thorn;at is clepid stiptica, &thorn;at maki&thorn; hard fleisch to|arise in &thorn;e stide of skyn.  &para; This is a good medicyn for to regendre| fleisch, &thorn;at is clepid litargirum nutritum, &thorn;at is norischid <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="258b">as it is
<PB N="345">|aforseid in &thorn;e chapitre de vlceribus.  &para; Ano&thorn;er poudre &thorn;at engendri&thorn;|fleisch / Take thuris minute, masticis, fenigreci ana, fiat|puluis.  &THORN;is poudre regendri&thorn; fleisch wel &amp; drawi&thorn;, &amp; nyle not|suffre &thorn;at vlcus schal stynke, but it maki&thorn; for to haue a good|sauour.  &para; Also an oynement &thorn;at is good for to regendre fleisch /|&rx;, litargiri nutriti <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .ij, puluis thuris, sarcocolle, galbani, colofonie,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>colofonie</I>, see <I>Alphita</I>, p. 42.</NOTE>|ana <ABBR EXPAN="[dram]">&yogh;</ABBR> .j, medle hem alle togidere, &amp; make &thorn;erof an oynement.|&para; Ano&thorn;er poudre, &rx;, radicem malui visci, &thorn;at summen clepen<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>clepen</I>, above line.</NOTE>|sanaticlam,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>sanaticla</I>.  See Wr. W&uuml;l., 554, 8: "Saniculum, i. sanicle, i. wudemerch."|<I>Minsheu</I> quotes the following proverb: "Celuy qui sanicle a, de|Mire affaire il n'a.  Et qui a du bugle &amp; du sanicle, fait au chirurgien la|nique.  He that hath Sanicle, respects not the Poticarie, and he that hath|Sanicle and Cumfrie, makes a iest of the Surgeon."</NOTE> &amp; sumen clepi&thorn; it vngaria; &amp; waische it &amp; drie it in a|furneis in sich maner &thorn;at &thorn;ou ne brenne it not.  &amp; &thorn;an grinde it &amp;|make &thorn;erof poudre, &amp; leie &thorn;erof a good quantite in vlceribus &thorn;at|ben holow / for off his owne propriete it engendri&thorn; fleisch, bo&thorn;e|bi him-silf &amp; also whanne it is medlid wi&thorn; o&thorn;ere &thorn;ingis / Also|take of &thorn;e forseid poudre <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .j, of thus &thorn;at be smal <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, vernicis,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Halle, <I>Table</I>, p. 134: "Out of the Iuniper tree sweateth certeine teares,|in the spring tyme chiefly and therefore called <I>Vernix</I>, quasi Vernus ros."</NOTE>|aloes, sarcocolle, masticis, fenigreci ana <ABBR EXPAN="[dram]">&yogh;</ABBR> .ij, medle hem wi&thorn; &thorn;e|&thorn;ingis aforseid, &amp; &thorn;ou mi&yogh;t make &thorn;erof an oynement wi&thorn; oile &amp;|wex; &amp; do <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j. of &thorn;e poudre in <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .iiij. of oile, &amp; <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>
<ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>. of wex.|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="259a">And &thorn;is &thorn;ou schalt knowe, &thorn;at &thorn;ere &thorn;ou puttist poudris, &thorn;ou |schalt putte none oynementis for to regendre fleisch / But whanne|poudre ne mai not come &thorn;erto to &thorn;e botme &thorn;erof, &thorn;an &thorn;ou muste|leie &thorn;eron oynementis, for &thorn;e moisture of &thorn;e oile maki&thorn; &thorn;e poudre|peerse to &thorn;e botme.  &para; Also &thorn;is oynement is good, for it drawi&thorn;|out quitture / &rx;, olij l&imacr;. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, resine <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .j, cere <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .<ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, minute thuris,|fenigreci ana <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .<ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, make herof an oynement &amp; cole it.  &para; Also|ano&thorn;er oynement &thorn;at is good for &thorn;is entencioun.  &rx;, consolide|maioris &amp; minoris, cinoglosse, pilocelle,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat. pilosella.  See Wr. W&uuml;l., p. 556, 18.</NOTE> plantaginis maioris &amp; minoris,|ana. <ABBR EXPAN="[handful]"><GAP></ABBR> .j, vermes terrestres longos, qui dicuntur lumbrici,|l&imacr;. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>; kutte alle &thorn;es smale,<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>&thorn;esmale</I>.</NOTE> &amp; leie hem in l&imacr;. j &amp; <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>. of oile of oliue,|&amp; lete hem ligge &thorn;ere .viij. daies, &amp; &thorn;an boile hem a litil &amp; &thorn;an cole|hem, &amp; do &thorn;erto schepis talow maad clene id est molten &amp; colid,|picis naualis l&imacr;. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, picis grece <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .iiij, armoniaci, galbanum, opoponaci,|terbentine, masticis communis minuti, ana <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>.  In &thorn;is maner
