at ben|engendrid oonli of sperme, &amp; &thorn;ei be kutt awei, &thorn;ei schulen neuere|wexe a&yogh;en / And alle &thorn;ese &thorn;ingis in a man ben engendrid oonli of|sperme, as a mannes skyn, &amp; boonys &amp; senewis; &amp; &thorn;erfor &amp; &thorn;er be|ony gobet kutt awei of &thorn;ese, &thorn;ei ne mowe neuere be regendrid|a&yogh;en, as .A. sei&thorn;, &amp; it is soo&thorn; / But in &thorn;is caas medicynes mowe|helpe for to engendre hard fleisch aboue, &amp; schal be in &thorn;e place of|skyn, vpon which place nyle neuer wexe here afterward<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: "medicina ista namque adiuuat, vt naseatur caro calosa dura,|que est loco cutis, super quam non nascitur pilus."</NOTE> / &para; Simple|medicyns &thorn;at ben in &thorn;is caas makyng skyn vpon a soor &thorn;at is|clene / Cortices arboris, pini, cortices thuris, centaurea combusta,|ossa combusta, abrotanum combustum, balaustie, galle, cipressi,|psidie, cucurma, rubea maioris combusta, lumbrici terestris adusti,|cathinia argenti &amp; auri, alumen sissum, folia fici, stercus canis|comedentis ossa siccatum,<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>sucatum</I>.</NOTE> aristologia longa &amp; rotunda combuste, es| vstum lauatum, &amp; ius medicina<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: "et omnis (abbr. <I>o&imacr;s</I>) medicina, que fit in duabus actiuis propter|temperamentum."</NOTE> / <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="260b">Sumtyme we medlide medicyns
