<DIV3 TYPE="chapter" N="7">
<HEAD>Of mollificatif medicyns or softenyng.</HEAD>
<P>We vsi&thorn; &thorn;ese medicyns &thorn;at ben .iiij. in eueri cause.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Lat.: Mollificatiuis vtimur medicinis in quatuor casibus.</NOTE>  Oon cause|is &thorn;is, whanne &thorn;e mater &thorn;at &thorn;ou wolt resolue is swi&thorn;e hard,|for &thorn;an oonli wi&thorn; resolutiuis as it is aforseid &thorn;e sotil mater wole|resolue, &amp; &thorn;at o&thorn;ir part wole bicome hard, &amp; &thorn;an &thorn;ou muste make|mollificatiuis.  &para; The .ij. cause is &thorn;is, whanne ony lyme is to-broke|ou&thorn;ir out of &thorn;e ioyncte, &thorn;ou&yogh; it be bro&yogh;t <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="267b">yn a&yogh;en, &thorn;e place wole be |hard, &amp; &thorn;e patient mai not meue &thorn;erwi&thorn;, &thorn;an &thorn;ou muste do<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>do</I>, above line.</NOTE> &thorn;erto|mollificatiuis til &thorn;e lyme be bettere as it is aforseid.  &para; The .iij.|cause is &thorn;is, whanne ony lyme &thorn;at ha&thorn; ben out of ioynct longe|tyme, &thorn;an &thorn;ou muste make &thorn;ingis forto make &thorn;e place moist a&yogh;en,|&thorn;at &thorn;e boon mowe come into his ioynt a&yogh;en.  &para; The .iiij. cause is,|whanne a lyme is corrupt &amp; is yuel ioyned, &amp; maki&thorn; al &thorn;e lyme foul,|as whanne a boon is to-broken &amp; is not ioyned, &thorn;an &thorn;ou muste breke|&thorn;e boon a&yogh;en, &amp; bringe it into his propre place as it schulde be /|In alle &thorn;ese causis we mote vse medicyns &thorn;at ben mollificatiuis, as|ben &thorn;ese: camomille, mellilotum, fenigreci, semen lini, &amp; almaner|fatnes, &amp; marowe, &amp; manie gummis, &amp; euery medicyn &thorn;at is hoot|&amp; moist wole make a lyme mollificatif / A good composicioun for|&thorn;e firste cause / Take oold oile .iiij. partis, wex partem .j., &amp; make|&thorn;erof an oynement, and anoynte &thorn;erwi&thorn; a lyme &thorn;at &thorn;ou wolt resolue|&thorn;e mater &thorn;at is &thorn;eron / ffor it wole make &thorn;e mater mollificatif, &amp;|make &thorn;e poris <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="268a">open to resolucioun // Ano&thorn;er &thorn;at is more strong / |&rx;, radicis malua visci <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .j., &amp; kutte it to smale gobetis, &amp; putte|hem in a morter wi&thorn; <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .iiij. of oile of lilie. &amp; &thorn;ou schalt sett &thorn;is|vessel of glas in hoot boilyng watir, &amp; &thorn;ere it schal stonde til &thorn;e|iuys of &thorn;e herbe be consumed.  Wi&thorn; &thorn;is oile &thorn;ou schalt anoynte &thorn;e|place, &amp; leie &thorn;ervpon lanam succidam id est wolle vnwaischen.  &amp; &thorn;is
