<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="6">
<HEAD>&para; The sixte Chapitle of &thorn;e &thorn;ridde techynge is of|Woundes &thorn;at han enpostemes, &amp; be&thorn; dystempryde.</HEAD>
<P>A wounde &thorn;at hath aposteme o&thorn;er an yuel discrasie&mdash;&thorn;at is to|sigge, out of kynde distempride, o&thorn;ere to hote o&thorn;ere to cold, he may|no&yogh;t ben helyd, ne schal nou&yogh;t ben heled, but first &thorn;e posteme be|aswagyde, &amp; &thorn;e yuele discrasie be amendide.  &amp; as y haue seyde, in|an o&thorn;ere place, yt is profitable to &thorn;e syke man, &amp; worschipful to &thorn;e|leche, &yogh;if &thorn;at he mowe dyffende &thorn;e lymes &thorn;at be&thorn; woundyde fro eny|postemys, &amp; fro an euyll discrasie.  For &thorn;enne a leche schal kepe|&thorn;e canon of galyen, &thorn;at is on of foure canones; on is to kepyn|lymes in here owne kendlye complexioun.  For woundys mowe|no&yogh;t ellys ben y-helyd, but &yogh;if &thorn;ey ben brou&yogh;t first to here owne|kynde, &amp; &thorn;e wounde may be kepte from aposteme &amp; an yuell|discrasie, &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;e leche be kunnynge &amp; do hys deffere, &amp; &thorn;e syke| man be obedyent to &thorn;e leche.  &THORN;e leche mot loke <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="52a">&yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;ere haue|go blod ynow&yogh; out of &thorn;e wounde; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;at the wounde haue no&yogh;t|bled blod ynow&yogh;, &thorn;e pacyent most ben lete blod, o&thorn;ere ellys ben
<PB N="55">|ventusyde, takynge rewarde to alle partikelere &thorn;ynges tofore seyde,|&amp; ordeyne hym a couenable dyotynge, as schal be tolde in &thorn;e|Chapitell of dyotynge; &amp; leye a defens aboute &thorn;e wounde: <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> j of|bol Armonyake, distemperid wi&thorn; oyle of rosys &amp; a lytel vynegre, to|&thorn;e &thorn;iknesse of hony; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;e tyme of &thorn;e &yogh;ere were hot, put to|&thorn;is medycine &thorn;e jus of sum colde erbe: as morel, ny&yogh;tschode, penywort,|virge pastoris, o&thorn;ere sum o&thorn;er colde erbe; &amp; bynde no&yogh;t &thorn;e|lyme to harde, ne lete no&yogh;t &thorn;e lyme hongyn; but &yogh;if it be &thorn;e arme,|honge him aboute &thorn;e nekke; &amp; &yogh;if it be &thorn;e fot o&thorn;er &thorn;e schyne, lete|hym ligge; &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;e lyme ak&thorn;e, aswage &thorn;e ak&thorn;e wi&thorn;|anoyntynge|of hote oyle of roses.  Ffor as Galyen seyth: &thorn;ere is no&thorn;ynge more|grefes, &thorn;an ys akynge &amp; declynacioun of a lyme, for &thorn;ese two maki&thorn;|sone an hote swellynge, the whiche is to &thorn;e ffeuyre as a welle, &amp; to|&thorn;e body as an Ovyn.  &THORN;e woundyde man most absteynen hym,|aftere &thorn;at &thorn;e chapitell of dyetynge techith; &amp; bo&thorn;e &thorn;e syke man &amp;|&thorn;e leche, &amp; alle &thorn;at ben aboute &thorn;e syke, mote absteynen hem from|fleschlye knowlachynge of a womman, ne a womman *in tyme of|menstrewe, ne loke no&yogh;t on &thorn;e syke man; &amp; onys in &thorn;e day &thorn;e syke|man schal schyte, &amp; &yogh;if he may no&yogh;t schyte kendly onys in &thorn;e day,
<PB N="56">|after &thorn;e quantyte of mete &thorn;at he ha&thorn; takyn, make hym a clistry, o&thorn;er|a suppositorye onys iche day.  &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;ou maiste no&yogh;t with alle &thorn;ese|&thorn;ynges defendyn &thorn;e lyme from aposteme, yt is an yuele signe, for &thorn;e|lyme ys feble, &amp; &thorn;e humores ben wykkede; &thorn;en begynne to maturen|&thorn;e swellynge, with potage y-made off flour, oyle &amp; water, o&thorn;er ellys|with &thorn;is maturatyff: &rx; malwe leuys, leffys of vyolett, &amp; &thorn;e rote| of holy hokke; se&thorn;e hem <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="52b">wel in water, &amp; &thorn;anne stampe hem, &amp;|take a pounde off &thorn;e water &thorn;at &thorn;ey be sodyn yn, &amp; of comyn oyle
<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iij, of whete flour <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iij, of flour of lynsed .<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR>. j, of flore vynegreke
<ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, of erbys i-stamped <ABBR EXPAN="[pound]">lb</ABBR>.<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. lj</NOTE> <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>; &amp; boylle alle &thorn;ese togedire, in a pan|ouere &thorn;e fyre, &amp; stire yt wel wi&thorn; a spator; &amp; &thorn;is maturatyff leye|on a lynne cloth, &amp; leye on &thorn;e posteme, tyl &thorn;at yt be maturyd; &amp;|whanne &thorn;at &thorn;e posteme is matured, make &thorn;e quyter, &yogh;if &thorn;ou maist,|ben y-cast to &thorn;e wounde; &amp; &yogh;if it may no&yogh;t ben y-cast to &thorn;e wounde,|opyne &thorn;e place &thorn;at ys most lowest &thorn;ere, as &thorn;e quyter may best gone|out; &amp; &thorn;an helyn &thorn;e wounde, as y schal tellyn, in &thorn;e &thorn;ridde|chapytell of Apostemys.  Take hede alweye to &thorn;is techynge, &thorn;at|&yogh;if a posteme were for &thorn;e prikynge of a synwe, ne leye no&yogh;t &thorn;ereto|&thorn;is potage maturatyff, but wyt &thorn;e vncture of oyle of roses &amp; of|o&thorn;er &thorn;ynge, as yt is seyde in &thorn;e woundys of synwys.  &THORN;ou schalt
<PB N="57">|y-knowe &thorn;e euyll dyscrasie of a wounde, &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;ou sest the schyn|&thorn;at is aboute &thorn;e wounde to reed, &amp; to hot in felynge, &thorn;enne &thorn;e|wounde is discrasyede in hete, namly &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;ere come out of &thorn;e|wounde a sotyll qyter &amp; a red; &amp; &thorn;ilke discrasye &thorn;ou schalt helpen|with coldynge &thorn;e lyme aboute &thorn;e wounde, with oyle of roses, &amp; with|vnguentum album&mdash;rasis of ceruse&mdash;whyche &thorn;ou schalt fynde in &thorn;e|Antodarie, &amp; wi&thorn; ius of o&thorn;ere colde erbys.  &amp; &thorn;ou schalt knowe a|colde discrasye by &thorn;e whitnesse o&thorn;er &thorn;e wannesse of &thorn;e place, &amp;|whanne &thorn;e place ys colde in touchynge, &amp; whanne &thorn;at &thorn;e quyter is|thykke; the whiche discrasye &thorn;ou schalt remeffen, by &thorn;e vncture of|hote oyles, as oyle of cost, oyle lauryne, oyle of enforbium, &amp; so|o&thorn;er hote oyles.  A moiste discrasie &thorn;ou schalt knowe by &thorn;e|nesschenesse of &thorn;e place, &amp; by &thorn;e Abundaunce of whit lyquyde|rotnesse, &thorn;e whiche &thorn;ou schalt helpyn with defficatyffes: as with|wasschynge of wyn &amp; honye togedres, in <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="53a">&thorn;e whiche bu&thorn; y-sode |balaustye, gallys, &amp; &thorn;e ryndes off poume garnettys, o&thorn;er alle o&thorn;er|some by hem-selffen.  &THORN;e drye dyscrasye &thorn;ou schalt knowe by &thorn;e|smalnesse of &thorn;e lyme, &amp; &thorn;e smalnesse of &thorn;e lippes of &thorn;e woundes &amp;|litel quyter, &yogh;if &thorn;at the quyter be &thorn;enne; &thorn;e whiche discrasye &thorn;ou
<PB N="58">|schalt helpen wi&thorn; castynge on of hote water, tyl &thorn;at &thorn;e lyme wexe|rede, &amp; with an oyntynge of moiste grecys, as hennys, gosys &amp;|dokys, &amp; &thorn;e marye bon of a Calff, &amp; with plentefoste of gode mete,|&thorn;at norysschyth, as &thorn;e brothys of flesch, &amp; temperat wyn, &amp; rere|eyren, &amp; smale fyssches, &amp; o&thorn;ere gode &thorn;ynges, &amp; with reste and with|softnesse of alle &thorn;e body &amp; of &thorn;e lyme &thorn;at is y-hurte; &amp; alwey to|&thorn;is techynge take hede, &thorn;at as sone as a membre ys y-bro&yogh;t to his|kendlye dysposicioun, anon a&yogh;eyne stonde with contraryouse medycine,|&amp; turne a&yogh;eyne to &thorn;e pryncipal cure of &thorn;e wounde.  But &thorn;ynke|no&yogh;t to helyn &thorn;e wounde, as longe as &thorn;e wounde ys apostomyde,|o&thorn;ere ellys ha&thorn; an yuele discrasye, but first remywe &thorn;ilke discrasye|ere &thorn;an &thorn;ou hele &thorn;e wounde.  For whenne &thorn;at tweye &thorn;ynges &thorn;at|scholde ben y-helyde, bu&thorn; togedres, &amp; &thorn;e on of hem mowe no&yogh;t ben|y-helyde withouten helynge of &thorn;e o&thorn;er, ffirst we schulle helyn hym,|&thorn;at may no&yogh;t be helyde withouten helynge of &thorn;e o&thorn;ere, as &thorn;e|posteme o&thorn;er &thorn;e dyscrasye; &amp; &thorn;us Avycene techith in &thorn;e last|chapitell of &thorn;e first bokys.  Ne nevere &thorn;e latere ne for&yogh;ete no&yogh;t &thorn;y|pryncipal cure, &thorn;at whanne the accidentes ben asesyde, turne a&yogh;eyne|to &thorn;e princypale cure.
</P>

