<DIV4 TYPE="chapter" N="12">
<HEAD>&para; Cap. xii of &thorn;e &thorn;ridde techynge of &thorn;e firste tretis is|of a<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>of a</I>, above line.</NOTE> festre.</HEAD>
<P>ffestre<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>ffirste</I>.</NOTE> is a depe olde wounde and<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>in</I>, cancelled; <I>and</I>, above line.</NOTE> &thorn;e mouth is streyt of hym &amp;|&thorn;e grounde is brod, &amp; he ha&thorn; wi&thorn; ynne hym a callose hardnesse alle|aboute, as yt were a gose penne o&thorn;er ellys a kane, &amp; a ffestre ha&thorn;|<MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="63b">diffence from a depe Vlcus &amp; a cauernose; for a depe Vlcus &amp; a |Cauernose, of whom yt ys tolde in &thorn;e chapitle toforeseyde, &thorn;ow&yogh;|&thorn;at &thorn;ey acorden togedire in depnesse &amp; in streytnesse of &thorn;e mou&thorn;,|&thorn;e Vlcus ha&thorn; no&yogh;t wi&thorn;yn hym a callose hardnesse, wherefore a|festre may no&yogh;t be clensyde with wasschynges, with &thorn;e whiche a<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a</I>, above line.</NOTE>|cavernose Vlcus may be clansyde, but it is necessarye, aftere &thorn;at
<PB N="90">|&thorn;ou hast y-wasschyde yt, to remeffyn &thorn;ilke callose hardnesse with a|cauterye, o&thorn;ere wi&thorn; a medycine cauterysynge &thorn;at ys brennynge, &thorn;e|whiche cauterye o&thorn;er brennynge scholde make &thorn;e dep&thorn;e of &thorn;e Vlcus|holwere &thorn;anne he was.  Wherefore it is necessarie to a surgiene to|knowe &thorn;e difference of &thorn;is scyence, &thorn;at he mowe conne hele bo&thorn;e &thorn;e|Vlcus &amp; &thorn;e festre with medycines different &thorn;at longyth to hem bo&thorn;e.|And &yogh;if &thorn;at a festre be in &thorn;e flesch, o&thorn;er ellys bytwene synwe &amp;|synwe, so &thorn;at &thorn;e Substaunce of &thorn;e synwe be no&yogh;t corupte ne &thorn;e bon,|yt nys non nede to take non o&thorn;ere medycine but egremoyne, &amp;|stampe hym wi&thorn; salt, as &thorn;ou woldest maken sause, &amp; drawe out &thorn;e|jus of &thorn;ilke egremoyne, &amp; do yt into &thorn;e hole of &thorn;e festre with a|penne, &amp; leye &thorn;e substaunce of &thorn;e same erbe &thorn;ere-vpon, tyl he haue|slaw<NOTE PLACE="foot">At the end of the line.  One letter wanting.</NOTE> alle &thorn;ilke festre &amp; y-clansyde yt; &amp; &thorn;at &thorn;ou schalt knowen|by &thorn;e rednesse &amp; sadnesse of flesch &thorn;at is withynne &thorn;e festre al|aboute, &amp; aftirwarde haue &thorn;is surype off honye, with &thorn;e whiche|&thorn;ou schalt wassche &thorn;e festre, &thorn;at ys now Vlcus componed, in &thorn;is|manere:<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Confection of syrup mellyne</I>, in margin.</NOTE> &rx; water <ABBR EXPAN="[pound]">li</ABBR> .j., of vynegre <ABBR EXPAN="[pound]">li</ABBR>. <ABBR EXPAN="[one half]">ss</ABBR>, of hony despumed <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> iiij,|off leuys of olyue-tre, y-bounde togedre with a &thorn;rede, <ABBR EXPAN="[dram]">&yogh;</ABBR> .j., of| <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="64a">sagytelle <ABBR EXPAN="[ounce]"><GAP></ABBR> .j., boylle al &thorn;is to &thorn;e perfytnesse of a sirupe, &amp; let yt
<PB N="91">|coldyn &amp; do aweye &thorn;e leffys of &thorn;e olyfe, &amp; kepe alle &thorn;e remnaunt of|&thorn;e surype with &thorn;e leffys of sagytelle, &amp; wassche &thorn;e Vlcus &thorn;at was|festre tofore with &thorn;is licoure twyes a day, &thorn;at &thorn;e lycoure may go to|&thorn;e grounde, &amp; afterwarde dreye it wel &amp; fyl yt ful of drye leffys of|sagytelle, &amp; leye a sagitelle leff aboue, and &thorn;is medycine &thorn;ou schalt|conteynen tyl &thorn;at it be hol.  Every festre &thorn;at is in flesch ys helyde|with &thorn;is medycine y-prefed, but &yogh;if &thorn;e substaunce of &thorn;e synwe &amp; of|&thorn;e bon be apeyred in &thorn;e grounde, &amp; specialyche &yogh;if &thorn;e festre be|nou&yogh;t old &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;e callosite be no&yogh;t to hard.  In &thorn;ese tweye|cases &thorn;e medycyne of egremoyne ne suffise&thorn; no&yogh;t, but it ys necessarye|a kauterye of fyre o&thorn;er a medycine caustyke; &amp; of &thorn;ese medycins|&thorn;ou schalt han a ful techynge, folwynge in &thorn;e boke.  And &yogh;if|&thorn;at &thorn;e bon were corupte in &thorn;e dep&thorn;e of &thorn;e festre, do yt aweye after|&thorn;e techynge, &thorn;at y haue tau&yogh;te &thorn;e in &thorn;e chapitell tofore.  And|hereof take hede: &yogh;if &thorn;at a festere perse be &thorn;e wey&yogh;es of &thorn;e vryne,|so &thorn;at &thorn;e Vryne go out by &thorn;ilke weye, as we haue seyne ofte tymes,|o&thorn;er ellys &thorn;at he go by crokyde placys and hudel<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>hudel</I>, adj.  See M&auml;tzner, <I>Dict</I>., hudels, sb.  O.E. <I>h&ymacr;dels</I>, hiding-place.</NOTE> places of &thorn;e face,|persynge into &thorn;e depnesse of &thorn;e hed whose grounde &thorn;ou maiste no&yogh;t|perseyue, hit ys bettyre no&yogh;t for to cure with a perfyte cure, but &thorn;ou|maiste pale it &amp; don awey &thorn;e stynke, with hony &amp; wasschynges of|emplastre in mundificatyfes &amp; with defensifes aboute &thorn;e place, &thorn;at
<PB N="92">|his malyce mowe &thorn;e lasse greff.  A festre &thorn;at is in juncturys as|&thorn;e fote o&thorn;er &thorn;e kne, o&thorn;er &thorn;e hand, o&thorn;ere &thorn;e elbowe, is hard forto|hele &amp; sumtyme vnpossible.  And &yogh;if &thorn;at he be in an o&thorn;ere place|&amp; he haue coroded o&thorn;er rotyd sumwhat of &thorn;e synwe, &thorn;ow&yogh; &thorn;at it be|greffes forto cure it, &thorn;ere nys none o&thorn;ere weye bote a ly&yogh;t cauterys-acioun|of &thorn;e synwe, &thorn;at is y-hurt: ffor cauterysacioun wi&thorn; hote| yren, o&thorn;er wi&thorn; gold &thorn;at is betyre clansyth &amp; drye&thorn; <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="64b">&thorn;e synwe &thorn;at|ys corupte, &amp; rectefyeth &thorn;e complexioun of al &thorn;e membre, and a|medycine caustyke worche&thorn; &thorn;e contrarye.  Brennynge medycines,|bo&thorn;e symple &amp; componed, &thorn;ou schalt han to &thorn;e fulle in &thorn;e antitodarye|of &thorn;is boke, &amp; &thorn;ou schalt fynde &thorn;e manere of cauterysinge to|&thorn;e fulle in &thorn;e &thorn;ridde tretys folwynge; &amp; whanne &thorn;ou hast made a|perfyte mundyficacioun of &thorn;ilke callose flesch, regenere flesch &amp; consoude|with medycines regeneratyfes &amp; consolidatyfes, &thorn;e whyche &thorn;ou|schalte fynde in &thorn;e antitodarye.</P>
