<P>Also &thorn;e brayn ys departyde into &thorn;re celules with &thorn;e additamentes|of &thorn;e pannycles of pie<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>pie</I>, twice.</NOTE> matris, &thorn;at &thorn;e spirites my&yogh;t &thorn;e|lengore dwellen in &thorn;e ventricles, to reseyfen by ordre, digestioun,|forme &amp; perfeccion, more &thorn;anne &thorn;ey hadden fyrst of &thorn;e hert, and|&thorn;at euery vertue myghte fulfylle hys accioun in hys ventrycle, ere
<PB N="116">|&thorn;anne &thorn;e foys &thorn;at ys comprehendyde myghte passe to &thorn;e ventricle|&thorn;at ys sywynge.  Now&yogh;t a&yogh;eynestondynge &thorn;ese propretes, &thorn;e brayn|ha&thorn; sum substaunce of marie whiche fulfille&thorn; &thorn;e voydenesses of &thorn;e|forseyde pannycleres.  And &thorn;ilke marye envyrownyth &thorn;e foreseyde|pannycles, of &thorn;e whyche marye &thorn;ere may sum partye in &thorn;e hurtynge|of &thorn;e hed ben y-lost; and no&yogh;t ageynestondynge &thorn;e goynge out of|sum partye of &thorn;ilke marye, a man schal no&yogh;t deye.  Ffor &thorn;is marye|is nought of &thorn;e substaunce of &thorn;e ventricles of &thorn;e brayn, of whiche|mynde ys y-mad; ffor &thorn;ey ben of so grete noblete, &yogh;if &thorn;ere be neuere|so litel infectioun o&thorn;ere ellys &thorn;at &thorn;ere falle neuere so lytel a lesynge|of hem, &thorn;ey ben depreffyde of alle here helthe, in so myche &thorn;at on|celele may no&yogh;t ben y-lost, and a man ben saffyde, as manye|ydyotes supposen.  Anothomye of eynen, neose, erne, chekelappes,|mou&thorn;, tonge &amp; te&thorn;, we deferren to ordeynen in &thorn;e &thorn;ridde tretys, in|&thorn;e distyncioun whiche &yogh;if god wol, we &thorn;ynke&thorn; forto treten of o&thorn;ere|syknesse of &thorn;e lymes, outsepte woundes.  And &thorn;o hurtynges &thorn;at|be&thorn; y-mad in &thorn;e hed, o&thorn;ere &thorn;ey ben mad withouten wounde, o&thorn;ere|with wounde.  &amp; whe&thorn;ere &thorn;at it be wyth wounde o&thorn;ere wi&thorn;outen|wounde, o&thorn;ere &thorn;ey ben with brekynge of &thorn;e brayn panne, o&thorn;ere
<PB N="117">|without brekynge of &thorn;e breyn panne.  And whe&thorn;er <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="72b">&thorn;at yt be mad|wi&thorn; &thorn;e breche of &thorn;e brayn panne o&thorn;ere withouten breche of &thorn;e breyn|panne, some ben with hurtynge of &thorn;e brayn, some without hurtynge |of &thorn;e brayn.  And ry&yogh;te as &thorn;ilke hurtynges habben dyfference in|toknes, so &thorn;ey hauen differens in pereles &amp; pronosticaciouns &amp;|maners, with &thorn;e whiche &thorn;ey most ben y-holpen.  And &yogh;if an hurt be|in &thorn;e hed withouten wounde, as with fallynge, o&thorn;ere with smytinge|of a ston, o&thorn;ere a staff, o&thorn;ere with sum o&thorn;ere thynge &thorn;at brusyth,|and &yogh;if &thorn;at yt be withouten breche of &thorn;e brayn panne, &amp; with outen|hurtynge of &thorn;e brayn panne, it nedyth nou&yogh;t but schaffynge of &thorn;e|hed, &amp; anoyntynge wi&thorn; hote oyle of roses, and abofen &thorn;e vncture*|to strawyn on &thorn;e poudre of &thorn;e seed of myrtylles, &amp; streyne &thorn;e place|with a band tyl al &thorn;e place be y-fastnyde &amp; &thorn;e swellynge be y-vanschyd|aweye.  In &thorn;is manere &thorn;ou schalt fastne al &thorn;e place, &thorn;at|no&thorn;yng schal be corumped, o&thorn;ere ellys &thorn;ere schall dwelle a lytel|corupcioun.  And &yogh;if enye &thorn;ynge of corumpcion abyde, &thorn;e place|schal ben y-opnyde with an Instrument, &amp; so alle &thorn;e quyter schal be|excludyd, &amp; he schal ben y-curyd ry&yogh;t as o&thorn;ere empostemys &thorn;at be&thorn;|y-woundyde.  And &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;e brayn panne were y-broke withoute|enye wounde of &thorn;e hed, &thorn;e whiche may ben y-knowe by dysposicioun|of &thorn;e cause &amp; eke of &thorn;e syke man, in byholdynge &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;at smyt
<PB N="118">|were stronge, o&thorn;ere ellys &thorn;at &thorn;e syke haue y-fallen from hye place,|o&thorn;ere ellys &thorn;at he was y-smyte with stronge smytynge; and also &yogh;if|&thorn;at he fel &amp; myght nought hastlye aryse, and &yogh;if &thorn;at he hadde|scotomye: &thorn;at ys to sugge a manere seknesse, whenne &thorn;at &thorn;ere|semyth as flye&yogh;es, o&thorn;ere smale blake gnattys vley&yogh;en tofore hys|ey&yogh;en, o&thorn;ere ellys he spywe&thorn; hys mete, o&thorn;ere he felyth to grete ak&thorn;e|in hys hed, and &yogh;if &thorn;at he may nought breken a knotte of a straw&yogh;|with hys teth, and &yogh;if &thorn;e hed be smyten with a ly&yogh;t drey&yogh;e staff, as| of salwe o&thorn;ere ellys pyne, and &thorn;enne leye &thorn;yn <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="73a">ere to hys hed; &amp;|&yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;e bon be hol. &thorn;ou schalt heren an hol soun after &thorn;e comparsoun|of &thorn;e soun of an hol belle &amp; a bloke belle; also &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;ou|makyste &thorn;e syke man to holde bytwene hys te&thorn; a &thorn;rede y-twyned|&amp; y-waxed, &amp; &thorn;enne begynne to harpen with &thorn;y naylles vpon &thorn;e|&thorn;rede faste be &thorn;e seke mannes mouth, &amp; so harpe with &thorn;yne naylles|vpon &thorn;e &thorn;red alle wey streyned, in makynge soun to &thorn;e ende of &thorn;e|&thorn;red, &amp; &thorn;ilke &thorn;red schal ben of leng&thorn;e from &thorn;e mouth be &thorn;e space|of a Kubyte; and &thorn;ou schalt harpe so ofte tymes, &amp; &yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;e|pacient mowe susteyne &thorn;e soun, he ha&thorn; no&yogh;t hys brayn panne|y-broke; ffor &yogh;if hys breyn panne were broke, &thorn;e seke man myghte|nought susteyne &thorn;e soun of &thorn;e &thorn;red.  Alle &thorn;ese signes o&thorn;ere ellis|manye of hem betokne &thorn;at &thorn;e breyn panne is broken.  And to &thorn;e
