<PB N="128">|me fro doute, by as myche as y haue assayede longe tyme bo&thorn;e by|sum auctores experyment, &amp; also by myn experyment, &amp; &thorn;at wey|is no&yogh;t certeyn, &thorn;erefore here &thorn;ey Galien, whiche &thorn;at seith: &yogh;if we|mowe romywe quyter without doynge awey bonys &thorn;at scholde be|do awey, hyt is good.  And Auisene &amp; Serapio acorden to &thorn;e same|sentense of cure of hed-ak&thorn;e, &thorn;at comyth off smytinge o&thorn;ere ellys of|fallynge, where &thorn;at he techith &thorn;e worchynge of hurtynges of &thorn;e|brayn panne &amp; of &thorn;e brayn, no&yogh;t by trepanacioun, but by emplastres|&amp; by medycines.  And also y toke gode hede &thorn;at manye mo men|ben y-helyde by manere medycines &amp; emplastres, &thorn;enne ben y-helyde|by trepanes &thorn;at be&thorn; persynge o&thorn;ere &thorn;ryllynge.  Ffor y ne vse no&yogh;t|Instrumentes to remywe &thorn;e bon, but in tweye cases&mdash;&thorn;at on cas ys|&yogh;if &thorn;at &thorn;e breyn panne be so myche y-scleud, &thorn;at &thorn;e part &thorn;at ys|y-broke entre vndire &thorn;e partye &thorn;at ys hol, &thorn;e secunde cas ys &yogh;if &thorn;at|enye pece be departyde from &thorn;e brayn panne, whyche &thorn;at pryketh|duram matrem.  In &thorn;e firste cas dura mater ys compressede.  In &thorn;e|secunde cas dura mater ys y-prikyde, &thorn;e whiche ys cause of ak&thorn;e,|&amp; akynge ys cause of drawynge of humoures, the whiche engendrith|a posteme vpon &thorn;e same pannycle, the whiche is cause of a<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>a</I>, above line.</NOTE> crampe,|&amp; of o&thorn;ere accidentes tofore seyde, &amp; at &thorn;e laste &thorn;ey bryngen de&thorn;
