<HEAD>&para; Capit. iiij. tretis .ij. is of woundes of &thorn;e spaude,|schuldre, arme, handis, ffingres, brawnes, veynes,|and here Anotamye.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e spawde ys one of &thorn;e iiij bonys whiche &thorn;at maki&thorn; &thorn;e forme|of &thorn;e schuldre, &amp; &thorn;e spawde-bon is &thorn;enne &amp; brode towarde &thorn;e|schuldres &amp; in hys endys grustly.  On &thorn;e vppere syde of hym he|ha&thorn; an egge sumwhat gret &amp; towarde &thorn;e arme in &thorn;e place of &thorn;e|schuldre he ys grete &amp; rounde.  And &thorn;ilke ende ys holwe as a box,|and &thorn;is bon ys lyche to a pele, &thorn;e whiche men settyth brede into|&thorn;e ovyne, and on &thorn;e hyndere partye of &thorn;e schuldre he ha&thorn; an|emynense.  &amp; in &thorn;e box of &thorn;is bon &mdash; &mdash;* whiche ys y-clepyde adiutorium|&thorn;e whiche ys a bon sumwhat crokyde, gret &amp; holow&yogh;.  &THORN;is|bon ys gret for necessite of strengthe, &amp; of schappe holwe, &thorn;at he|were ly&yogh;te, &thorn;at he scholde nou&yogh;t &thorn;rowen his hevynesse lette &thorn;e|wirchynge of lacertes, and &thorn;e rounde extremite of &thorn;is bon entre&thorn; into|&thorn;e holwenesse of the spaude.  &amp; &thorn;ey be&thorn; y-bounde togedre with|a bowable ligament.  &THORN;e canel-bon of &thorn;e brest ys in this manere
<PB N="156">|y-made, habbynge an additamente sumwhat <MILESTONE UNIT="folio" N="86b">rounde in &thorn;e ne&thorn;ere|partye, &thorn;e whiche entryth a manere box, &thorn;e whiche ys in &thorn;e offere| partye of &thorn;e ovyre bon of &thorn;e vij. bonys of &thorn;e brest.  And euerye|extremyte of &thorn;ilke vij. bonys be&thorn; y-Ioyned wi&thorn; &thorn;e spawde, &thorn;at &thorn;e|schuldre myghte be &thorn;e more strenger; and forto make &thorn;is place &thorn;e|more strengere, &thorn;ere be&thorn; sette two smale bonys whiche be&thorn; y-clepyde|rostralis to &thorn;e lyknesse of &thorn;e byle of a crowe, &amp; forto fastne &thorn;e|schuldres, &thorn;is bon rostrale ys y-put in &thorn;e manere of a wegge.  But|&thorn;e bon of &thorn;e adiutorie ha&thorn; in &thorn;e ne&thorn;ere partye towarde &thorn;e elbowe|tweye emynences, and &thorn;e on of &thorn;e emynence ys more herre &thorn;enne|&thorn;e othire; and bo&thorn;e &thorn;ese emynence be&thorn; as yt were half a bokett|wi&thorn; &thorn;e whiche men drawi&thorn; water; and &thorn;ilke tweye Additamentis|be&thorn; y-Ioyned with &thorn;e bonys of &thorn;e arme.  &THORN;e Arme from &thorn;e Elbowe|dunwarde, ha&thorn; two bonys, and &thorn;e offere bon whiche &thorn;at strecchi&thorn;|from &thorn;e &thorn;owmbe &thorn;at ys clepyde adiutorium is smallere bon, and &thorn;e|ne&thorn;ere bon &thorn;at strecchith from &thorn;e lytel fyngere to &thorn;e elbowe is &thorn;e|grettere bon.  &amp; he ha&thorn; in &thorn;e offere ende towarde the elbowe an|additament like to a byle o&thorn;ere a pyk, and &thorn;ilke pyk makyth &thorn;e|elbowe scharpe, whenne &thorn;at &thorn;e arme ys y-folden, and it lette&thorn; &thorn;at|&thorn;e arme may no&yogh;t ben y-bowyde bakwarde.*  &THORN;ese tweye bonys be&thorn;
<PB N="157">|so y-Ioynede togedire, &thorn;at it semyth as on bon.  And &thorn;e ne&thorn;ere ende|of &thorn;ese bonys be&thorn; y-Ioyned wi&thorn; &thorn;e bonys of &thorn;e hande, whiche be&thorn;|y-clepyde rasceta &thorn;at beth viij bonys.</P></DIV3>
